obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (28273)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 1st July, 1989, vide notification No. S.O. 368(E), dated 22nd May, 1989, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28273&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Motor Vehicles Act,`
  line 1988.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different State and any reference in`
  line `this Act to the commencement of this Act shall, in relation to a States, be construed as a reference to the`
  line `coming into force of this Act in that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (28274)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28274&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `^1[(1) "adapted vehicle" means a motor vehicle either specially designed and constructed, or to`
  line `which alterations have been made under sub-section (2) of section 52, for the use of a person`
  line `suffering from any physical defect or disability, and used solely by or for such person;`
  line
  line `(1A) "aggregator" means a digital intermediary or market place for a passenger to connect with a`
  line `driver for the purpose of transportation;`
  line
  line `(1B) "area", in relation to any provision of this Act, means such area as the State Government`
  line `may, having regard to the requirements of that provision, specify by notification in the Official`
  line Gazette;]
  line
  line `(2) "articulated vehicle" means a motor vehicle to which a semitrailer is attached;`
  line
  line `(3) "axle weight" means in relation to an axle of a vehicle the total weight transmitted by the`
  line `several wheels attached to that axle to the surface on which the vehicle rests;`
  line
  line `(4) "certificate of registration" means the certificate issued by a competent authority to the effect`
  line `that a motor vehicle has been duly registered in accordance with the provisions of Chapter IV;`
  line
  line `^2[(4A) "community service" means an unpaid work which a person is required to perform as a`
  line `punishment for an offence committed under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(5) "conductor", in relation to a stage carriage, means a person engaged in collecting fares from`
  line `passengers, regulating their entrance into, or exit from, the stage carriage and performing such other`
  line `functions as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(6) "conductor's licence" means the licence issued by a competent authority under Chapter III`
  line `authorising the person specified therein to act as a conductor;`
  line
  line `(7) "contract carriage" means a motor vehicle which carries a passenger or`
  line `passengers for hire or reward and is engaged under a contract, whether expressed or implied, for the`
  line `use of such vehicle as a whole for the carriage of passengers mentioned therein and entered into by a`
  line `person with a holder of a permit in relation to such vehicle or any person authorised by him in this`
  line `behalf on a fixed or an agreed rate or sum--`
  line
  line `(a) on a time basis, whether or not with reference to any route or distance; or`
  line
  line `(b) from one point to another,`
  line `and in either case, without stopping to pick up or set down passengers not included in the contract`
  line `anywhere during the journey, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a maxicab; and`
  line
  line `(ii) a motor cab notwithstanding that separate fares are charged for its passengers;`
  line
  line `(8) "dealer" includes a person who is engaged--`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) in building bodies for attachment to chassis; or`
  line
  line `(c) in the repair of motor vehicles; or`
  line
  line `(d) in the business of hypothecation, leasing or hire-purchase of motor vehicle;`
  line
  line `(9) "driver" includes, in relation to a motor vehicle which is drawn by another motor vehicle, the`
  line `person who acts as a steersman of the drawn vehicle;`
  line
  line `^4[(9A) "driver refresher training course" means the course referred to in sub-section (2A) of section`
  line 19;]
  line
  line `(10) "driving licence" means the licence issued by a competent authority under Chapter II authorising`
  line `the person specified therein to drive, otherwise than as a learner, a motor vehicle or a motor vehicle of`
  line `any specified class or description;`
  line
  line `(11) "educational institution bus" means an omnibus, which is owned by a college, school or other`
  line `educational institution and used solely for the purpose of transporting students or staff of the educational`
  line `institution in connection with any of its activities;`
  line
  line `(12) "fares" includes sums payable for a season ticket or in respect of the hire of a contract carriage;`
  line
  line `^4[(12A) "golden hour" means the time period lasting one hour following a traumatic injury during`
  line `which there is highest likelihood of preventing death by providing prompt medical care;]`
  line
  line `(13) "goods" includes live-stock, and anything (other than equipment ordinarily used with the`
  line `vehicle) carried by a vehicle except living persons, but does not include luggage or personal effects`
  line `carried in a motor car or in a trailer attached to a motor car or the personal luggage of passengers`
  line `travelling in the vehicle;`
  line
  line `(14) "goods carriage" means any motor vehicle constructed or adapted for use solely for the carriage`
  line `of goods, or any motor vehicle not so constructed or adapted when used for the carriage of goods;`
  line
  line `(15) "gross vehicle weight" means in respect of any vehicle the total weight of the vehicle and load`
  line `certified and registered by the registering authority as permissible for that vehicle;`
  line
  line `(16) "heavy goods vehicle" means any goods carriage the gross vehicle weight of which, or a tractor`
  line `or a road-roller the unladen weight of either of which, exceeds 12,000 kilograms;`
  line
  line `(17) "heavy passenger motor vehicle" means any public service vehicle or private service vehicle or`
  line `educational institution bus or omnibus the gross vehicle weight of any of which, or a motor car the`
  line `unladen weight of which, exceeds 12,000 kilograms;`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(19) "learner's licence" means the licence issued by a competent authority under Chapter II`
  line `authorising the person specified therein to drive as a learner, a motor vehicle or a motor vehicle of any`
  line `specified class or description;`
  line
  line `(20) "licensing authority" means an authority empowered to issue licences under Chapter II or, as the`
  line `case may be, Chapter III;`
  line
  line `(21) "light motor vehicle" means a transport vehicle or omnibus the gross vehicle weight of either of`
  line `which or a motor car or tractor or road-roller the unladen weight of any of which, does not exceed`
  line `^6[7500] kilograms;`
  line
  line `^7[(21A) "manufacturer" means a person who is engaged in the manufacture of motor vehicles;]`
  line
  line `(22) "maxicab" means any motor vehicle constructed or adapted to carry more than six passengers,`
  line `but not more than twelve passengers, excluding the driver, for hire or reward;`
  line
  line `(23) "medium goods vehicle" means any goods carriage other than a light motor vehicle or a heavy`
  line `goods vehicle;`
  line
  line `(24) "medium passenger motor vehicle" means any public service vehicle or private service vehicle,`
  line `or educational institution bus other than a motor cycle, ^8[adapted vehicle], light motor vehicle or heavy`
  line `passenger motor vehicle;`
  line
  line `(25) "motorcab" means any motor vehicle constructed or adapted to carry not more than six`
  line `passengers excluding the driver for hire or reward;`
  line
  line `(26) "motor car" means any motor vehicle other than a transport vehicle, omnibus, road-roller,`
  line `tractor, motor cycle or ^8[adapted carriage];`
  line
  line `(27) "motor cycle" means a two-wheeled motor vehicle, inclusive of any detachable side-car having`
  line `an extra wheel, attached to the motor vehicle;`
  line
  line `(28) "motor vehicle" or "vehicle" means any mechanically propelled vehicle adapted for use upon`
  line `roads whether the power of propulsion is transmitted thereto from an external or internal source and`
  line `includes a chassis to which a body has not been attached and a trailer; but does not include a vehicle`
  line `running upon fixed rails or a vehicle of a special type adapted for use only in a factory or in any other`
  line `enclosed premises or a vehicle having less than four wheels fitted with engine capacity of not exceeding`
  line `^9[twenty-five cubic centimetres];`
  line
  line `(29) "omnibus" means any motor vehicle constructed or adapted to carry more than six persons`
  line `excluding the driver;`
  line
  line `(30) "owner" means a person in whose name a motor vehicle stands registered, and where such`
  line `person is a minor, the guardian of such minor, and in relation to a motor vehicle which is the subject of a`
  line `hire-purchase, agreement, or an agreement of lease or an agreement of hypothecation, the person in`
  line `possession of the vehicle under that agreement;`
  line
  line `(31) "permit" means a permit issued by a State or Regional Transport Authority or an authority`
  line `prescribed in this behalf under this Act authorising the use of a motor vehicle as a transport vehicle;`
  line
  line `(32) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(33) "private service vehicle" means a motor vehicle constructed or adapted to carry more than six`
  line `persons excluding the driver and ordinarily used by or on behalf of the owner of such vehicle for the`
  line `purpose of carrying persons for, or in connection with, his trade or business otherwise than for hire or`
  line `reward but does not include a motor vehicle used for public purposes;`
  line
  line `(34) "public place" means a road, street, way or other place, whether a thoroughfare or not, to which`
  line `the public have a right of access, and includes any place or stand at which passengers are picked up or set`
  line `down by a stage carriage;`
  line
  line `(35) "public service vehicle" means any motor vehicle used or adapted to be used for the carriage of`
  line `passengers for hire or reward, and includes a maxicab, a motorcab, contract carriage, and stage carriage;`
  line
  line `(36) "registered axle weight" means in respect of the axle of any vehicle, the axle weight certified and`
  line `registered by the registering authority as permissible for that axle;`
  line
  line `(37) "registering authority" means an authority empowered to register motor vehicles under Chapter`
  line IV;
  line
  line `(38) "route" means a line of travel which specifies the highway which may be traversed by a motor`
  line `vehicle between one terminus and another;`
  line
  line `^10[(38A) "scheme" means a scheme framed under this Act;]`
  line
  line `^11[(39) "semi-trailer" means a vehicle not mechanically propelled (other than a trailer), which is`
  line `intended to be connected to a motor vehicle and which is so constructed that a portion of it is superimposed on, and a part of whose weight is borne by, that motor vehicle;]`
  line
  line `(40) "stage carriage" means a motor vehicle constructed or adapted to carry more than six passengers`
  line `excluding the driver for hire or reward at separate fares paid by or for individual passengers, either for the`
  line `whole journey or for stages of the journey;`
  line
  line `(41) "State Government" in relation to a Union territory means the Administrator thereof appointed`
  line `under article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(42) "State transport undertaking" means any undertaking providing road transport service, where`
  line `such undertaking is carried on by,--`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Government or a State Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) any Road Transport Corporation established under section 3 of the Road Transport`
  line `Corporations Act, 1950 (64 of 1950);`
  line
  line `(iii) any municipality or any corporation or company owned or controlled by the Central`
  line `Government or one or more State Governments, or by the Central Government and one or more State`
  line Governments;
  line
  line `^12[(iv) Zilla Parishad or any other similar local authority.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, "road transport service" means a service of motor`
  line `vehicles carrying passengers or goods or both by road for hire or reward;`
  line
  line `^10[(42A) "testing agency" means any entity designated as a testing agency under section 110B;]`
  line
  line `(43) "tourist vehicle" means a contract carriage constructed or adapted and equipped and maintained`
  line `in accordance with such specifications as may be prescribed in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(44) "tractor" means a motor vehicle which is not itself constructed to carry any load (other than`
  line `equipment used for the purpose of propulsion); but excludes a road-roller;`
  line
  line `(45) "traffic signs" includes all signals, warning sign posts, direction posts, markings on the road or`
  line `other devices for the information, guidance or direction of drivers of motor vehicles;`
  line
  line `(46) "trailer" means any vehicle, other than a semi-trailer and a side-car, drawn or intended to be`
  line `drawn by a motor vehicle;`
  line
  line `(47) "transport vehicle" means a public service vehicle, a goods carriage, an educational institution`
  line `bus or a private service vehicle;`
  line
  line `(48) "unladen weight" means the weight of a vehicle or trailer including all equipment ordinarily used`
  line `with the vehicle or trailer when working, but excluding the weight of a driver or attendant; and where`
  line `alternative parts or bodies are used the unladen weight of the vehicle means the weight of the vehicle with`
  line `the heaviest such alternative part or body;`
  line
  line `(49) "weight" means the total weight transmitted for the time being by the wheels of a vehicle to the`
  line `surface on which the vehicle rests ^10[or moves].`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 2, for clause (1) (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-clause (a) omitted by Act 54 of 1994, s. 2 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Clause (18) omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 2, for 6000 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 2, for "invalid carriage" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 2, for "thirty-five cubic centimetres" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 54 of 1988, s. 2, for clause (39) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (28275)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `e-cart and e-rickshaw.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2015, s. 2 (w.e.f. 7-1-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28275&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[2A. e-cart and e-rickshaw.--(1) Save as otherwise provided in the proviso to sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 7 and sub-section (10) of section 9, the provisions of this Act shall apply to e-cart and e-rickshaw.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, "e-cart or e-rickshaw" means a special purpose battery powered`
  line `vehicle of power not exceeding 4000 watts, having three wheels for carrying goods or passengers, as the`
  line `case may be, for hire or reward, manufactured, constructed or adapted, equipped and maintained in`
  line `accordance with such specifications, as may be prescribed in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_b:
  sectionId (49494)
  sectionNo 2B
  orderNo 4
  title `Promotion of innovation`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49494&sectionno=2B&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_2_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[2B.Promotion of innovation.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act and subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed by the Central Government, in order to promote innovation, research and`
  line `development in the fields of vehicular engineering, mechanically propelled vehicles and transportation in`
  line `general, the Central Government may exempt certain types of mechanically propelled vehicles from the`
  line `application of the provisions of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (28276)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 5
  title `Necessity for driving licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 3 for "a motor cab" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28276&sectionno=3&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall drive a motor vehicle in any public place`
  line `unless he holds an effective driving licence issued to him authorising him to drive the vehicle; and no`
  line `person shall so drive a transport vehicle [other than ^1[a motor cab or motor cycle] hired for his own use or`
  line `rented under any scheme made under sub-section (2) of section 75] unless his driving licence specifically`
  line `entitles him so to do.`
  line
  line `(2) The conditions subject to which sub-section (1) shall not apply to a person receiving instructions`
  line `in driving a motor vehicle shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (28277)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 6
  title `Age limit in connection with driving of motor vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 4, for "a motor cycle without gear" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28277&sectionno=4&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person under the age of`
  line `eighteen years shall drive a motor vehicle in any public place:`
  line
  line `Provided that ^1[a motor cycle with engine capacity not exceeding 50cc] may be driven in a`
  line `public place by a person after attaining the age of sixteen years.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 18, no person under the age of twenty years shall drive a`
  line `transport vehicle in any public place.`
  line
  line `(3) No learners licence or driving licence shall be issued to any person to drive a vehicle of the class`
  line `to which he has made an application unless he is eligible to drive that class of vehicle under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (28278)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 7
  title `Responsibility of owners of motor vehicles for contravention of sections 3 and 4.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28278&sectionno=5&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `No owner`
  line `or person in charge of a motor vehicle shall cause or permit any person who does not satisfy the`
  line `provisions of section 3 or section 4 to drive the vehicle.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (28279)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 8
  title `Restrictions on the holding of driving licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28279&sectionno=6&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, while he holds any driving`
  line `licence for the time being in force, hold any other driving licence except a learner’s licence or a driving`
  line `licence issued in accordance with the provisions of section 18 or a document authorising, in accordance`
  line `with the rules made under section 139, the person specified therein to drive a motor vehicle.`
  line
  line `(2) No holder of a driving licence or a learner’s licence shall permit it to be used by any other person.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall prevent a licensing authority having the jurisdiction referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 9 from adding to the classes of vehicles which the driving licence authorises the`
  line `holder to drive.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (28280)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 9
  title `Restrictions on the granting of learner's licences for certain vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28280&sectionno=7&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) No person shall`
  line `be granted a learner's licence to drive a transport vehicle unless he has held a driving licence to`
  line `drive a light motor vehicle for at least one year:]`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to an e-cart or e-rickshaw.]`
  line
  line `(2) No person under the age of eighteen years shall be granted a learner’s licence to drive a motor`
  line `cycle without gear except with the consent in writing of the person having the care of the person desiring`
  line `the learner’s licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 2015, s. 3 (w.e.f. 7-1-2015)`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (28281)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 10
  title `Grant of learner's licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28281&sectionno=8&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who is not disqualified under section 4 for driving a`
  line `motor vehicle and who is not for the time being disqualified for holding or obtaining a driving licence`
  line `may, subject to the provisions of section 7, apply to ^1[any of the licensing authority in the State]--`
  line
  line `(i) in which he ordinarily resides or carries on business, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in which the school or establishment referred to in section 12 from where he intends to`
  line `receive instruction in driving a motor vehicle is situate,`
  line `for the issue to him of a learner's licence.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be in such form and shall be accompanied by such`
  line `documents ^2[with such fee and submit in such manner, including electronic means] as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application ^3[to drive a transport vehicle made] under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied`
  line `by a medical certificate in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government and signed by such`
  line `registered medical practitioner, as the State Government or any person authorised in this behalf by the`
  line `State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint for this purpose:`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(4) If, from the application or from the medical certificate referred to in sub-section (3), it appears`
  line `that the applicant is suffering from any disease or disability which is likely to cause the driving by him of`
  line `a motor vehicle of the class which he would be authorised by the learner's licence applied for to drive to`
  line `be a source of danger to the public or to the passengers, the licensing authority shall refuse to issue the`
  line `learner's licence:`
  line
  line `Provided that a learners licence limited to driving an ^5[adapted vehicle] may be issued to the`
  line `applicant, if the licensing authority is satisfied that he is fit to drive such a carriage.`
  line
  line `(5) No learner's licence shall be issued to any applicant unless he ^6[`
  line `satisfies such conditions] as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line .
  line
  line `(6) When an application has been duly made to the appropriate licensing authority and the applicant`
  line `has satisfied such authority of his physical fitness under sub-section (3) and has passed to the satisfaction`
  line `of the licensing authority the test referred to in sub-section (5), the licensing authority shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions of section 7, issue the applicant a learner's licence unless the applicant is disqualified under`
  line `section 4 for driving a motor vehicle or is for the time being disqualified for holding or obtaining a`
  line `licence to drive a motor vehicle:`
  line
  line `Provided that a licensing authority may issue a learner's licence to drive a motor cycle or a light`
  line `motor vehicle notwithstanding that it is not the appropriate licensing authority, if such authority is`
  line `satisfied that there is good reason for the applicant's inability to apply to the appropriate licensing`
  line authority.
  line
  line `^7[Provided further that a licencing authority may issue a learner's licence in electronic form and such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the licensing authority may, before issuing the license, verify the identity of the`
  line `applicant in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(7) Where the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by`
  line `rules made in this behalf, exempt generally, either absolutely or subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `specified in the rules, any class of persons from the provisions of sub-section (3), or sub-section (5), or`
  line both.
  line
  line `(8) Any learner's licence for driving a motor cycle in force immediately before the commencement of`
  line `this Act shall, after such commencement, be deemed to be effective for driving a motor cycle with or`
  line `without gear.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s.4, for "the licensing authority having jurisdiction in the area" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "and with such fee" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. The proviso omitted by s. 4, ibid (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "invalid carriage" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "passes to the satisfaction of the licensing authority such test" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `7. The Provisos ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 4 (1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (28282)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 11
  title `Grant of driving licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28282&sectionno=9&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who is not for the time being disqualified for holding or`
  line `obtaining a driving licence may apply to ^1[any licensing authority in the State]--`
  line
  line `(i) in which he ordinarily resides or carries on business, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in which the school or establishment referred to in section 12 from where he is receiving or`
  line `has received instruction in driving a motor vehicle is situated,`
  line
  line `for the issue to him of a driving licence.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be in such form and shall be accompanied by such`
  line `fee and such documents as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) If the applicant passes such test as may be prescribed by the Central Government, he shall be`
  line `issued the driving licence:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such test shall be necessary where the applicant produces proof to show that--`
  line
  line `(a) (i) the applicant has previously held a driving licence to drive such class of vehicle and that`
  line `the period between thed ate of expiry of that licence and the date of the application does not exceed`
  line `five years, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the applicant holds or has previously held a driving licence to drive such class of vehicle`
  line `issued under section 18, or`
  line
  line `(iii) the applicant holds a driving licence to drive such class of vehicle issued by a competent`
  line `authority of any country outside India, subject to the condition that the applicant complies with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (3) of section 8,`
  line
  line `(b) the applicant is not suffering from any disability which is likely to cause the driving by him to`
  line `be a source of danger to the public; and the licensing authority may, for that purpose, require the`
  line `applicant to produce a medical certificate in the same form and in the same manner as is referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 8:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that a driving licence for driving an adapted vehicle may be issued to the`
  line `applicant, if the licensing authority is satisfied that he is fit to drive such motor vehicle.]]`
  line
  line `(4) Where the application is for a licence to drive a transport vehicle, no such authorisation shall be`
  line `granted to any applicant unless he possesses ^4*** a driving certificate issued by a school or establishment`
  line `referred to in section 12.`
  line
  line `^5[(5) Where the applicant does not pass the test; he may be permitted to re-appear for the test after a`
  line `period of seven days:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the applicant does not pass the test even after three appearances, he shall not be`
  line `qualified to re-appear for such test before the expiry of a period of sixty days from the date of last such`
  line `test ^6[and such applicant shall be required to complete a remedial driver training course from any school`
  line `or establishment under section 12].]`
  line
  line `(6) The test of competence to drive shall be carried out in a vehicle of the type to which the`
  line `application refers:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who passed a test in driving a motor cycle with gear shall be deemed also to`
  line `have passed a test in driving a motor cycle without gear.`
  line
  line `(7) When any application has been duly made to the appropriate licensing authority and the applicant`
  line `has satisfied such authority of his competence to drive, the licensing authority shall issue the applicant a`
  line `driving licence unless the applicant is for the time being disqualified for holding or obtaining a driving`
  line `licence:`
  line
  line `Provided that a licensing authority may issue a driving licence to drive a motor cycle or a light motor`
  line `vehicle notwithstanding that it is not the appropriate licensing authority, if the licensing authority is`
  line `satisfied that there is good and sufficient reason for the applicant’s inability to apply to the appropriate`
  line `licensing authority:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the licensing authority shall not issue a new driving licence to the applicant, if`
  line `he had previously held a driving licence, unless it is satisfied that there is good and sufficient reason for`
  line `his inability to obtain a duplicate copy of his former licence.`
  line
  line `(8) If the licensing authority is satisfied, after giving the applicant an opportunity of being heard, that`
  line he--
  line
  line `(a) is a habitual criminal or a habitual drunkard; or`
  line
  line `(b) is a habitual addict to any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance within the meaning of the`
  line `Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985); or`
  line
  line `(c) is a person whose licence to drive any motor vehicle has, at any time earlier, been revoked,`
  line `it may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, make an order refusing to issue a driving licence to such`
  line `person and any person aggrieved by an order made by a licensing authority under this sub-section may,`
  line `within thirty days of the receipt of the order, appeal to the prescribed authority.`
  line
  line `(9) Any driving licence for driving a motor cycle in force immediately before the commencement of`
  line `this Act shall, after such commencement, bedeemed to be effective for driving a motor cycle with or`
  line `without gear.`
  line
  line `^7[(10) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the driving licence to drive e-cart or`
  line `e-rickshaw shall be issued in such manner and subject to such conditions, as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "the licensing authority having jurisdiction in the area" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 7, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 5, for the second proviso (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. The words "such minimum educational qualification as may be prescribed by the Central Government and" omitted by s. 5,`
  line `ibid (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 7, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 5, (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 3 of 2015, s. 4 (w.e.f. 7-1-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (28283)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 12
  title `Form and contents of licences to drive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28283&sectionno=10&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every learner's licence and driving licence, except`
  line `a driving licence issued under section 18, shall be in such form and shall contain such information as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) A learner’s licence or, as the case may be, driving licence shall also be expressed as entitling the`
  line `holder to drive a motor vehicle of one or more of the following classes, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) motor cycle without gear;`
  line
  line `(b) motor cycle with gear;`
  line
  line `(c) ^1[adapted vehicle];`
  line
  line `(d) light motor vehicle;`
  line
  line `^2[(e) transport vehicle;]`
  line
  line `(i) road-roller;`
  line
  line `(j) motor vehicle of a specified description.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 6, for "invalid carriage" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 8, for clauses (e) to (h) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994)`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (28284)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Additions to driving licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28284&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person holding a driving licence to drive any class or`
  line `description of motor vehicles, who is not for the time being disqualified for holding or obtaining a driving`
  line `licence to drive any other class or description of motor vehicles, may apply to ^1[any licensing authority in`
  line `the State] in which he resides or carries on his business in such form and accompanied by such documents`
  line `and with such fees as may be prescribed by the Central Government for the addition of such other class or`
  line `description of motor vehicles to the licence.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such rules as may be prescribed by the Central Government, the provisions of section 9`
  line `shall apply to an application under this section as if the said application were for the grant of a licence`
  line `under that section to drive the class or description of motor vehicles which the applicant desires to be`
  line `added to his licence.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the licensing authority may, before issuing the license verify the identity of the`
  line `applicant in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 7, for "the licensing authority having jurisdiction in the area" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 7, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (28285)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Licensing and regulation of schools or establishments for imparting instruction in driving of motor vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 8, (w.e.f. 1-7-2021)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28285&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may make rules for the purpose of licensing and`
  line `regulating, by the State Governments, schools or establishments (by whatever name called) for imparting`
  line `instruction in driving of motor vehicles and matters connected therewith.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) licensing of such schools or establishments including grant, renewal and revocation of such`
  line licences;
  line
  line `(b) supervision of such schools or establishments;`
  line
  line `(c) the form of application and the form of licence and the particulars to be contained therein;`
  line
  line `(d) fee to be paid with the application for such licences;`
  line
  line `(e) conditions subject to which such licences may be granted;`
  line
  line `(f) appeals against the orders of refusal to grant or renew such licences and appeals against the`
  line `orders revoking such licences;`
  line
  line `(g) conditions subject to which a person may establish and maintain any such school or`
  line `establishment for imparting instruction in driving of motor vehicles;`
  line
  line `(h) nature, syllabus and duration of course or courses for efficient instruction in driving any motor`
  line vehicle;
  line
  line `(i) apparatus and equipments (including motor vehicles fitted with dual control) required for the`
  line `purpose of imparting such instruction;`
  line
  line `(j) suitability of the premises at which such schools or establishments may be established or`
  line `maintained and facilities to be provided therein;`
  line
  line `(k) qualifications, both educational and professional (including experience), which a person`
  line `imparting instruction in driving a motor vehicle shall possess;`
  line
  line `(l) inspection of such schools and establishments (including the services rendered by them and the`
  line `apparatus, equipments and motor vehicles maintained by them for imparting such instruction);`
  line
  line `(m) maintenance of records by such schools or establishments;`
  line
  line `(n) financial stability of such schools or establishments;`
  line
  line `(o) the driving certificates, if any, to be issued by such schools or establishments and the form in`
  line `which such driving certificates shall be issued and the requirements to be complied with for the`
  line `purposes of issuing such certificates;`
  line
  line `(p) such other matters as may be necessary to carry out the purposes of this section.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by`
  line `rules made in this behalf, exempt generally, either absolutely or subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `specified in the rules, any class of schools or establishments imparting instruction in driving of motor`
  line `vehicles or matters connected therewith from the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(4) A school or establishment imparting instruction in driving of motor vehicles or matters connected`
  line `therewith immediately before the commencement of this Act whether under a licence or not, may`
  line `continue to impart such instruction without a licence issued under this Act for a period of one month from such commencement, and if it has made an application for such licence under this Act within the said`
  line `period of one month and such application is in the prescribed form, contains the prescribed particulars and`
  line `is accompanied by the prescribed fee, till the disposal of such application by the licensing authority.`
  line
  line `^1[(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision, where any school or establishment`
  line `has been accredited by a body notified by the Central Government under any other law for the time being`
  line `in force, any person who has successfully completed a training module at such school or establishment`
  line `covering a particular type of motor vehicle shall be eligible to obtain a driving licence for such type of`
  line `motor vehicle.`
  line
  line `(6) The curriculum of the training module referred to in sub-section (5) and the remedial driver`
  line `training course referred to in sub-section (5) of section 9 shall be such as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government and that Government may make rules for the regulation of such schools or`
  line establishments.]
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (28286)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Extent of effectiveness of licences, to drive motor vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28286&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `A learner’s licence or a driving`
  line `licence issued under this Act shall be effective throughout India.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (28287)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Currency of licences to drive motor vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28287&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) A learner's licence issued under this Act`
  line `shall, subject to the other provisions of this Act, be effective for a period of six months from the date of`
  line `issue of the licence.`
  line
  line `(2) A driving licence issued or renewed under this Act shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a licence to drive a transport vehicle, be effective for a period of ^1[five years]:`
  line
  line ^2***
  line
  line `^3[Provided that in the case of licence to drive a transport vehicle carrying goods of dangerous`
  line `or hazardous nature be effective for a period of ^4[three years and renewal thereof shall be subject to`
  line `such conditions as the Central Government may prescribe; and];]`
  line
  line `^5[(b) in the case of any other licence, subject to such conditions as the Central Government may`
  line `prescribe, if the person obtaining the licence, either originally or on renewal thereof,--`
  line
  line `(i) has not attained the age of thirty years on the date of issue or, renewal thereof, be effective`
  line `until the date on which such person attains the age of forty years; or`
  line
  line `(ii) has attained the age of thirty years but has not attained the age of fifty years on the date of`
  line `issue or, renewal thereof, be effective for a period of ten years from the date of such issue or`
  line `renewal; or`
  line
  line `(iii) has attained the age of fifty years but has not attained the age of fifty-five years on the`
  line `date of issue or, renewal thereof, be effective until the date on which such person attains the age`
  line `of sixty years; or`
  line
  line `(iv) has attained the age of fifty-five years on the date of issue or as the case may be, renewal`
  line `thereof, be effective for a period of five years from the date of such issue or renewal.]`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 9, for "three years" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. The word "and" omitted by Act 54 of 1994, s. 9 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for cl. (b) (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `6. The proviso omitted by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (28288)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Renewal of driving licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28288&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any licensing authority may, on application made to it, renew`
  line `a driving licence issued under the provisions of this Act with effect from the date of its expiry:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any case where the application for the renewal of a licence is made ^1[either one year`
  line `prior to date of its expiry or within one year] after the date of its expiry, the driving licence shall be`
  line `renewed with effect from the date of its renewal:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the application is for the renewal of a licence to drive a transport vehicle`
  line `or where in any other case the applicant has attained the age of forty years, the same shall be accompanied`
  line `by a medical certificate in the same form and in the same manner as is referred to in sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 8, and the provisions of sub-section (4) of section 8 shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to`
  line `every such case as they apply in relation to a learners licence.`
  line
  line `(2) An application for the renewal of a driving licence shall be made in such form and accompanied`
  line `by such documents as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application for the renewal of a driving licence is made previous to, or not more than`
  line `^2[one year] after the date of its expiry, the fee payable for such renewal shall be such as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an application for the renewal of a driving licence is made more than 1`
  line `[one year] after the`
  line `date of its expiry, the fee payable for such renewal shall be such amount as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the fee referred to in sub-section (3) may be accepted by the licensing authority in`
  line `respect of an application for the renewal of a driving licence made under this sub-section if it is satisfied`
  line `that the applicant was prevented by good and sufficient cause from applying within the time specified in`
  line `sub-section (3):`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the application is made more than ^3[one year after the driving licence has`
  line `ceased to be effective, the licensing authority shall] refuse to renew the driving licence, unless the`
  line `applicant undergoes and passes to its satisfaction the test of competence to drive referred to in sub-section`
  line `(3) of section 9.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the application for renewal has been rejected, the fee paid shall be refunded to such extent`
  line `and in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the authority renewing the driving licence is not the authority which issued the driving`
  line `licence it shall intimate the fact of renewal to the authority which issued the driving licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "more than thirty days" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 10, for "thirty days" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "five years after the driving licence has ceased to be effective, the licensing authority may" (w.e.f. 1-`
  line `9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (28289)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Revocation of driving licence on grounds of disease or disability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28289&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the foregoing sections, any licensing authority may at any time revoke a driving licence or`
  line `may require, as a condition of continuing to hold such driving licence, the holder thereof to produce a`
  line `medical certificate in the same form and in the same manner as is referred to in sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 8, if the licensing authority has reasonable grounds to belive that the holder of the driving licence`
  line `is, by virtue of any disease or disability, unfit to drive a motor vehicle and where the authority revoking a`
  line `driving licence is not the authority which issued the same, it shall intimate the fact of revocation to the`
  line `authority which issued that licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (28290)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Orders refusing or revoking driving licences and appeals therefrom.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28290&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a licensing`
  line `authority refuses to issue any learner’s licence or to issue or renew, or revokes, any driving licence, or`
  line `refuses to add a class or description of motor vehicle to any driving licence, it shall do so by an order`
  line `communicated to the applicant or the holder, as the case may be, giving the reasons in writing for such`
  line `refusal or revocation.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by an order made under sub-section (1) may, within thirty days of the`
  line `service on him of the order, appeal to the prescribed authority which shall decide the appeal after giving`
  line `such person and the authority which made the order an opportunity of being heard and the decision of the`
  line `appellate authority shall be binding on the authority which made the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (28291)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Driving Licences to drive motor vehicles, belonging to the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28291&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Such`
  line `authority as may be prescribed by the Central Government may issue driving licence valid throughout`
  line `India to persons who have completed their eighteenth year to drive motor vehicles which are the property`
  line `or for the time being under the exclusive control of the Central Government and are used for Government`
  line `purposes relating to the defence of the country and unconnected with any commercial enterprise.`
  line
  line `(2) A driving licence issued under this section shall specify the class or description of vehicle which`
  line `the holder is entitled to drive and the period for which he is so entitled.`
  line
  line `(3) A driving licence issued under this section shall not entitle the holder to drive any motor vehicle`
  line `except a motor vehicle referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The authority issuing any driving licence under this section shall, at the request of any State`
  line `Government, furnish such information respecting any person to whom a driving licence is issued as that`
  line `Government may at any time require.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (28292)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power of licensing authority to disqualify from holding a driving licence or revoke such licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28292&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a licensing authority is satisfied, after giving the holder of a driving licence an`
  line `opportunity of being heard, that he--`
  line
  line `(a) is a habitual criminal or a habitual drunkard; or`
  line
  line `(b) is a habitual addict to any narcotic drug or psychotropic substance within the meaning of the`
  line `Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985); or`
  line
  line `(c) is using or has used a motor vehicle in the commission of a cognizable offence; or`
  line
  line `(d) has by his previous conduct as driver of a motor vehicle shown that his driving is likely to be`
  line `attended with danger to the public; or`
  line
  line `(e) has obtained any driving licence or a licence to drive a particular class or description of motor`
  line `vehicle by fraud or misrepresentation; or`
  line
  line `(f) has committed any such act which is likely to cause nuisance or danger to the public, as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Central Government, having regard to the objects of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(g) has failed to submit to, or has not passed, the tests referred to in the proviso to sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 22; or`
  line
  line `(h) being a person under the age of eighteen years who has been granted a learner's licence or a`
  line `driving licence with the consent in writing of the person having the care of the holder of the licence`
  line `and has ceased to be in such care,`
  line
  line `it may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, make an order--`
  line
  line `(i) disqualifying that person for a specified period for holding or obtaining any driving licence to`
  line `drive all or any classes or descriptions of vehicles specified in the licence; or`
  line
  line `(ii) revoke any such licence.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) Where a licence has been forwarded to the licensing authority under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 206, the licensing authority, if satisfied after giving the holder of the driving licence an`
  line `opportunity of being heard, may either discharge the holder of a driving licence or, it may for detailed`
  line `reasons recorded in writing, make an order disqualifying such person from holding or obtaining any`
  line `licence to drive all or any class or description of vehicles specified in the licence--`
  line
  line `(a) for a first offence, for a period of three months;`
  line
  line `(b) for a second or subsequent offence, with revocation of the driving licence of such person:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a driving licence is revoked under this section, the name of the holder of such`
  line `driving licence may be placed in the public domain in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.]
  line
  line `(2) Where an order under sub-section (1) ^2[or sub-section (1A)] is made, the holder of a driving`
  line `licence shall forthwith surrender his driving licence to the licensing authority making the order, if the`
  line `driving licence has not already been surrendered, and the licensing authority shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the driving licence is a driving licence issued under this Act, keep it until the`
  line `disqualification has expired or has been removed; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it is not a driving licence issued under this Act, endorse the disqualification upon it and send`
  line `it to the licensing authority by which it was issued; or`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of revocation of any licence, endorse the revocation upon it and if it is not the`
  line `authority which issued the same, intimate the fact of revocation to the authority which issued that`
  line `licence:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that the driving licence shall be returned to the holder at the end of the period of`
  line `disqualification only if he successfully completes the driver refresher training course.]`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(2A) The licence holder whose licence has been suspended shall undergo the driver refresher training`
  line `course from a school or establishment licenced and regulated under section 12 or such other agency, as`
  line `may be notified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2B) The nature, syllabus and duration of the driver refresher training course shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(3) Any person aggrieved by an order made by a licensing authority under sub-section (1) ^2[or subsection (1A)] may, within thirty days of the receipt of the order, appeal to the prescribed authority, and`
  line `such appellate authority shall give notice to the licensing authority and hear either party if so required by`
  line `that party and may pass such order as it thinks fit and an order passed by any such appellate authority`
  line `shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 11, (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. The Proviso subs. by s. 11, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 11, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (28293)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power of Court to disqualify.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28293&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person is convicted of an offence under this Act or`
  line `of an offence in the commission of which a motor vehicle was used, the Court by which such person is`
  line `convicted may, subject to the provisions of this Act, in addition to imposing any other punishment authorised by law, declare the persons so convicted to be disqualified, for such period as the Court may`
  line `specify, from holding any driving licence to drive all classes or description of vehicles, or any particular`
  line `class or description of such vehicles, as are specified in such licence:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of an offence punishable under section 183 no such order shall be made for`
  line `the first or second offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a person is convicted of an offence under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 132,`
  line `section 134 or section 185, the Court convicting any person of any such offence shall order the`
  line `disqualification under sub-section (1), and if the offence is relatable to clause (c) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 132 or section 134, such disqualification shall be for a period of not less than one month, and if`
  line `the offence is relatable to section 185, such disqualification shall be for a period of not less than six`
  line months.
  line
  line `(3) A Court shall, unless for special reasons to be recorded in writing it thinks fit to order otherwise,`
  line `order the disqualification of a person-`
  line
  line `(a) who having been convicted of an offence punishable under section 184 is again convicted of`
  line `an offence punishable under that section,`
  line
  line `(b) who is convicted of an offence punishable under section 189, or`
  line
  line `(c) who is convicted of an offence punishable under section 192:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of disqualification shall not exceed, in the case referred to in clause (a), five`
  line `years, or, in the case referred to in clause (b), two years or, in the case referred to in clause (c), one year.`
  line
  line `(4) A Court ordering the disqualification of a person convicted of an offence punishable under section`
  line `184 may direct that such person shall, whether he has previously passed the test of competence to drive as`
  line `referred to in sub-section (3) of section 9 or not, remain disqualified until he has subsequent to the making`
  line `of the order of disqualification passed that test to the satisfaction of the licensing authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Court to which an appeal would ordinarily lie from any conviction of an offence of the nature`
  line `specified in sub-section (1) may set aside or vary any order of disqualification made under that`
  line `sub-section notwithstanding that no appeal would lie against the conviction as a result of which such`
  line `order of disqualification was made.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (28294)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Suspension of driving licence in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28294&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in relation to a person who had`
  line `been previously convicted of an offence punishable under section 184, a case is registered by a police`
  line `officer on the allegation that such person has, by such dangerous driving as is referred to in the said`
  line `section 184, of any class or description of motor vehicle caused the death of, or grievous hurt to, one or`
  line `more persons, the driving licence held by such person shall in relation to such class or description of`
  line `motor vehicle become suspended--`
  line
  line `(a) for a period of six months from the date on which the case is registered, or`
  line
  line `(b) if such person is discharged or acquitted before the expiry of the period aforesaid, until such`
  line `discharge or acquittal, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Where by virtue of the provisions of sub-section (1), the driving licence held by a person becomes`
  line `suspended, the police officer, by whom the case referred to in sub-section (1) is registered, shall bring`
  line `such suspension to the notice of the Court competent to take cognizance of such offence, and thereupon,`
  line `such Court shall take possession of the driving licence, endorse the suspension thereon and intimate the`
  line `fact of such endorsement to the licensing authority by which the licence was granted or last renewed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the person referred to in sub-section (1) is acquitted or discharged, the Court shall cancel`
  line `the endorsement on such driving licence with regard to the suspension thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) If a driving licence in relation to a particular class or description of motor vehicles is suspended`
  line `under sub-section (1), the person holding such licence shall be debarred from holding or obtaining any`
  line `licence to drive such particular class or description of motor vehicles so long as the suspension of the`
  line `driving licence remains in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (28295)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Suspension or cancellation of driving licence on conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28295&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (3) of section 20 where a person, referred to in sub-section (1) of section 21 is`
  line `convicted of an offence of causing, by such dangerous driving as is referred to in section 184 of any class`
  line `or description of motor vehicle the death of, or grievous hurt to, one or more persons, the Court by which`
  line `such person is convicted may cancel, or suspend for such period as it may think fit, the driving licence`
  line `held by such person in so far as it relates to that class or description of motor vehicle.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 20, if a person, having been`
  line `previously convicted of an offence punishable under section 185 is again convicted of an offence`
  line `punishable under that section, the Court, making such subsequent conviction, shall, by order, cancel the`
  line `driving licence held by such person.`
  line
  line `(3) If a driving licence is cancelled or suspended under this section, the Court shall take the driving`
  line `licence in its custody, endorse the cancellation or, as the case may be, suspension, thereon and send the`
  line `driving licence so endorsed to the authority by which the licence was issued or last renewed and such`
  line `authority shall, on receipt of the licence, keep the licence in its safe custody, and in the case of a`
  line `suspended licence, return the licence to the holder thereof after the expiry of the period of suspension on`
  line `an application made by him for such return:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such licence shall be returned unless the holder thereof has, after the expiry of the`
  line `period of suspension, undergone and passed, to the satisfaction of the licensing authority by which the`
  line `licence was issued or last renewed, a fresh test of competence to drive referred to in sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 9 and produced a medical certificate in the same form and in the same manner as is referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 8.`
  line
  line `(4) If a licence to drive a particular class or description of motor vehicles is cancelled or suspended`
  line `under this section, the person holding such a licence shall be debarred from holding, or obtaining, any`
  line `licence to drive such particular class or description of motor vehicles so long as the cancellation or`
  line `suspension of the driving licence remains in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (28296)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 25
  title `Effect of disqualification order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28296&sectionno=23&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person in respect of whom any disqualification order is`
  line `made under section 19 or section 20 shall be debarred to the extent and for the period specified in such`
  line `order from holding or obtaining a driving licence and the driving licence, if any, held by such person at`
  line `the date of the order shall cease to be effective to such extent and during such period.`
  line
  line `(2) The operation of a disqualification order made under section 20 shall not be suspended or`
  line `postponed while an appeal is pending against such order or against the conviction as a result of which`
  line `such order is made, unless the appellate court so directs.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person in respect of whom any disqualification order has been made may at any time after the`
  line `expiry of six months from the date of the order apply to the Court or other authority by which the order`
  line `was made, to remove the disqualification; and the Court or authority, as the case may be, may, having`
  line `regard to all the circumstances, either cancel or vary the disqualification order:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Court or other authority refuses to cancel or vary any disqualification order`
  line `under this section, a second application thereunder shall not be entertained before the expiry of a period of`
  line `three months from the date of such refusal.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (28297)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title Endorsement.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28297&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court or authority making an order of disqualification shall endorse or`
  line `cause to be endorsed upon the driving licence if any, held by the person disqualified, particulars of the`
  line `order of disqualification and of any conviction of an offence in respect of which an order of`
  line `disqualification is made; and particulars of any cancellation or variation of an order of disqualification`
  line `made under sub-section (3) of section 23 shall be similarly so endorsed.`
  line
  line `(2) A Court by which any person is convicted of an offence under this Act as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government, having regard to the objects of this Act, shall, whether or not a disqualification`
  line `order is made in respect of such conviction, endorse or cause to be endorsed particulars of such conviction`
  line `on any driving licence held by the person convicted.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person accused of an offence prescribed under sub-section (2) shall when attending the Court`
  line `bring with him his driving licence if it is in his possession.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any person is convicted of any offence under this Act and sentenced to imprisonment for a`
  line `period exceeding three months the Court awarding the sentence shall endorse the fact of such sentence`
  line `upon the driving licence of the person concerned and the prosecuting authority shall intimate the fact of`
  line `such endorsement to the authority by which the driving licence was granted or last renewed.`
  line
  line `(5) When the driving licence is endorsed or caused to be endorsed by any Court, such Court shall`
  line `send the particulars of the endorsement to the licensing authority by which the driving licence was`
  line `granted or last renewed.`
  line
  line `(6) Where on an appeal against any conviction or order of a Court, which has been endorsed on a`
  line `driving licence, the appellate court varies or sets aside the conviction or order, the appellate court shall`
  line `inform the licensing authority by which the driving licence was granted or last renewed and such`
  line `authority shall amend or cause to be amended the endorsement.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (28298)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Transfer of endorsement and issue of driving licence free from endorsement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28298&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) An`
  line `endorsement on any driving licence shall be transferred to any new or duplicate driving licence obtained`
  line `by the holder thereof until the holder becomes entitled under the provisions of this section to have a`
  line `driving licence issued to him free from endorsement.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a driving licence is required to be endorsed and the driving licence is not in the possession`
  line `of the Court or authority by which the endorsement is to be made, then--`
  line
  line `(a) if the person in respect of whom the endorsement is to be made is at the time the holder of a`
  line `driving licence, he shall produce the driving licence to the Court or authority within five days, or such`
  line `longer time as the Court or authority may fix; or`
  line
  line `(b) if, not being then the holder of a driving licence, he subsequently obtains a driving licence, he`
  line `shall within five days after obtaining the driving licence produce it to the Court or authority,`
  line
  line `and if the driving licence is not produced within the time specified, it shall, on the expiration of such time,`
  line `be of no effect until it is produced for the purpose of endorsement.`
  line
  line `(3) A person whose driving licence has been endorsed shall, if during a continuous period of three`
  line `years after such endorsement no further endorsement has been made against him, be entitled on`
  line `surrendering his driving licence and on payment of a fee of five rupees, to receive a new driving licence`
  line `free from all endorsements:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the endorsement is only in respect of an offence contravening the speed limits`
  line `referred to in section 112, such person shall be entitled to receive a new driving licence free from such`
  line `endorsements on the expiration of one year of the date of the endorsement:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in reckoning the said period of three years and one year, respectively, any period`
  line `during which the said person was disqualified for holding or obtaining a driving licence shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25_a:
  sectionId (50171)
  sectionNo 25A
  orderNo 28
  title `National Register of Driving Licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=50171&sectionno=25A&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[25A. National Register of Driving Licences.---(1) The Central Government shall maintain a`
  line `National Register of Driving Licences in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) All State Registers of Driving Licences shall be subsumed under the National Register of`
  line `Driving Licences by a date to be notified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) No driving licence issued, or renewed, under this Act shall be valid unless it has been issued a`
  line `unique driving licence number under the National Register of Driving Licences.`
  line
  line `(4) All State Governments and licensing authorities under this Act shall transmit all information`
  line `including contained data in the State Register of Driving Licences in such form and manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Governments shall be entitled to access the National Register and update their`
  line `records in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (28299)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 29
  title `Maintenance of State Registers of Driving Licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28299&sectionno=26&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[26. Maintenance of State Registers of Driving Licences.-- Each State Government shall`
  line `maintain, in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government, a register to be known as the`
  line `State Register of Driving Licences, in respect of driving licences issued and renewed by the licensing`
  line `authorities of the State Government, containing particulars, including--`
  line
  line `(a) names and addresses of holders of driving licences;`
  line
  line `(b) licence numbers;`
  line
  line `(c) dates of issue or renewal of licences;`
  line
  line `(d) dates of expiry of licences;`
  line
  line `(e) classes and types of vehicles authorised to be driven; and`
  line
  line `(f) such other particulars as the Central Government may prescribe.]`
  line
  line `(2) Each State Government shall supply to the Central Government a ^2[printed copy or copy in such`
  line `other form as the Central Government may require] of the State Register of Driving Licences and shall`
  line `inform the Central Government without delay of all additions to and other amendments in such register`
  line `made from time to time.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Register of Driving Licences shall be maintained in such manner as may be prescribed`
  line `by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for the section 26 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 10, for "printed copy" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (28300)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28300&sectionno=27&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may make rules--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) specifications relating to e-cart and e-rickshaw under sub-section (2) of section 2A;]`
  line
  line `^2[(aa)] regarding conditions referred to in sub-section (2) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) providing for the form in which the application for learner’s licence may be made, the`
  line `information it shall contain and the documents to be submitted with the application referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) providing for the form of medical certificate referred to in sub-section (3) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(d) providing for the particulars for the test referred to in sub-section (5) of section 8;`
  line
  line `^3[(da) the form and manner in which a licensing authority may issue a learner’s licence under`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(db) the manner in which a licensing authority may verify the identity of the applicant under the`
  line `third proviso to sub-section (6) of section 8;]`
  line
  line `(e) providing for the form in which the application for driving licence may be made, the`
  line `information it shall contain and the documents to be submitted with the application referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(f) providing for the particulars regarding test of competence to drive, referred to in sub-section`
  line `(3) of section 9;`
  line
  line `^2[(ff) the manner and the conditions subject to which the driving licence may be issued under`
  line `sub-section (10) of section 9;]`
  line
  line `(g) specifying the minimum educational qualifications of persons to whom licences to drive`
  line `transport vehicles may be issued under this Act and the time within which such qualifications are to`
  line `be acquired by such persons;`
  line
  line `(h) providing for the form and contents of the licences referred to in sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(i) providing for the form and contents of the application referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 11 and documents to be submitted with the application and the fee to be charged;`
  line
  line `(j) providing for the conditions subject to which section 9 shall apply to an application made`
  line `under section 11;`
  line
  line `^3[(ja) the curriculum of training modules and the regulation of schools and establishments under`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(jb) the conditions for the renewal of licence to drive transport vehicles carrying goods of`
  line `dangerous or hazardous nature and other motor vehicles under clause (a) and clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(jc) the manner in which a licensing authority may verify the identity of the applicant under the`
  line `third proviso to sub-section (2) of section 11;]`
  line
  line `(k) providing for the form and contents of the application referred to in sub-section (1) of section`
  line `15 and the documents to accompany such application under sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(l) providing for the authority to grant licences under sub-section (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(m) specifying the fees payable under sub-section (2) of section 8, sub-section (2) of section 9 and`
  line `sub-sections (3) and (4) of section 15 for the grant of learner’s licences, and for the grant and renewal`
  line `of driving licences and licences for the purpose of regulating the schools or establishment for`
  line `imparting instructions in driving motor vehicles;`
  line
  line `(n) specifying the acts for the purposes of clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `^4[(na) the manner of placing in the public domain of the name of the licence holder as referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1A) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(nb) providing for the nature, syllabus and duration of the driver refresher training course as`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2B) of section 19;]`
  line
  line `(o) specifying the offences under this Act for the purposes of sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `^4[(oa) all or any of the matters referred to in section 25A;]`
  line
  line `(p) to provide for all or any of the matters referred to in ^5*** section 26;`
  line
  line `(q) any other matter which is, or has to be, prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2015, s. 5 (w.e.f. 7-1-2015).`
  line `2. Clause (a) renumbered as clause (aa) thereof by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-1-2015).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line `5. The words, brackets and figure "sub-section (1) of" omitted by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (28301)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Clause (j) omitted by s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28301&sectionno=28&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Government may make rules for the`
  line `purpose of carrying into effect the provisions of this Chapter other than the matters specified in`
  line `section 27.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the appointment, jurisdiction, control and functions of licensing authorities and other`
  line `prescribed authorities;`
  line
  line `(b) the conduct and hearing of appeals that may be preferred under this Chapter, the fees to be`
  line `paid in respect of such appeals and the refund of such fees:`
  line
  line `Provided that no fee so fixed shall exceed twenty-five rupees;`
  line
  line `(c) the issue of duplicate licences to replace licences lost, destroyed or mutilated, the replacement`
  line `of photographs which have become obsolete and the fees to be charged therefor;`
  line
  line `(d) the badges and uniform to be worn by drivers of transport vehicles and the fees to be paid in`
  line `respect of badges;`
  line
  line `(e) the fee payable for the issue of a medical certificate under sub-section (3) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(f) the exemption of prescribed persons, or prescribed classes of persons, from payment of all or`
  line `any portion of the fees payable under this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(g) the communication of particulars of licences granted by one licensing authority to other`
  line `licensing authorities;`
  line
  line `(h) the duties, functions and conduct of such persons to whom licences to drive transport vehicles`
  line `are issued;`
  line
  line `(i) the exemption of drivers of road-rollers from all or any of the provisions of this Chapter or of`
  line `the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `^1* * * *`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (28302)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 32
  title `Necessity for conductor's licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28302&sectionno=29&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall act as a conductor of a stage carriage`
  line `unless he holds an effective conductors licence issued to him authorising him to act as such conductor;`
  line `and no person shall employ or permit any person who is not so licensed to act as a conductor of a stage`
  line carriage.
  line
  line `(2) A State Government may prescribe the conditions subject to which sub-section (1) shall not apply`
  line `to a driver of a stage carriage performing the functions of a conductor or to a person employed to act as a`
  line `conductor for a period not exceeding one month.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (28303)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 33
  title `Grant of conductor's licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28303&sectionno=30&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who possesses such minimum educational`
  line `qualification as may be prescribed by the State Government and is not disqualified under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 31 and who is not for the time being disqualified for holding or obtaining a conductor's licence`
  line `may apply to the licensing authority having jurisdiction in the area in which he ordinarily resides or`
  line `carries on business for the issue to him of a conductor's licence.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be in such form and shall contain such information`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application for a conductor's licence shall be accompanied by a medical certificate in such`
  line `form as may be prescribed, signed by a registered medical practitioner and shall also be accompanied by`
  line `two clear copies of a recent photograph of the applicant.`
  line
  line `(4) A conductor's licence issued under this Chapter shall be in such form and contain such particulars`
  line `as may be prescribed and shall be effective throughout the State in which it is issued.`
  line
  line `(5) The fee for a conductor's licence and for each renewal thereof shall be one-half of that for a`
  line `driving licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (28304)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 34
  title `Disqualifications for the grant of conductor's licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28304&sectionno=31&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person under the age of`
  line `eighteen years shall hold, or be granted, a conductor's licence.`
  line
  line `(2) The licensing authority may refuse to issue a conductor's licence--`
  line
  line `(a) if the applicant does not possess the minimum educational qualification;`
  line
  line `(b) if the medical certificate produced by the applicant discloses that he is physically unfit to act`
  line `as a conductor; and`
  line
  line `(c) if any previous conductor's licence held by the applicant was revoked.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (28305)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 35
  title `Revocation of a conductor's licence on grounds of disease or disability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28305&sectionno=32&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `A conductor's`
  line `licence may at any time be revoked by any licensing authority if that authority has reasonable grounds to`
  line `believe that the holder of the licence is suffering from any disease or disability which is likely to render`
  line `him permanently unfit to hold such a licence and where the authority revoking a conductor's licence is`
  line `not the authority which issued the same, it shall intimate the fact of such revocation to the authority which`
  line `issued that licence:`
  line
  line `Provided that before revoking any licence, the licensing authority shall give the person holding such`
  line `licence a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (28306)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 36
  title `Orders refusing, etc, conductor's licences and appeals therefrom.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28306&sectionno=33&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a licensing`
  line `authority refuses to issue or renew, or revokes any conductor's licence, it shall do so by an order`
  line `communicated to the applicant or the holder, as the case may be, giving the reasons in writing for such`
  line `refusal or revocation.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by an order made under sub-section (1) may, within thirty days of the`
  line `service on him of the order, appeal to the prescribed authority which shall decide the appeal after giving`
  line `such person and the authority which made the order an opportunity of being heard and the decision of the`
  line `appellate authority shall be binding on the authority which made the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (28307)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power of licensing authority to disqualify.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28307&sectionno=34&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any licensing authority is of opinion that it is`
  line `necessary to disqualify the holder of a conductor's licence for holding or obtaining such a licence on`
  line `account of his previous conduct as a conductor, it may, for reasons to be recorded, make an order`
  line `disqualifying that person for a specified period, not exceeding one year, for holding or obtaining a`
  line `conductor's licence:`
  line
  line `Provided that before disqualifying the holder of a licence, the licensing authority shall give the person`
  line `holding such licence a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the issue of any such order, the holder of the conductor's licence shall forthwith surrender`
  line `the licence to the authority making the order, if the licence has not already been surrendered, and the`
  line `authority shall keep the licence until the disqualification has expired or has been removed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the authority disqualifying the holder of a conductor's licence under this section is not the`
  line `authority which issued the licence, it shall intimate the fact of such disqualification to the authority which`
  line `issued the same.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by an order made under sub-section (1) may, within thirty days of the`
  line `service on him of the order, appeal to the prescribed authority which shall decide the appeal after giving`
  line `such person and the authority which made the order an opportunity of being heard and the decision of the`
  line `appellate authority shall be binding on the authority which made the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (28308)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power of Court to disqualify.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28308&sectionno=35&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person holding a conductor's licence is convicted`
  line `of an offence under this Act, the Court by which such person is convicted may, in addition to imposing`
  line `any other punishment authorised by law, declare the person so convicted to be disqualified for such`
  line `period as the Court may specify for holding a conductor's licence.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court to which an appeal lies from any conviction of an offence under this Act may set aside`
  line `or vary any order of disqualification made by the Court below, and the Court to which appeals ordinarily`
  line `lie from such Court, may set aside or vary any order of disqualification made by that Court,`
  line `notwithstanding that no appeal lies against the conviction in connection with which such order was made.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (28309)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 39
  title `Certain provisions of Chapter II to apply to conductor's licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28309&sectionno=36&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 6, sections 14, 15 and 23, sub-section (1) of section 24 and section 25 shall, so`
  line `far as may be, apply in relation to a conductors licence, as they apply in relation to a driving licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (28310)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 40
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28310&sectionno=37&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `If any licence to act as a conductor of a stage carriage (by whatever name called) has`
  line `been issued in any State and is effective immediately before the commencement of this Act, it shall`
  line `continue to be effective, notwithstanding such commencement, for the period for which it would have`
  line `been effective, if this Act had not been passed, and every such licence shall be deemed to be a licence`
  line `issued under this Chapter as if this Chapter had been in force on the date on which that licence was`
  line granted.
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (28311)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28311&sectionno=38&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Government may make rules for the`
  line `purpose of carrying into effect the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the appointment, jurisdiction, control and functions of licensing authorities and other`
  line `prescribed authorities under this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions subject to which drivers of stage carriages performing the functions of a`
  line `conductor and persons temporarily employed to act as conductors may be exempted from the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(c) the minimum educational qualifications of conductors; their duties and functions and the`
  line `conduct of persons to whom conductor's licences are issued;`
  line
  line `(d) the form of application for conductor's licences or for renewal of such licences and the`
  line `particulars it may contain;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which conductor's licences may be issued or renewed and the particulars it may`
  line contain;
  line
  line `(f) the issue of duplicate licences to replace licences lost, destroyed or mutilated, the replacement`
  line `of photographs which have become obsolete and the fees to be charged therefor;`
  line
  line `(g) the conduct and hearing of appeals that may be preferred under this Chapter, the fees to be`
  line `paid in respect of such appeals and the refund of such fees:`
  line
  line `Provided that no fee so fixed shall exceed twenty-five rupees;`
  line
  line `(h) the badges and uniform to be worn by conductors of stage carriages and the fees to be paid in`
  line `respect of such badges;`
  line
  line `(i) the grant of the certificates referred to in sub-section (3) of section 30 by registered medical`
  line `practitioners and the form of such certificates;`
  line
  line `(j) the conditions subject to which, and the extent to which, a conductor's licence issued in`
  line `another State shall be effective in the State;`
  line
  line `(k) the communication of particulars of conductor's licences from one authority to other`
  line `authorities; and`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (28312)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 42
  title `Necessity for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28312&sectionno=39&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `No person shall drive any motor vehicle and no owner of a motor`
  line `vehicle shall cause or permit the vehicle to be driven in any public place or in any other place unless the`
  line `vehicle is registered in accordance with this Chapter and the certificate of registration of the vehicle has`
  line `not been suspended or cancelled and the vehicle carries a registration mark displayed in the prescribed`
  line `manner:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to a motor vehicle in possession of a dealer subject to`
  line `such conditions as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (28313)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 43
  title `Registration, where to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 16, for "a registering authority" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28313&sectionno=40&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 42, section 43 and section`
  line `60, every owner of a motor vehicle shall cause the vehicle to be registered by ^1[any registering authority`
  line `in the State] in whose jurisdiction he has the residence or place of business where the vehicle is normally`
  line kept.
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (28314)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 44
  title `Registration, how to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28314&sectionno=41&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application by or on behalf of the owner of a motor`
  line `vehicle for registration shall be in such form and shall be accompanied by such documents, particulars`
  line `and information and shall be made within such period as may be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a motor vehicle is jointly owned by more persons than one, the application shall`
  line `be made by one of them on behalf of all the owners and such applicant shall be deemed to be the owner of`
  line `the motor vehicle for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that in the case of a new motor vehicle, the application for registration in the State`
  line `shall be made by the dealer of such motor vehicle, if the new motor vehicle is being registered in the same`
  line `State in which the dealer is situated.]`
  line
  line `(2) An application referred to in sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by such fee as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The registering authority shall issue ^2[a certificate of registration in the name of the owner] in such`
  line `form and containing such particulars and information and in such manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) In addition to the other particulars required to be included in the certificate of registration, it shall`
  line `also specify the type of the motor vehicle, being a type as the Central Government may, having regard to`
  line `the design, construction and use of the motor vehicle, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `(5) The registering authority shall enter the particulars of the certificate referred to in sub-section (3)`
  line `in a register to be maintained in such form and manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The registering authority shall assign to the vehicle, for display thereon, a distinguishing mark`
  line `(in this Act referred to as the registration mark) consisting of one of the groups of such of those letters`
  line `and followed by such letters and figures as are allotted to the State by the Central Government from time`
  line `to time by notification in the Official Gazette, and displayed and shown on the motor vehicle in such form`
  line `and in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that in case of a new motor vehicle, the application for the registration of which is made`
  line `under the second proviso to sub-section (1), such motor vehicle shall not be delivered to the owner until`
  line `such registration mark is displayed on the motor vehicle in such form and manner as may prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(7) A certificate of registration issued under sub-section (3), whether before or after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, in respect of a motor vehicle, ^4***, shall, subject to the provisions contained`
  line `in this Act, be valid only for a period of fifteen years from the date of issue of such certificate ^3[or for`
  line `such period as may be prescribed by the Central Government] and shall be renewable.`
  line
  line `(8) An application by or on behalf of the owner of a motor vehicle, ^4***, for the renewal of a`
  line `certificate of registration shall be made within such period and in such form, containing such particulars`
  line `and information as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(9) An application referred to in sub-section (8) shall be accompanied by such fee as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(10) Subject to the provisions of section 56, the registering authority may, on receipt of an application`
  line `under sub-section (8), renew the certificate of registration ^5[for such period, as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government] and intimate the fact to the original registering authority, if it is not the original`
  line `registering authority.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that the Central Government may prescribe different period of renewal for different types`
  line `of motor vehicles.]`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
  line
  line `(14) An application for the issue of a duplicate certificate of registration shall be made to the ^7[last`
  line `registering authority] in such form, containing such particulars and information along with such fee as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 41, Central Act 59 of 1988.—In section 41 of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988`
  line `(Central Act 59 of 1988),-`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-sections (7) and (8), the expression, “other than a transport vehicle,” shall be deleted;`
  line
  line `(b) after sub-section (7) so amended, the following proviso shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `“Provided that in the case of transport vehicles, State Government may require the transport vehicles`
  line `to be re-registered in the manner prescribed, subject to the age limit, if any, prescribed under section 59 of`
  line `the Act.”; and`
  line
  line `(c) in sub-section (10) after the words “for a period of five years” and before the words “and`
  line `intimate”, the expression “on payment of all taxes, penalties and interest, if any, levied by the State`
  line `Government” shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 1 of 2002, s. 2.]`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "to the owner of a motor vehicle registered by it a certificate of registration" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 17, (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. The words "other than a transport vehicle" omitted by s. 17, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "for a period of five years" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Sub-sections (11), (12), (13) omitted by s. 17, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-7-2021).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 11, for "original registering authority" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (28315)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 45
  title `Special provision for registration of motor vehicles of diplomatic officers, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28315&sectionno=42&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `.(1) Where an`
  line `application for registration of a motor vehicle is made under sub-section (1) of section 41 by or on behalf`
  line `of any diplomatic officer or consular officer, then, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3)`
  line `or sub-section (6) of that section, the registering authority shall register the vehicle in such manner and in`
  line `accordance with such procedure as may be provided by rules made in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Government under sub-section (3) and shall assign to the vehicle for display thereon a special registration`
  line `mark in accordance with the provisions contained in those rules and shall issue a certificate (hereafter in`
  line `this section referred to as the certificate of registration) that the vehicle has been registered under this`
  line `section; and any vehicle so registered shall not, so long as it remains the property of any diplomatic`
  line `officer or consular officer, require to be registered otherwise under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) If any vehicle registered under this section ceases to be the property of any diplomatic officer or`
  line `consular officer, the certificate of registration issued under this section shall also cease to be effective, and`
  line `the provisions of sections 39 and 40 shall thereupon apply.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may make rules for the registration of motor vehicles belonging to`
  line `diplomatic officers and consular officers regarding the procedure to be followed by the registering`
  line `authority for registering such vehicles, the form in which the certificates of registration of such vehicles`
  line `are to be issued, the manner in which such certificates of registration are to be sent to the owners of the`
  line `vehicles and the special registration marks to be assigned to such vehicles.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this section, "diplomatic officer" or "consular officer" means any person who`
  line `is recognised as such by the Central Government and if any question arises as to whether a person is or is`
  line `not such an officer, the decision of the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (28316)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 46
  title `Temporary registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 18, for section 43 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28316&sectionno=43&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `^1[43. Temporary registration.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in section 40, the owner of a`
  line `motor vehicle may apply to any registering authority or other authority as may be prescribed by the State`
  line `Government to have the motor vehicle temporarily registered and such authority shall issue a temporary`
  line `certificate of registration and temporary registration mark in accordance with such rules as may be made`
  line `by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may register a motor vehicle that plies, temporarily, within the`
  line `State and issue a certificate of registration and registration mark for a period of one month in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed by the State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (28317)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 47
  title `Production of vehicle at the time of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by, s. 19, ibid., for section 44 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28317&sectionno=44&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `^1[44. Production of vehicle at the time of registration.-- (1) Subject to such terms and conditions as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government in this behalf, a motor vehicle sold by an authorised dealer`
  line `shall not require production before a registering authority for the purposes of registration for the first`
  line time.
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such terms and conditions as may be prescribed by the State Government, a person in`
  line `whose name a certificate of registration has been issued shall not be required to produce the vehicle`
  line `registered or transferred before a registering authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (28318)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 48
  title `Refusal of registration or renewal of the certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28318&sectionno=45&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The registering authority`
  line `may, by order, refuse to register any motor vehicle, or renew the certificate of registration in respect of a`
  line `motor vehicle (other than a transport vehicle), if in either case, the registering authority has reason to`
  line `believe that it is a stolen motor vehicle or the vehicle is mechanically defective or fails to comply with the`
  line `requirements of this Act or of the rules made thereunder, or if the applicant fails to furnish particulars of`
  line `any previous registration of the vehicle or furnishes inaccurate particulars in the application for`
  line `registration of the vehicle or, as the case may be, for renewal of the certificate or registration thereof and`
  line `the registering authority shall furnish the applicant whose vehicle is refused registration, or whose`
  line `application for renewal of the certificate of registration is refused, a copy of such order, together with the`
  line `reasons for such refusal.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (28319)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 49
  title `Effectiveness in India of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28319&sectionno=46&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 47, a motor vehicle`
  line `registered in accordance with this Chapter in any State shall not require to be registered elsewhere in`
  line `India and a certificate of registration issued or in force under this Act in respect of such vehicle shall be`
  line `effective throughout India.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (28320)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 50
  title `Assignment of new registration mark on removal to another State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28320&sectionno=47&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a motor`
  line `vehicle registered in one State has been kept in another State, for a period exceeding twelve months, the`
  line `owner of the vehicle shall, within such period and in such form containing such particulars as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government, apply to the registering authority, within whose jurisdiction the`
  line `vehicle then is, for the assignment of a new registration mark and shall present the certificate of`
  line `registration to that registering authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that an application under this sub-section shall be accompanied-`
  line
  line `(i) by the no objection certificate obtained under section 48, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in a case where no such certificate has been obtained, by--`
  line
  line `(a) the receipt obtained under sub-section (2) of section 48; or`
  line
  line `(b) the postal acknowledgement received by the owner of the vehicle if he has sent an`
  line `application in this behalf by registered post acknowledgement due to the registering authority`
  line `referred to in section 48,`
  line
  line `together with a declaration that he has not received any communication from such authority refusing to`
  line `grant such certificate or requiring him to comply with any direction subject to which such certificate may`
  line `be granted:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, in a case where a motor vehicle is held under a hire-purchase, lease or`
  line `hypothecation agreement, an application under this sub-section shall be accompanied by a no objection`
  line `certificate from the person with whom such agreement has been entered into, and the provisions of`
  line `section 51, so far as may be, regarding obtaining of such certificate from the person with whom such`
  line `agreement has been entered into, shall apply.`
  line
  line `(2) The registering authority, to which application is made under sub-section (1), shall after making`
  line `such verification, as it thinks fit, of the returns, if any, received under section 62, assign the vehicle a`
  line `registration mark as specified in sub-section (6) of section 41 to be displayed and shown thereafter on the`
  line `vehicle and shall enter the mark upon the certificate of registration before returning it to the applicant and`
  line `shall, in communication with the registering authority by whom the vehicle was previously registered,`
  line `arrange for the transfer of the registration of the vehicle from the records of that registering authority to its`
  line `own records.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a motor vehicle is held under a hire-purchase or lease or hypothecation agreement, the`
  line `registering authority shall, after assigning the vehicle a registration mark under sub-section (2), inform the`
  line `person whose name has been specified in the certificate of registration as the person with whom the`
  line `registered owner has entered into the hire-purchase or lease or hypothecation agreement (by sending to`
  line `such person a notice by registered post acknowledgement due at the address of such person entered in the`
  line `certificate of registration the fact of assignment of the said registration mark).`
  line
  line `(4) A State Government may make rules under section 65 requiring the owner of a motor vehicle not`
  line `registered within the State, which is brought into or is for the time being in the State, to furnish to the`
  line `prescribed authority in the State such information with respect to the motor vehicle and its registration as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) If the owner fails to make an application under sub-section (1) within the period prescribed, the`
  line `registering authority may, having regard to the circumstances of the case, require the owner to pay, in lieu`
  line `of any action that may be taken against him under section 177, such amount not exceeding one hundred`
  line `rupees as may be prescribed under sub-section (7):`
  line
  line `Provided that action under section 177 shall be taken against the owner where the owner fails to pay`
  line `the said amount.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the owner has paid the amount under sub-section (5), no action shall be taken against him`
  line `under section 177.`
  line
  line `(7) For the purposes of sub-section (5), the State Government may prescribe different amounts having`
  line `regard to the period of delay on the part of the owner in making an application under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (28321)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 51
  title `No objection certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 13 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28321&sectionno=48&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner of a motor vehicle when applying for the assignment of`
  line `a new registration mark under sub-section (1) of section 47, or where the transfer of a motor vehicle is to`
  line `be effected in a State other than the State of its registration, the transferor of such vehicle when reporting`
  line `the transfer under sub-section (1) of section 50, shall make an application in such form and in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government to the registering authority by which the vehicle`
  line `was registered for the issue of a certificate (hereafter in this section referred to as the no objection certificate), to the effect that the registering authority has no objection for assigning a new registration`
  line `mark to the vehicle or, as the case may be, for entering the particulars of the transfer of ownership in the`
  line `certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `(2) The registering authority shall, on receipt of an application under sub-section (1), issue a receipt in`
  line `such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the registering authority may, after making`
  line `such inquiry and requiring the applicant to comply with such directions as it deems fit and within thirty`
  line `days of the receipt thereof, by order in writing, communicate to the applicant that it has granted or refused`
  line `to grant the no objection certificate:`
  line
  line `Provided that a registering authority shall not refuse to grant the no objection certificate unless it has`
  line `recorded in writing the reasons for doing so and a copy of the same has been communicated to the`
  line applicant.
  line
  line `(4) Where within a period of thirty days referred to in sub-section (3), the registering authority does`
  line `not refuse to grant the no objection certificate or does not communicate the refusal to the applicant, the`
  line `registering authority shall be deemed to have granted the no objection certificate.`
  line
  line `(5) Before granting or refusing to grant the no objection certificate, the registering authority shall`
  line `obtain a report in writing from the police that no case relating to the theft of the motor vehicle concerned`
  line `has been reported or is pending, verify whether all the amounts due to Government including road tax in`
  line `respect of that motor vehicle have been paid and take into account such other factors as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^1[(6) The owner of the vehicle shall also inform at the earliest, in writing, the registering`
  line `authority about the theft of his vehicle together with the name of the police station where the theft`
  line `report was lodged, and the registering authority shall take into account such report while disposing of`
  line `any application for no objection certification, registration, transfer of ownership or issue of duplicate`
  line `registration certificate.]`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (28322)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 52
  title `Change of residence or place of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28322&sectionno=49&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the owner of a motor vehicle ceases to reside`
  line `or have his place of business at the address recorded in the certificate of registration of the vehicle, he`
  line `shall, within thirty days of any such change of address, intimate in such form accompanied by such`
  line `documents as may be prescribed by the Central Government, his new address, to the registering authority`
  line `by which the certificate of registration was issued, or, if the new address is within the jurisdiction of`
  line `another ^1[State, to any registering authority in that State], and shall at the same time forward the`
  line `certificate of registration to the registering authority or, as the case may be, to the other registering`
  line `authority in order that the new address may be entered therein.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) The intimation under sub-section (1) may be sent to the appropriate registering authority in`
  line `electronic form along with the electronic form of such documents, including proof of authentication in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(2) If the owner of a motor vehicle fails to intimate his new address to the concerned registering`
  line `authority within the period specified in sub-section (1), the registering authority may, having regard to the`
  line `circumstances of the case, require the owner to pay, in lieu of any action that may be taken against him`
  line `under section 177 such amount not exceeding ^3[five hundred rupees] as may be prescribed under`
  line `sub-section (4):`
  line
  line `Provided that action under section 177 shall be taken against the owner where he fails to pay the said`
  line amount.
  line
  line `(3) Where a person has paid the amount under sub-section (2), no action shall be taken against him`
  line `under section 177.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of sub-section (2), a State Government may prescribe different amounts having`
  line `regard to the period of delay in intimating his new address.`
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of intimation under sub-section (1), the registering authority may, after making such`
  line `verification as it may think fit, cause the new address to be entered in the certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `(6) A registering authority other than the original registering authority making any such entry shall`
  line `communicate the altered address to the original registering authority.`
  line
  line `(7) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply where the change of the address recorded in the certificate`
  line `of registration is due to a temporary absence not intended to exceed six months in duration or where the`
  line `motor vehicle is neither used nor removed from the address recorded in the certificate of registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 20, for "registering authority, to that other registering authority" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for "one hundred rupees" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (28323)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 53
  title `Transfer of ownership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28323&sectionno=50&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the ownership of any motor vehicle registered under this`
  line `Chapter is transferred,--`
  line
  line `(a) the transferor shall,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of a vehicle registered within the same State, within fourteen days of the`
  line `transfer, report the fact of transfer, in such form with such documents and in such manner, as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Central Government to the registering authority within whose jurisdiction`
  line `the transfer is to be effected and shall simultaneously send a copy of the said report to the`
  line `transferee; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a vehicle registered outside the State, within forty-five days of the transfer,`
  line `forward to the registering authority referred to in sub-clause (i)--`
  line
  line `(A) the no objection certificate obtained under section 48; or`
  line
  line `(B) in a case where no such certificate has been obtained,--`
  line
  line `(I) the receipt obtained under sub-section (2) of section 48; or`
  line
  line `(II) the postal acknowledgement received by the transferred if he has sent an`
  line `application in this behalf by registered post acknowledgement due to the registering`
  line `authority referred to in section 48,`
  line
  line `together with a declaration that he has not received any communication from such authority`
  line `refusing to grant such certificate or requiring him to comply with any direction subject to which`
  line `such certificate may be granted;`
  line
  line `(b) the transferee shall, within thirty days of the transfer, report the transfer to the registering`
  line `authority within whose jurisdiction he has the residence or place of business where the vehicle is`
  line `normally kept, as the case may be, and shall forward the certificate of registration to that registering`
  line `authority together with the prescribed fee and a copy of the report received by him from the transferor`
  line `in order that particulars of the transfer of ownership may be entered in the certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `(2) Where--`
  line
  line `(a) the person in whose name a motor vehicle stands registered dies, or`
  line
  line `(b) a motor vehicle has been purchased or acquired at a public auction conducted by, or on behalf`
  line `of, Government,`
  line
  line `the person succeeding to the possession of the vehicle or, as the case may be, who has purchased or`
  line `acquired the motor vehicle, shall make an application for the purpose of transferring the ownership of the`
  line `vehicle in his name, to the registering authority in whose jurisdiction he has the residence or place of`
  line `business where the vehicle is normally kept, as the case may be, in such manner, accompanied with such`
  line `fee, and within such period as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) If the transferor or the transferee fails to report to the registering authority the fact of transfer`
  line `within the period specified in clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1), as the case may be, or if the`
  line `person who is required to make an application under sub-section (2) hereafter in this section referred to`
  line `as the other person fails to make such application within the period prescribed, the registering authority`
  line `may, having regard to the circumstances of the case, require the transferor or the transferee, or the other`
  line `person, as the case may be, to pay, in lieu of any action that may be taken against him under section 177`
  line `such amount not exceeding one hundred rupees as may be prescribed under sub-section (5):`
  line
  line `Provided that action under section 177 shall be taken against the transferor or the transferee or the`
  line `other person, as the case may be, where he fails to pay the said amount.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a person has paid the amount under sub-section (3), no action shall be taken against him`
  line `under section 177.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of sub-section (3), a State Government may prescribe different amounts having`
  line `regard to the period of delay on the part of the transferor or the transferee in reporting the fact of transfer`
  line `of ownership of the motor vehicle or of the other person in making the application under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(6) On receipt of a report under sub-section (1), or an application under sub-section (2), the`
  line `registering authority may cause the transfer of ownership to be entered in the certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `(7) A registering authority making any such entry shall communicate the transfer of ownership to the`
  line `transferor and to the original registering authority, if it is not the original registering authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (28324)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 54
  title `Special provisions regarding motor vehicle subject to hire-purchase agreement, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28324&sectionno=51&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Where an application for registration of a motor vehicle which is held under a hire-purchase, lease or`
  line `hypothecation agreement (hereafter in this section referred to as the said agreement) is made, the`
  line `registering authority shall make an entry in the certificate of registration regarding the existence of the`
  line `said agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the ownership of any motor vehicle registered under this Chapter is transferred and the`
  line `transferee enters into the said agreement with any person, the ^1[last registering authority] shall, on receipt`
  line `of an application in such form as the Central Government may prescribe from the parties to the said`
  line `agreement, make an entry as to the existence of the said agreement in the certificate of registration ^2[and`
  line `an intimation in this behalf shall be sent to the original registering authority if the last registering`
  line `authority is not the original registering authority].`
  line
  line `(3) Any entry made under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), may be cancelled by the ^1[last registering`
  line `authority] on proof of the termination of the said agreement by the parties concerned on an application`
  line `being made in such form as the Central Government may prescribe ^2[and an intimation in this behalf`
  line `shall be sent to the original registering authority if the last registering authority is not the original`
  line `registering authority].`
  line
  line `(4) No entry regarding the transfer of ownership of any motor vehicle which is held under the said`
  line `agreement shall be made in the certificate of registration except with the written consent of the person`
  line `whose name has been specified in the certificate of registration as the person with whom the registered`
  line `owner has entered into the said agreement.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the person whose name has been specified in the certificate of registration as the person`
  line `with whom the registered owner has entered into the said agreement, satisfies the registering authority`
  line `that he has taken possession of the vehicle ^3[from the registered owner] owing to the default of the`
  line `registered owner under the provisions of the said agreement and that the registered owner refuses to`
  line `deliver the certificate of registration or has absconded, such authority may, after giving the registered`
  line `owner an opportunity to make such representation as he may wish to make (by sending to him a notice by`
  line `registered post acknowledgement due at his address entered in the certificate of registration) and`
  line `notwithstanding that the certificate of registration is not produced before it, cancel the certificate and issue`
  line `a fresh certificate of registration in the name of the person with whom the registered owner has entered`
  line `into the said agreement:`
  line
  line `Provided that a fresh certificate of registration shall not be issued in respect of a motor vehicle, unless`
  line `such person pays the prescribed fee:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a fresh certificate of registration issued in respect of a motor vehicle, other than`
  line `a transport vehicle, shall be valid only for the remaining period for which the certificate cancelled under`
  line `this sub-section would have been in force.`
  line
  line `(6) The registered owner shall, before applying to the appropriate authority, for the renewal of a`
  line `permit under section 81 or for the issue of duplicate certificate of registration under sub-section (14) of`
  line `section 41, or for the assignment of a new registration mark ^4[under section 47, or removal of the vehicle`
  line `to another State, or at the time of conversion of the vehicle from one class to another, or for issue of no`
  line `objection certificate under section 48, or for change of residence or place of business under section 49, or`
  line `for the alteration of the vehicle under section 52, make an application] to the person with whom the`
  line `registered owner has entered into the said agreement (such person being hereafter in this section referred`
  line `to as the financier) for the issue of a no objection certificate (hereafter in this section referred to as the`
  line `certificate).`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section and sub-sections (8) and (9), "appropriate`
  line `authority" in relation to any permit means the authority which is authorised by this Act to renew such`
  line `permit and, in relation to registration, means the authority which is authorised by this Act to issue`
  line `duplicate certificate of registration or to assign a new registration mark.`
  line
  line `(7) Within seven days of the receipt of an application under sub-section (6), the financier may issue,`
  line `or refuse for reasons which shall be recorded in writing and communicated to the applicant, to issue, the`
  line `certificate applied for and where the financier fails to issue the certificate and also fails to communicate`
  line `the reasons for refusal to issue the certificate to the applicant within the said period of seven days, the`
  line `certificate applied for shall be deemed to have been issued by the financier.`
  line
  line `(8) The registered owner shall, while applying to the appropriate authority for the renewal of any`
  line `permit under section 81, or for the issue of a duplicate certificate of registration under sub-section (14) of`
  line `section 41, or while applying for assignment of a new registration mark under section 47, submit with`
  line `such application the certificate, if any, obtained under sub-section (7) or, where no such certificate has`
  line `been obtained, the communication received from the financier under that sub-section, or, as the case may`
  line `be a declaration that he has not received any communication from the financier within the period of seven`
  line `days specified in that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(9) On receipt of an application for the renewal of any permit or for the issue of duplicate certificate`
  line `of registration or for assignment of a new registration mark in respect of a vehicle which is held under the`
  line `said agreement, the appropriate authority may, subject to the other provisions of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where the financier has refused to issue the certificate applied for, after giving the`
  line `applicant an opportunity of being heard, either--`
  line
  line `(i) renew or refuse to renew the permit, or`
  line
  line `(ii) issue or refuse to issue the duplicate certificate of registration, or`
  line
  line `(iii) assign or refuse to assign a new registration mark;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case,`
  line
  line `(i) renew the permit, or`
  line
  line `(ii) issue duplicate certificate of registration, or`
  line
  line `(iii) assign a new registration mark.`
  line
  line `(10) A registering authority making an entry in the certificate of registration regarding--`
  line
  line `(a) hire-purchase, lease or hypothecation agreement of a motor vehicle, or`
  line
  line `(b) the cancellation under sub-section (3) of an entry, or`
  line
  line `(c) recording transfer of ownership of motor vehicle, or`
  line
  line `(d) any alteration in a motor vehicle, or`
  line
  line `(e) suspension or cancellation of registration of a motor vehicle, or`
  line
  line `(f) change of address,`
  line
  line `shall communicate ^5[by registered post acknowledgment due] to the financier that such entry has been`
  line made.
  line
  line `^6[(11) A registering authority registering the new vehicle, or issuing the duplicate certificate of`
  line `registration or a no objection certificate or a temporary certificate of registration, or issuing or`
  line `renewing, a fitness certificate or substituting entries relating to another motor vehicle in the`
  line `permit, shall intimate the financier of such transaction.`
  line
  line `(12) The registering authority where it is not the original registering authority, when making`
  line `entry under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), or cancelling the said entry under sub-section (3) or`
  line `issuing the fresh certificate of registration under sub-section (5) shall communicate the same to the`
  line `original registering authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 14, for "original registering authority" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Added. by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 14, for "under section 47, make an application" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 54 of 1994, s.14 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s.14, ibid., for sub-section (11) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (28325)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 55
  title `Alteration in motor vehicle.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28325&sectionno=52&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `^1[52. Alteration in motor vehicle.-- (1) No owner of a motor vehicle shall so alter the vehicle that`
  line `the particulars contained in the certificate of registration are at variance with those originally specified by`
  line `the manufacturer:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the owner of a motor vehicle makes modification of the engine, or any part`
  line `thereof, of a vehicle for facilitating its operation by different type of fuel or source of energy including`
  line `battery, compressed natural gas, solar power, liquid petroleum gas or any other fuel or source of energy,`
  line `by fitment of a conversion kit, such modification shall be carried out subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided further that the Central Government may prescribe specifications, conditions for approval,`
  line `retrofitment and other related matters for the alteration of motor vehicles and in such cases, the warranty`
  line `granted by the manufacturer shall not be considered as void for the purposes of such alteration or`
  line retrofitment.]
  line
  line `Provided also that the Central Government may grant exemption for alteration of vehicles in a`
  line `manner other than specified above, for any specific purpose.`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) A manufacturer of a motor vehicle shall on the direction issued by the Central Government,`
  line `alter or retrofit safety equipment, or any other equipment in accordance with such standards and`
  line `specifications as may be specified by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), any person may, with the subsequent`
  line `approval of the registering authority, alter or cause to be altered any vehicle owned by him to be`
  line `converted into an adapted vehicle:`
  line
  line `Provided that such alteration complies with such conditions as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.]
  line
  line `(3) Where any alteration has been made in motor vehicle without the approval of registering`
  line `authority ^5***, the owner of the vehicle shall, within fourteen days of the making of the alteration, report`
  line `the alteration to the registering authority within whose jurisdiction he resides and shall forward the`
  line `certificate of registration to that authority together with the prescribed fee in order that particulars of`
  line `registration may be entered therein.`
  line
  line `(4) A registering authority other than the original registering authority making any such entry shall`
  line `communicate the details of the entry to the original registering authority.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions made under sub-sections (1), (2), (3) and (4), no person holding a vehicle`
  line `under a hire-purchase agreement shall make any alteration to the vehicle except with the written consent`
  line `of the registered owner.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "alteration" means a change in the structure of a`
  line `vehicle which results in a change in its basic feature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 2000, s. 2, for section 52 (w.e.f. 11-8-2000).`
  line
  line `2. The Proviso subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 21, (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `5. The words "or by reason of replacement of its engine without such approval under sub-section (2)" omitted by s. 21, ibid.,`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (28326)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 56
  title `Suspension of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28326&sectionno=53&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any registering authority or other prescribed authority has`
  line `reason to believe that any motor vehicle within its jurisdiction--`
  line
  line `(a) is in such a condition that its use in a public place would constitute a danger to the public, or`
  line `that it fails to comply with the requirements of this Act or of the rules made thereunder, or`
  line
  line `(b) has been, or is being, used for hire or reward without a valid permit for being used as such,`
  line
  line `the authority may, after giving the owner an opportunity of making any representation he may wish to`
  line `make (by sending to the owner a notice by registered post acknowledgement due at his address entered in`
  line `the certificate of registration), for reasons to be recorded in writing, suspend the certificate of registration`
  line `of the vehicle--`
  line
  line `(i) in any case falling under clause (a), until the defects are rectified to its satisfaction; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in any case falling under clause (b), for a period not exceeding four months.`
  line
  line `(2) An authority other than a registering authority shall, when making a suspension order under`
  line `sub-section (1), intimate in writing the fact of such suspension and the reasons therefor to the registering`
  line `authority within whose jurisdiction the vehicle is at the time of the suspension.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the registeration of a motor vehicle has been suspended under sub-section (1), for a`
  line `continuous period of not less than one month, the registering authority, within whose jurisdiction the`
  line `vehicle was when the registration was suspended, shall, if it is not the original registering authority,`
  line `inform that authority of the suspension.`
  line
  line `(4) The owner of a motor vehicle shall, on the demand of a registering authority or other prescribed`
  line `authority which has suspended the certificate of registration of the vehicle under this section, surrender`
  line `the certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `(5) A certificate of registration surrendered under sub-section (4) shall be returned to the owner when`
  line `the order suspending registration has been rescinded and not before.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (28327)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 57
  title `Cancellation of registration suspended under section 53.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28327&sectionno=54&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Where the suspension of`
  line `registration of a vehicle under section 53 has continued without interruption for a period of not less than`
  line `six months, the registering authority within whose jurisdiction the vehicle was when the registration was`
  line `suspended, may, if it is the original registering authority, cancel the registration, and if it is not the`
  line `original registering authority, shall forward the certificate of registration to that authority which may`
  line `cancel the registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (28328)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 58
  title `Cancellation of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28328&sectionno=55&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a motor vehicle has been destroyed or has been rendered`
  line `permanently incapable of use, the owner shall, within fourteen days or as soon as may be, report the fact`
  line `to the registering authority within whose jurisdiction he has the residence or place of business where the`
  line `vehicle is normally kept, as the case may be, and shall forward to that authority the certificate of`
  line `registration of the vehicle.`
  line
  line `(2) The registering authority shall, if it is the original registering authority, cancel the registration and`
  line `the certificate of registration, or, if it is not, shall forward the report and the certificate of registration to`
  line `the original registering authority and that authority shall cancel the registration.`
  line
  line `(3) Any registering authority may order the examination of a motor vehicle within its jurisdiction by`
  line `such authority as the State Government may by order appoint and, if, upon such examination and after`
  line `giving the owner an opportunity to make any representation he may wish to make (by sending to the`
  line `owner a notice by registered post acknowledgement due at his address entered in the certificate of`
  line `registration), it is satisfied that the vehicle is in such a condition that it is incapable of being used or its`
  line `use in a public place would constitute a danger to the public and that it is beyond reasonable repair, may`
  line `cancel the registration.`
  line
  line `(4) If a registering authority is satisfied that a motor vehicle has been permanently removed out of`
  line `India, the registering authority shall cancel the registration.`
  line
  line `(5) If a registering authority is satisfied that the registration of a motor vehicle has been obtained on`
  line `the basis of documents which were, or by representation of facts which was, false in any material particular, or the engine number or the chassis number embossed thereon are different from such number`
  line `entered in the certificate of registration, the registering authority shall after giving the owner an`
  line `opportunity to make such representation as he may wish to make (by sending to the owner a notice by`
  line `registered post acknowledgement due at his address entered in the certificate of registration), and for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing cancel the registration.`
  line
  line `^1[(5A) If any registering authority or other prescribed authority has reason to believe that any motor`
  line `vehicle within its jurisdiction has been used in the commission of an offence punishable under section`
  line `199A, the authority may, after giving the owner an opportunity of making a representation in writing,`
  line `cancel the certificate of registration of the vehicle for a period of one year:`
  line `Provided that the owner of the motor vehicle may apply for fresh registration in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 40 and section 41.]`
  line
  line `(6) A registering authority cancelling the registration of a motor vehicle under section 54 or under this`
  line `section shall communicate such fact in writing to the owner of the vehicle, and the owner of the vehicle`
  line `shall forthwith surrender to that authority the certificate of registration of the vehicle.`
  line
  line `(7) A registering authority making an order of cancellation under section 54 or under this section`
  line `shall, if it is the original registering authority, cancel the certificate of registration and the entry relating to`
  line `the vehicle in its records, and, if it is not the original registering authority, forward the certificate of`
  line `registration to that authority, and that authority shall cancel the certificate of registration and the entry`
  line `relating to the motor vehicle in its records.`
  line
  line `(8) The expression "original registering authority" in this section and in sections 41, 49, 50, 51, 52, 53`
  line `and 54 means the registering authority in whose records the registration of the vehicle is recorded.`
  line
  line `(9) In this section, "certificate of registration" includes a certificate of registration renewed under the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (28329)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 59
  title `Certificate of fitness of transport vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28329&sectionno=56&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sections 59 and 60,`
  line `a transport vehicle shall not be deemed to be validly registered for the purposes of section 39, unless it`
  line `carries a certificate of fitness in such form containing such particulars and information as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government, issued by the prescribed authority, or by an authorised testing`
  line `station mentioned in sub-section (2), to the effect that the vehicle complies for the time being with all the`
  line `requirements of this Act and the rules made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the prescribed authority or the authorised testing station refuses is issue such`
  line `certificate, it shall supply the owner of the vehicle with its reasons in writing for such refusal.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that no certificate of fitness shall be granted to a vehicle, after such date as may be`
  line `notified by the Central Government, unless such vehicle has been tested at an automated testing station.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The "authorised testing station" referred to in sub-section (1) means any facility, including`
  line `automated testing facilities, authorised by the State Government, where fitness testing may be conducted`
  line `in accordance with the rules made by the Central Government for recognition, regulation and control of`
  line `such stations.]`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), a certificate of fitness shall remain effective for such`
  line `period as may be prescribed by the Central Government having regard to the objects of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The prescribed authority may for reasons to be recorded in writing cancel a certificate of fitness at`
  line `any time, if satisfied that the vehicle to which it relates no longer complies with all the requirements of`
  line `this Act and the rules made thereunder; and on such cancellation the certificate of registration of the vehicle and any permit granted in respect of the vehicle under Chapter V shall be deemed to be suspended`
  line `until a new certificate of fitness has been obtained:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that no such cancellation shall be made by the prescribed authority unless, --`
  line
  line `(a) such prescribed authority holds such technical qualification as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government and where the prescribed authority does not hold the technical qualification, such`
  line `cancellation is made on the basis of the report of an officer having such qualification; and`
  line
  line `(b) the reasons recorded in writing cancelling a certificate of fitness are confirmed by an`
  line `authorised testing station chosen by the owner of the vehicle whose certificate of fitness is sought to be`
  line `cancelled:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the cancellation is confirmed by the authorised testing station, the cost of`
  line `undertaking the test shall be borne by the owner of the vehicle being tested and in the alternative by the`
  line `prescribed authority.]`
  line
  line `(5) A certificate of fitness issued under this Act shall, while it remains effective, be valid throughout`
  line India.
  line
  line `^4[(6) All transport vehicles with a valid certificate of fitness issued under this section shall carry, on`
  line `their bodies, in a clear and visible manner such distinguishing mark as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(7) Subject to such conditions as the Central Government may prescribe, the provisions of this section`
  line `may be extended to non-transport vehicles.]`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by, s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 23, ibid., for "sub-section (2)" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 23, (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 23, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (28330)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 60
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s.17, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28330&sectionno=57&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Any person aggrieved by an order of the registering authority under section`
  line `41, 42, 43, 45, 47, 48, 49, 50, 52, 53, 55 or 56 may, within thirty days of the date on which he has`
  line `received notice of such order, appeal against the order to the prescribed authority.]`
  line
  line `(2) The appellate authority shall give notice of the appeal to the original authority and after giving an`
  line `opportunity to the original authority and the appellant to be heard in the appeal pass such orders as it`
  line `thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (28331)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 61
  title `Special provisions in regard to transport vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28331&sectionno=58&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, having`
  line `regard to the number, nature and size of the tyres attached to the wheels of a transport vehicle, (other than`
  line `a motorcab), and its make and model and other relevant considerations, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify, in relation to each make and model of a transport vehicle, the ^1[maximum gross vehicle`
  line `weight] of such vehicle and the maximum safe axle weight of each axle of such vehicle.`
  line
  line `(2) A registering authority, when registering a transport vehicle, other than a motorcab, shall enter in`
  line `the record of registration and shall also enter in the certificate of registration of the vehicle the following`
  line `particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the unladen weight of the vehicle;`
  line
  line `(b) the number, nature and size of the tyres attached to each wheel;`
  line
  line `(c) the gross vehicle weight of the vehicle and the registered axle weights pertaining to the several`
  line `axles thereof; and`
  line
  line `(d) if the vehicle is used or adapted to be used for the carriage of passengers solely or in addition`
  line `to goods, the number of passengers for whom accommodation is provided,`
  line `and the owner of the vehicle shall have the same particulars exhibited in the prescribed manner on the`
  line vehicle.
  line
  line `(3) There shall not be entered in the certificate of registration of any such vehicle any gross vehicle`
  line `weight or a registered axle weight of any of the axles different from that specified in the notification`
  line `under sub-section (1) in relation to the make and model of such vehicle and to the number, nature and size`
  line `of the tyres attached to its wheels:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it appears to the Central Government that heavier weights than those specified in`
  line `the notification under sub-section (1) may be permitted in a particular locality for vehicles of a particular`
  line `type, the Central Government may, by order in the Official Gazette direct that the provisions of this`
  line `sub-section shall apply with such modifications as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(5) In order that the gross vehicle weight entered in the certificate of registration of a vehicle may be`
  line `revised in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3), the registering authority may require the`
  line `owner of transport vehicle in accordance with such procedure as may be prescribed to produce the`
  line `certificate of registration within such time as may be specified by the registering authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for "maximum safe laden weight" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (4) omitted by Act 27 of 2000, s. 3 (w.e.f. 11-8-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (28332)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 62
  title `Power to fix the age limit of motor vehicle.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28332&sectionno=59&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, having regard`
  line `to the public safety, convenience and objects of this Act, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify`
  line `the life of a motor vehicle reckoned from the date of its manufacture, after the expiry of which the motor`
  line `vehicle shall not be deemed to comply with the requirements of this Act and the rules made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may specify different ages for different classes or different`
  line `types of motor vehicles.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government may, having`
  line `regard to the purpose of a motor vehicle, such as, display or use for the purposes of a demonstration in`
  line `any exhibition, use for the purposes of technical research or taking part in a vintage car rally, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, exempt, by a general or special order, subject to such conditions as`
  line `may be specified in such notification, any class or type of motor vehicle from the operation of`
  line `sub-section (1) for the purpose to be stated in the notification.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 56, no prescribed authority or authorised testing`
  line `station shall grant a certificate of fitness to a motor vehicle in contravention of the provisions of any`
  line `notification issued under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `^1[(4) The Central Government may, having regard to the public safety, convenience, protection of the`
  line `environment and the objects of this Act, make rules prescribing the manner of recycling of motor vehicles`
  line `and parts thereof which have exceeded their life.]`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (28333)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 63
  title `Registration of vehicles belonging to the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28333&sectionno=60&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Such authority as the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify, may register any motor vehicle`
  line `which is the property or for the time being under the exclusive control of the Central Government and is`
  line `used for Government purposes relating to the defence of the country and unconnected with any`
  line `commercial enterprise and any vehicle so registered shall not, so long as it remains the property or under`
  line `the exclusive control of the Central Government, require to be registered otherwise under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The authority registering a vehicle under sub-section (1) shall assign a registration mark in`
  line `accordance with the provisions contained in the rules made in this behalf by the Central Government and`
  line `shall issue a certificate in respect of that vehicle to the effect that such vehicle complies for the time being`
  line `with all the requirements of this Act and the rules made thereunder and that the vehicle has been`
  line `registered under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) A vehicle registered under this section shall carry the certificate issued under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) If a vehicle registered under this section ceases to be the property or under the exclusive control of`
  line `the Central Government, the provisions of sections 39 and 40 shall thereupon apply.`
  line
  line `(5) The authority registering a vehicle under sub-section (1) shall furnish to any State Government all`
  line `such information regarding the general nature, overall dimensions and axle weights of the vehicle as the`
  line `State Government may at any time require.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (28334)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 64
  title `Application of Chapter to trailers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28334&sectionno=61&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Chapter shall apply to the`
  line `registration of trailers as they apply to the registration of any other motor vehicle.`
  line
  line `(2) The registration mark assigned to a trailer shall be displayed in such manner on the side of the`
  line `drawing vehicle, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall drive a motor vehicle to which a trailer is or trailers are attached unless the`
  line `registration mark of the motor vehicle so driven is displayed on the trailer or on the last trailer in the train,`
  line `as the case may be, in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (28335)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 65
  title `Information regarding stolen and recovered motor vehicles to be furnished by the police to the State Transport Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28335&sectionno=62&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, if it thinks necessary or expedient so to do`
  line `in the public interest, direct the submission by the Inspector General of Police (by whatever designation`
  line `called) and such other police officers as the State Government may specify in this behalf, of such returns`
  line `containing the information regarding vehicles which have been stolen and stolen vehicles which have`
  line `been recovered of which the police are aware, to the State Transport Authority, and may prescribe the`
  line `form in which and the period within which such returns shall be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62_a:
  sectionId (50172)
  sectionNo 62A
  orderNo 66
  title `Prohibition of registration and issuance of certificate of fitness to oversized vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=50172&sectionno=62A&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_62_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[62A. Prohibition of registration and issuance of certificate of fitness to oversized vehicles.--(1)`
  line `No registering authority shall register any motor vehicle that contravenes any rule made under clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 110.`
  line
  line `(2) No prescribed authority or authorised testing station shall issue a certificate of fitness under`
  line `section 56 to any motor vehicle that contravenes any rule made under section 110.]`
obj_root_law_sections_62_b:
  sectionId (50173)
  sectionNo 62B
  orderNo 67
  title `National Register of Motor Vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=50173&sectionno=62B&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_62_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[62B. National Register of Motor Vehicles. --(1) The Central Government shall maintain a National`
  line `Register of Motor Vehicles in such form and manner as may be prescribed by it:`
  line
  line `Provided that all State Registers of Motor Vehicles shall be subsumed under the National Register of`
  line `Motor Vehicles by such date as may be notified in the Official Gazette by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) No certificate of registration issued, or renewed, under this Act shall be valid unless it has been`
  line `issued a unique registration number under the National Register of Motor Vehicles.`
  line
  line `(3) In order to maintain the National Register of Motor Vehicles, all State Governments and`
  line `registering authorities under this Act shall transmit all information and data in the State Register of Motor`
  line `Vehicles to the Central Government in such form and manner as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(4) State Governments shall be able to access the National Register of Motor Vehicles and update`
  line `records in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the rules made by the Central Government`
  line thereunder.]
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (28336)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 68
  title `Maintenance of State Registers of Motor Vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28336&sectionno=63&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `^1[63. Maintenance of State Registers of Motor Vehicles.-- (1) Each State Government shall`
  line `maintain in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government a register to be known as the`
  line `State Register of Motor Vehicles, in respect of the motor vehicles in that State, containing the particulars`
  line including
  line
  line `(a) registration numbers;`
  line
  line `(b) years of manufacture;`
  line
  line `(c) classes and types;`
  line
  line `(d) names and addresses of registered owners; and`
  line
  line `(e) such other particulars as may be prescribed by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(2) Each State Government shall supply to the Central Government ^2[if so desired by it] a printed`
  line `copy of the State Register of Motor Vehicles and shall also inform the Central Government without delay`
  line `of all additions to and other amendments in such register made from time to time.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Register of Motor Vehicles shall be maintained in such manner as may be prescribed by`
  line `the State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 26, ibid., for section 63 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 19 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (28337)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 69
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28337&sectionno=64&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may make rules to`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the period within which and the form in which an application shall be made and the`
  line `documents, particulars and information it shall accompany under sub-section (1) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(b) the form in which the certificate of registration shall be made and the particulars and`
  line `information it shall contain and the manner in which it shall be issued under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 41;`
  line
  line `(c) the form and manner in which the particulars of the certificate of registration shall be entered`
  line `in the records of the registering authority under sub-section (5) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which and the form in which the registration mark, the letters and figures and`
  line `other particulars referred to in sub-section (6) of section 41 shall be displayed and shown;`
  line
  line `^1[(da) providing for the period of validity of a certificate of registration under sub-section (7) of`
  line `section 41;]`
  line
  line `(e) the period within which and the form in which the application shall be made and the`
  line `particulars and information it shall contain under sub-section (8) of section 41;`
  line
  line `^1[(ea) the period of renewal of certificate of registration of different types of motor vehicles under`
  line `sub-section (10) of section 41;]`
  line
  line `(f) the form in which the application referred to in sub-section (14) of section 41 shall be made,`
  line `the particulars and information it shall contain and the fee to be charged;`
  line
  line `^1[(fa) the issue of temporary certificate of registration and temporary registration mark under`
  line `section 43;`
  line
  line `(fb) the terms and conditions under which a motor vehicle sold by an authorised dealer shall not`
  line `require production before a registering authority under sub-section (1) of section 44;]`
  line
  line `(g) the form in which the period within which the application referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 47 shall be made and the particulars it shall contain;`
  line
  line `(h) the form in which and the manner in which the application for "No Objection Certificate"`
  line `shall be made under sub-section (1) of section 48 and the form of receipt to be issued under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 48;`
  line
  line `(i) the matters that are to be complied with by an applicant before no objection certificate may be`
  line `issued under section 48;`
  line
  line `(j) the form in which the intimation of change of address shall be made under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 49 and the documents to be submitted along with the application;`
  line
  line `^2[(ja) the form and manner for the electronic submission of the intimation of change of address,`
  line `documents to be submitted along with such intimation including proof of authentication under`
  line `sub-section (1A) of section 49;]`
  line
  line `(k) the form in which and the manner in which the intimation of transfer of ownership shall be`
  line `made under sub-section (1) of section 50 or under sub-section (2) of section 50 and the document to`
  line `be submitted along with the application;`
  line
  line `(l) the form in which the application under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 51 shall`
  line `be made;`
  line
  line `^2[(la) specifications, conditions for approval, retrofitment and other related matters for the`
  line `alteration of motor vehicles under sub-section (1) of section 52;`
  line
  line `(lb) the conditions for the alteration of any motor vehicle into an adapted vehicle under subsection (2) of section 52;]`
  line
  line `(m) the form in which the certificate of fitness shall be issued under sub-section (1) of section 56`
  line `and the particulars and information it shall contain;`
  line
  line `(n) the period for which the certificate of fitness granted or renewed under section 56 shall be`
  line effective;
  line
  line `^2[(na) the distinguishing mark to be carried on the body of transport vehicles under sub-section`
  line `(6) of section 56;`
  line
  line `(nb) the conditions under which the application of section 56 may be extended to non-transport`
  line `vehicles under sub-section (7) of section 56;`
  line
  line `(nc) the recycling of motor vehicles and parts thereof which have exceeded their life under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 59;]`
  line
  line `(o) the fees to be charged for the issue or renewal or alteration of certificates of registration, for`
  line `making an entry regarding transfer of ownership on a certificate of registration, for making or`
  line `cancelling an endorsement in respect of agreement of hire-purchase or lease or hypothecation on a`
  line `certificate of registration, for certificates of fitness for registration marks, and for the examination or`
  line `inspection of motor vehicles, and the refund of such fees.`
  line
  line `^2[(oa) all or any of the matters under sub-section (1) of section 62B;`
  line
  line `(ob) all or any of the matters under sub-section (1) and sub-section (2) of section 63;]`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (28338)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 70
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28338&sectionno=65&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Government may make rules for the`
  line `purpose of carrying into effect the provisions of this Chapter other than the matters specified in`
  line `section 64.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the conduct and hearing of appeals that may be preferred under this Chapter (the fees to be`
  line `paid in respect of such appeals and the refund of such fees);`
  line
  line `(b) the appointment, functions and jurisdiction of registering and other prescribed authorities;`
  line
  line `(c) the exemption of road-rollers, graders and other vehicles designed and used solely for the`
  line `construction, repair and cleaning of roads from all or any of the provisions of this Chapter and the`
  line `rules made thereunder and the conditions governing such exemption;`
  line
  line `(d) the issue or renewal of certificates of registration and fitness and duplicates of such`
  line `certificates to replace the certificates lost, destroyed or mutilated;`
  line
  line `(e) the production of certificates of registration before the registering authority for the revision of`
  line `entries therein of particulars relating to the gross vehicle weight;`
  line
  line `(f) the temporary registration of motor vehicles, and the issue of temporary certificate of`
  line `registration and marks ^1[under the proviso to section 43];`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which the particulars referred to in sub-section (2) of section 58 and other`
  line `prescribed particulars shall be exhibited;`
  line
  line `(h) the exemption of prescribed persons or prescribed classes of persons from payment of all or`
  line `any portion of the fees payable under this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(i) the forms, other than those prescribed by the Central Government, to be used for the purpose`
  line `of this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(j) the communication between registering authorities of particulars of certificates of registration`
  line `and by owners of vehicles registered outside the State of particulars of such vehicles and of their`
  line registration;
  line
  line `(k) the amount or amounts under sub-section (13) of section 41 or sub-section (7) of section 47 or`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 49 or sub-section (5) of section 50;`
  line
  line `(l) the extension of the validity of certificates of fitness pending consideration of applications for`
  line `their renewal;`
  line
  line `(m) the exemption from the provisions of this Chapter, and the conditions and fees for exemption,`
  line `of motor vehicles in the possession of dealers;`
  line
  line `(n) the form in which and the period within which the return under section 62 shall be sent;`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 28, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (o) omitted by Act 32 of 2019, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (28339)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 71
  title `Necessity for permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28339&sectionno=66&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) No owner of a motor vehicle shall use or permit the use of the`
  line `vehicle as a transport vehicle in any public place whether or not such vehicle is actually carrying any`
  line `passengers or goods save in accordance with the conditions of a permit granted or countersigned by a`
  line `Regional or State Transport Authority or any prescribed authority authorising him the use of the vehicle`
  line `in that place in the manner in which the vehicle is being used:`
  line
  line `Provided that a stage carriage permit shall, subject to any conditions that may be specified in the`
  line `permit, authorise the use of the vehicle as a contract carriage:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a stage carriage permit may, subject to any conditions that may be specified in`
  line `the permit, authorise the use of the vehicle as a goods carriage either when carrying passengers or not:`
  line
  line `Provided also that a goods carriage permit shall, subject to any conditions that may be specified in the`
  line `permit, authorise the use of the vehicle for the carriage of goods for or in connection with a trade or`
  line `business carried on by him.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided also that where a transport vehicle has been issued any permit or permits, as well as a`
  line `licence under this Act, such vehicle may be used either under the permit, or permits, so issued to it, or`
  line `under such licence, at the discretion of the vehicle owner.]`
  line
  line `(2) The holder of a goods carriage permit may use the vehicle, for the drawing of any public or semitrailer not owned by him, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the holder of a permit of any articulated vehicle may use the prime-mover of that`
  line `articulated vehicle for any other semi-trailor.]`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply--`
  line
  line `(a) to any transport vehicle owned by the Central Government or a State Government and used`
  line `for Government purposes unconnected with any commercial enterprise;`
  line
  line `(b) to any transport vehicle owned by a local authority or by a person acting under contract with a`
  line `local authority and used solely for road cleansing, road watering or conservancy purposes;`
  line
  line `(c) to any transport vehicle used solely for police, fire brigade or ambulance purposes;`
  line
  line `(d) to any transport vehicle used solely for the conveyance of corpses and the mourners`
  line `accompanying the corpses;`
  line
  line `(e) to any transport vehicle used for towing a disabled vehicle or for removing goods from a`
  line `disabled vehicle to a place of safety;`
  line
  line `(f) to any transport vehicle used for any other public purpose as may be prescribed by the State`
  line `Government in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(g) to any transport vehicle used by a person who manufactures or deals in motor vehicles or`
  line `builds bodies for attachment to chassis, solely for such purposes and in accordance with such`
  line `conditions as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this`
  line behalf;
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(i) to any goods vehicle, the gross vehicle weight of which does not exceed 3,000 kilograms;`
  line
  line `(j) subject to such conditions as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify, to any transport vehicle purchased in one State and proceeding to a place, situated in`
  line `that State or in any other State, without carrying any passenger or goods;`
  line
  line `(k) to any transport vehicle which has been temporarily registered under section 43 while`
  line `proceeding empty to any place for the purpose of registration of the vehicle;`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(m) to any transport vehicle which, owing to flood, earthquake or any other natural calamity,`
  line `obstruction on road, or unforeseen circumstances is required to be diverted through any other route,`
  line `whether within or outside the State, with a view to enabling it to reach its destination;`
  line
  line `(n) to any transport vehicle used for such purposes as the Central or State Government may, by`
  line `order, specify;`
  line
  line `(o) to any transport vehicle which is subject to a hire-purchase, lease or hypothecation agreement`
  line `and which owing to the default of the owner has been taken possession of by or on behalf of, the`
  line `person with whom the owner has entered into such agreement, to enable such motor vehicle to reach`
  line `its destination; or`
  line
  line `(p) to any transport vehicle while proceeding empty to any place for purpose of repair.`
  line
  line `^5[(q) to any transport vehicle having been issued a licence under a scheme, under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 67 or sub-section (1) of section 88A, or plying under such orders as may be issued by the`
  line `Central Government or by the State Government.](4) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), sub-section (1) shall if the State Government by rule`
  line `made under section 96 so prescribes, apply to any motor vehicle adapted to carry more than nine persons`
  line `excluding the driver.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 29, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Added by Act 54 of 1994, s. 20 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Cl. (h) omitted by Act 27 of 2000, s. 4 (w.e.f. 11-8-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Cl. (l) omitted by Act 39 of 2001, s. 2 (w.e.f. 27-9-2001).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_66_a:
  sectionId (49495)
  sectionNo 66A
  orderNo 72
  title `National Transportation Policy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49495&sectionno=66A&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_66_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[66A. National Transportation Policy.-- The Central Government may develop a National`
  line `Transportation Policy consistent with the objects of this Act in concurrence with the State Governments`
  line `and other agencies with a view to--`
  line
  line `(i) establish a planning framework for passengers and goods transportation within which transport`
  line `bodies are to operate;`
  line
  line `(ii) establish a medium and long term planning framework for all forms of road transport, identify`
  line `areas for the development of transport improvement infrastructure across India in consultation with`
  line `the authorities and agencies related to ports, railways and aviation as well as with local and State level`
  line `planning, land holding and regulatory authorities for the delivery of an integrated multimodal`
  line `transport system;`
  line
  line `(iii) establish the framework of grant of permits and schemes;`
  line
  line `(iv) establish strategic policy for transport by road and its role as a link to other means of`
  line transport;
  line
  line `(v) identify strategic policies and specify priorities for the transport system that address current`
  line `and future challenges;`
  line
  line `(vi) provide medium to long term strategic directions, priorities and actions;`
  line
  line `(vii) promote competition, innovation, increase in capacity, seamless mobility and greater`
  line `efficiency in transport of goods or livestock or passengers, and economical use of resources;`
  line
  line `(viii) safeguard the interest of the public and promote equity, while seeking to enhance private`
  line `participation and public-private partnership in the transport sector;`
  line
  line `(ix) demonstrate an integrated approach to transport and land use planning;`
  line
  line `(x) identify the challenges that the National Transportation Policy seeks to address; and`
  line
  line `(xi) address any other matter deemed relevant by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_66_b:
  sectionId (49496)
  sectionNo 66B
  orderNo 73
  title `No bar against permit holders to apply and hold licences under schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49496&sectionno=66B&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_66_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[66B. No bar against permit holders to apply and hold licences under schemes.-- No person who`
  line `holds the permit issued under this Act shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be disqualified from applying for a licence under the scheme made under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 67 or sub-section (1) of section 88A by reason of holding such permit; and`
  line
  line `(b) be required to get such permit cancelled on being issued a licence under any scheme made`
  line `under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (28340)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 74
  title `Power to State Government to control road transport.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28340&sectionno=67&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) A State Government, having`
  line `regard to--`
  line
  line `(a) the advantages offered to the public, trade and industry by the development of motor`
  line transport;
  line
  line `(b) the desirability of co-ordinating road and rail transport;`
  line
  line `(c) the desirability of preventing the deterioration of the road system, and`
  line
  line `(d) promoting effective competition among the transport service providers,`
  line
  line `may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette issue directions both to the State Transport`
  line `Authority and Regional Transport Authority regarding the passengers convenience, economically`
  line `competitive fares, prevention of overcrowding and road safety.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any direction under sub-section (1) regarding the fixing of fares and freights for stage carriages,`
  line `contract carriages and goods carriages may provide that such fares or freights shall be inclusive of the tax`
  line `payable by the passengers or the consignors of the goods, as the case may be, to the operators of the stage`
  line `carriages, contract carriages or goods carriages under any law for the time being in force relating to tax on`
  line `passengers and goods:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the State Government may subject to such conditions as it may deem fit, and with a`
  line `view to achieving the objectives specified in clause (d) of sub-section (1), relax all or any of the`
  line `provisions made under this Chapter.]`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the State Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, modify any permit issued under this Act or make schemes for the transportation of`
  line `goods and passengers and issue licences under such scheme for the promotion of development and`
  line `efficiency in transportation--`
  line
  line `(a) last mile connectivity;`
  line
  line `(b) rural transport;`
  line
  line `(c) reducing traffic congestion;`
  line
  line `(d) improving urban transport;`
  line
  line `(e) safety of road users;`
  line
  line `(f) better utilisation of transportation assets;`
  line
  line `(g) the enhancement of economic vitality of the area, through competitiveness, productivity and`
  line efficiency;
  line
  line `(h) the increase in the accessibility and mobility of people;`
  line
  line `(i) the protection and enhancement of the environment;`
  line
  line `(j) the promotion of energy conservation;`
  line
  line `(k) improvement of the quality of life;`
  line
  line `(l) enhance integration and connectivity of the transportation system, across and between modes`
  line `of transport; and`
  line
  line `(m) such other matters as the Central Government may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The scheme framed under sub-section (3), shall specify the fees to be charged, form of application`
  line `and grant of a licence including the renewal, suspension, cancellation or modification of such licence.]`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (28341)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 75
  title `Transport Authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28341&sectionno=68&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `constitute for the State a State Transport Authority to exercise and discharge the powers and functions`
  line `specified in sub-section (3), and shall in like manner constitute Regional Transport Authorities to exercise`
  line `and discharge throughout such areas (in this Chapter referred to as regions) as may be specified in the`
  line `notification, in respect of each Regional Transport Authority; the powers and functions conferred by or`
  line `under this Chapter on such Authorities:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the Union territories, the Administrator may abstain from constituting any Regional`
  line `Transport Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) A State Transport Authority or a Regional Transport Authority shall consist of a Chairman who`
  line `has had judicial experience or experience as an appellate or a revisional authority or as an adjudicating`
  line `authority competent to pass any order or take any decision under any law and in the case of a State`
  line `Transport Authority, such other persons (whether officials or not), not being more than four and, in the`
  line `case of a Regional Transport Authority, such other persons (whether officials or not), not being more than`
  line `two, as the State Government may think fit to appoint; but no person who has any financial interest`
  line `whether as proprietor, employee or otherwise in any transport undertaking shall be appointed, or continue to be, a member of a State or Regional Transport Authority, and, if any person being a member of any`
  line `such Authority acquires a financial interest in any transport undertaking, he shall within four weeks of so`
  line `doing, give notice in writing to the State Government of the acquisition of such interest and shall vacate`
  line `office:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall prevent any of the members of the State Transport`
  line `Authority or a Regional Transport Authority, as the case may be, to preside over a meeting of such`
  line `Authority during the absence of the Chairman, notwithstanding that such member does not possess`
  line `judicial experience or experience as an appellate or a revisional authority or as an adjudicating authority`
  line `competent to pass any order or take any decision under any law:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the State Government may,--`
  line
  line `(i) where it considers necessary or expedient so to do, constitute the State Transport Authority or`
  line `a Regional Transport Authority for any region so as to consist of only one member who shall be an`
  line `official with judicial experience or experience as an appellate or a revisional authority or as an`
  line `adjudicating authority competent to pass any order or take any decision under any law;`
  line
  line `(ii) by rules made in this behalf, provide for the transaction of business of such authorities in the`
  line `absence of the Chairman or any other member and specify the circumstances under which, and the`
  line `manner in which, such business could be so transacted:`
  line
  line `Provided also that nothing in this sub-section shall be construed as debarring an official (other than an`
  line `official connected directly with the management or operation of a transport undertaking) from being`
  line `appointed or continuing as a member of any such authority merely by reason of the fact that the`
  line `Government employing the official has, or acquires, any financial interest in a transport undertaking.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Transport Authority and every Regional Transport Authority shall give effect to any`
  line `directions issued under section 67 and the State Transport Authority shall, subject to such directions and`
  line `save as otherwise provided by or under this Act, exercise and discharge throughout the State the`
  line `following powers and functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to co-ordinate and regulate the activities and policies of the Regional Transport Authorities, if`
  line `any, of the State;`
  line
  line `(b) to perform the duties of a Regional Transport Authority where there is no such Authority and,`
  line `if it thinks fit or if so required by a Regional Transport Authority, to perform those duties in respect`
  line `of any route common to two or more regions;`
  line
  line `(c) to settle all disputes and decide all matters on which differences of opinion arise between`
  line `Regional Transport Authorities; and`
  line
  line `^1[(ca) Government to formulate routes for plying stage carriages;]`
  line
  line `(d) to discharge such other functions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of exercising and discharging the powers and functions specified in`
  line `sub-section (3), a State Transport Authority may, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, issue`
  line `directions to any Regional Transport Authority, and the Regional Transport Authority shall, in the`
  line `discharge of its functions under this Act, give effect to and be guided by such directions.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Transport Authority and any Regional Transport Authority, if authorised in this behalf`
  line `by rules made under section 96, may delegate such of its powers and functions to such authority or person`
  line `subject to such restrictions, limitations and conditions as may be prescribed by the said rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (28342)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 76
  title `General provision as to applications for permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28342&sectionno=69&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application for a permit shall be`
  line `made to the Regional Transport Authority of the region in which it is proposed to use the vehicle or`
  line `vehicles:`
  line
  line `Provided that if it is proposed to use the vehicle or vehicles in two or more regions lying within the`
  line `same State, the application shall be made to the Regional Transport Authority of the region in which the`
  line `major portion of the proposed route or area lies, and in case the portion of the proposed route or area in`
  line `each of the regions is approximately equal, to the Regional Transport Authority of the region in which it`
  line `is proposed to keep the vehicle or vehicles:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if it is proposed to use the vehicle or vehicles in two or more regions lying in`
  line `different States, the application shall be made to the Regional Transport Authority of the region in which`
  line `the applicant resides or has his principal place of business.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the State Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, direct that in the case of any vehicle or vehicles proposed to be used in two or`
  line `more regions lying in different States, the application under that sub-section shall be made to the State`
  line `Transport Authority of the region in which the applicant resides or has his principal place of business.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (28343)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 77
  title `Application for stage carriage permit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28343&sectionno=70&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for a permit in respect of a stage`
  line `carriage (in this Chapter referred to as a stage carriage permit) or as a reserve stage carriage shall, as far`
  line `as may be, contain the following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the route or routes or the area or areas to which the application relates;`
  line
  line `(b) the type and seating capacity of each such vehicle;`
  line
  line `(c) the minimum and maximum number of daily trips proposed to be provided and the time-table`
  line `of the normal trips.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, section 72, section 80 and section 102, "trip"`
  line `means a single journey from one point to another, and every return journey shall be deemed to be a`
  line `separate trip;`
  line
  line `(d) the number of vehicles intended to be kept in reserve to maintain the service and to provide`
  line `for special occasions;`
  line
  line `(e) the arrangements intended to be made for the housing, maintenance and repair of the vehicles,`
  line `for the comfort and convenience of passengers and for the storage and safe custody of luggage;`
  line
  line `(f) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) An application referred to in sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by such documents as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (28344)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 78
  title `Procedure of Regional Transport Authority in considering application for stage carriage permit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28344&sectionno=71&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Regional Transport Authority shall, while considering an application for a stage carriage`
  line `permit, have regard to the objects of this Act:`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) A Regional Transport Authority shall refuse to grant a stage carriage permit if it appears from any`
  line `time-table furnished that the provisions of this Act relating to the speed at which vehicles may be driven`
  line `are likely to be contravened:`
  line
  line `Provided that before such refusal an opportunity shall be given to the applicant to amend the timetable so as to conform to the said provisions.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) The State Government shall, if so directed by the Central Government having regard to the`
  line `number of vehicles, road conditions and other relevant matters, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct a State Transport Authority and a Regional Transport Authority to limit the number of stage`
  line `carriages generally or of any specified type, as may be fixed and specified in the notification, operating on`
  line `city routes in towns with a population of not less than five lakhs.`
  line
  line `(b) Where the number of stage carriages are fixed under clause (a), the Government of the State shall`
  line `reserve in the State certain percentage of stage carriage permits for the scheduled castes and the scheduled`
  line `tribes in the same ratio as in the case of appointments made by direct recruitment to public services in the`
  line State.
  line
  line `(c) Where the number of stage carriages are fixed under clause (a), the Regional Transport Authority`
  line `shall reserve such number of permits for the scheduled castes and the scheduled tribes as may be fixed by`
  line `the State Government under sub-clause (b).`
  line
  line `(d) After reserving such number of permits as is referred to in clause (c), the Regional Transport`
  line `Authority shall in considering an application have regard to the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) financial stability of the applicant;`
  line
  line `(ii) satisfactory performance as a stage carriage operator including payment of tax if the applicant`
  line `is or has been an operator of stage carriage service; and`
  line
  line `(iii) such other matters as may be prescribed by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that, other conditions being equal, preference shall be given to applications for permits`
  line from--
  line
  line `(i) State transport undertakings;`
  line
  line `(ii) co-operative societies registered or deemed to have been registered under any enactment for`
  line `the time being in force; ^2***`
  line
  line `(iii) ex-servicemen; ^3[or]`
  line
  line `^3[(iv) any other class or category of persons, as the State Government may, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing consider necessary.]`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section "company" means any body corporate, and includes a`
  line `firm or other association of individuals; and "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Kerala--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 71.--In section 71 of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988 (Central Act 59 of 1988),`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the principal Act), in sub-section (4).--`
  line
  line `(i) for the words "five" and “ten", the words "ten" and "fifty" shall, respectively, be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) for the words "any company", the words "any co-operative society or to any company" shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Kerala Act 12 of 1993, sec. 2.]`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Proviso omitted by Act 54 of 1994, s. 23 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line `2. The word "or" omitted by Act 54 of 1994, s. 23 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line `3. Ins.by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line `4. Sub-sections (4) and (5) omitted by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (28345)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 79
  title `Grant of stage carriage permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28345&sectionno=72&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 71, a Regional`
  line `Transport Authority may, on an application made to it under section 70, grant a stage carriage permit in`
  line `accordance with the application or with such modifications as it deems fit or refuse to grant such a permit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such permit shall be granted in respect of any route or area not specified in the`
  line application.
  line
  line `(2) The Regional Transport Authority, if it decides to grant a stage carriage permit, may grant the`
  line `permit for a stage carriage of a specified description and may, subject to any rules that may be made`
  line `under this Act, attach to the permit any one or more of the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) that the vehicles shall be used only in a specified area, or on a specified route or routes;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the operation of the stage carriage shall be commenced with effect from a specified date;`
  line
  line `(iii) the minimum and maximum number of daily trips to be provided in relation to any route or`
  line `area generally or on specified days and occasions;`
  line
  line `(iv) that copies of the time-table of the stage carriage approved by the Regional Transport`
  line `Authority shall be exhibited on the vehicles and at specified stands and halts on the route or within`
  line `the area;`
  line
  line `(v) that the stage carriage shall be operated within such margins of deviation from the approved`
  line `time-table as the Regional Transport Authority may from time to time specify;`
  line
  line `(vi) that within municipal limits and such other areas and places as may be prescribed, passengers`
  line `or goods shall not be taken up or set down except at specified points;`
  line
  line `(vii) the maximum number of passengers and the maximum weight of luggage that may be`
  line `carried on the stage carriage, either generally or on specified occasions or at specified times and`
  line seasons;
  line
  line `(viii) the weight and nature of passengers' luggage that shall be carried free of charge, the total`
  line `weight of luggage that may be carried in relation to each passenger, and the arrangements that shall`
  line `be made for the carriage of luggage without causing inconvenience to passengers;`
  line
  line `(ix) the rate of charge that may be levied for passengers' luggage in excess of the free allowance;`
  line
  line `(x) that vehicles of a specified type fitted with body conforming to approved specifications shall`
  line `be used:`
  line
  line `Provided that the attachment of this condition to a permit shall not prevent the continued use, for`
  line `a period of two years from the date of publication of the approved specifications, of any vehicle`
  line `operating on that date;`
  line
  line `(xi) that specified standards of comfort and cleanliness shall be maintained in the vehicles;`
  line
  line `(xii) the conditions subject to which goods may be carried in the stage carriage in addition to or to`
  line `the exclusion of passengers;`
  line
  line `(xiii) that fares shall be charged in accordance with the approved fare table;`
  line
  line `(xiv) that a copy of, or extract from, the fare table approved by the Regional Transport Authority`
  line `and particulars of any special fares or rates of fares so approved for particular occasions shall be`
  line `exhibited on the stage carriage and at specified stands and halts;`
  line
  line `(xv) that tickets bearing specified particulars shall be issued to passengers and shall show the`
  line `fares actually charged and that records of tickets issued shall be kept in a specified manner;`
  line
  line `(xvi) that mails shall be carried on the vehicle subject to such conditions (including conditions as`
  line `to the time in which mails are to be carried and the charges which may be levied) as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(xvii) the vehicles to be kept as reserve by the holder of the permit to maintain the operation and`
  line `to provide for special occasions;`
  line
  line `(xviii) the conditions subject to which vehicle may be used as a contract carriage;`
  line
  line `(xix) that specified arrangements shall be made for the housing, maintenance and repair of`
  line vehicle;
  line
  line `(xx) that any specified bus station or shelter maintained by Government or a local authority shall`
  line `be used and that any specified rent or fee shall be paid for such use;`
  line
  line `(xxi) that the conditions of the permit shall not be departed from, save with the approval of the`
  line `Regional Transport Authority;`
  line
  line `(xxii) that the Regional Transport Authority may, after giving notice of not less than one`
  line month,--
  line
  line `(a) vary the conditions of the permit;`
  line
  line `(b) attach to the permit further conditions:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conditions specified in pursuance of clause (i) shall not be varied so as to alter`
  line `the distance covered by the original route by more than 24 kilometers, and any variation within such`
  line `limits shall be made only after the Regional Transport Authority is satisfied that such variation will`
  line `serve the convenience of the public and that it is not expedient to grant a separate permit in respect of`
  line `the original route as so varied or any part thereof;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) that the holder of a permit shall furnish to the Regional Transport Authority such periodical`
  line `returns, statistics and other information as the State Government may from time to time prescribe;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) any other conditions which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Regional Transport Authority may waive any such condition for a stage carriage`
  line `permit operating in a rural area, as it deems fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (28346)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 80
  title `Application for contract carriage permit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28346&sectionno=73&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `An application for a permit in respect of a contract`
  line `carriage (in this Chapter referred to as a contract carriage permit) shall contain the following particulars,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the type and seating capacity of the vehicle;`
  line
  line `(b) the area for which the permit is required;`
  line
  line `(c) any other particulars which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (28347)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 81
  title `Grant of contract carriage permit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28347&sectionno=74&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), a Regional`
  line `Transport Authority may, on an application made to it under section 73, grant a contract carriage permit`
  line `in accordance with the application or with such modifications as it deems fit or refuse to grant such a`
  line `permit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such permit shall be granted in respect of any area not specified in the application.`
  line
  line `(2) The Regional Transport Authority, if it decides to grant a contract carriage permit, may, subject to`
  line `any rules that may be made under this Act, attach to the permit any one or more of the following`
  line `conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) that the vehicles shall be used only in a specified area or on a specified route or routes;`
  line
  line `(ii) that except in accordance with specified conditions, no contract of hiring, other than an`
  line `extension or modification of a subsisting contract, may be entered into outside the specified area;`
  line
  line `(iii) the maximum number of passengers and the maximum weight of luggage that may be carried`
  line `on the vehicles, either generally or on specified occasions or at specified times and seasons;`
  line
  line `(iv) the conditions subject to which goods may be carried in any contract carriage in addition to,`
  line `or to the exclusion of, passengers;`
  line
  line `(v) that, in the case of motor cabs, specified fares or rates of fares shall be charged and a copy of`
  line `the fare table shall be exhibited on the vehicle;`
  line
  line `(vi) that, in the case of vehicles other than motor cabs, specified rates of hiring not exceeding`
  line `specified maximum shall be charged;`
  line
  line `(vii) that, in the case of motor cabs, a special weight of passengers' luggage shall be carried free`
  line `of charge, and that the charge, if any, for any luggage in excess thereof shall be at a specified rate;`
  line
  line `(viii) that, in the case of motor cabs, a taximeter shall be fitted and maintained in proper working`
  line `order, if prescribed;`
  line
  line `(ix) that the Regional Transport Authority may, after giving notice of not less than one month,--`
  line
  line `(a) vary the conditions of the permit;`
  line
  line `(b) attach to the permit further conditions;`
  line
  line `(x) that the conditions of permit shall not be departed from save with the approval of the Regional`
  line `Transport Authority;`
  line
  line `(xi) that specified standards of comfort and cleanliness shall be maintained in the vehicles;`
  line
  line `(xii) that, except in the circumstances of exceptional nature, the plying of the vehicle or carrying`
  line `of the passengers shall not be refused;`
  line
  line `(xiii) any other conditions which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Regional Transport Authority may in the interests of last mile connectivity`
  line `waive any such condition in respect of any such types of vehicles as may be specified by the Central`
  line Government.]
  line
  line `(3) (a) The State Government shall, if so directed by the Central Government, having regard to the`
  line `number of vehicles, road conditions and other relevant matters, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct a State Transport Authority and a Regional Transport Authority to limit the number of contract`
  line `carriages generally or of any specified type, as may be fixed and specified in the notification, operating on`
  line `city routes in towns with a population of not less than five lakhs.`
  line
  line `(b) Where the number of contract carriages are fixed under clause (a), the Regional Transport`
  line `Authority shall, in considering an application for the grant of permit in respect of any such contract`
  line `carriage, have regard to the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) financial stability of the applicant;`
  line
  line `(ii) satisfactory performance as a contract carriage operator including payment of tax if the`
  line `applicant is or has been an operator of contract carriages; and`
  line
  line `(iii) such other matters as may be prescribed by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that, other conditions being equal, preference shall be given to applications for permits`
  line from--
  line
  line `(i) the India Tourism Development Corporation;`
  line
  line `(ii) State Tourism Development Corporations;`
  line
  line `(iii) State Tourism Departments;`
  line
  line `iv) State transport undertakings;`
  line
  line `(v) co-operative societies registered or deemed to have been registered under any enactment for`
  line `the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(vi) ex-servicemen;`
  line
  line `^1[(vii) self-help groups.]`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (28348)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 82
  title `Scheme for renting of motor cabs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 24, for "motor cabs to persons desiring to drive the cabs" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28348&sectionno=75&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make a scheme for the purpose of regulating the business of renting of ^1[motor cabs or`
  line `motor cycles to persons desiring to drive either by themselves or through drivers, motor cabs or motor`
  line `cycles] for their own use and for matters connected therewith.`
  line
  line `(2) A scheme made under sub-section (1) may provide for all or any of the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) licensing of operators under the scheme including grant, renewal and revocation of such`
  line licences;
  line
  line `(b) form of application and form of licences and the particulars to be contained therein;`
  line
  line `(c) fee to be paid with the application for such licences;`
  line
  line `(d) the authorities to which the application shall be made;`
  line
  line `(e) condition subject to which such licences may be granted, renewed or revoked;`
  line
  line `(f) appeals against orders of refusal to grant or renew such licences and appeals against orders`
  line `revoking such licences;`
  line
  line `(g) conditions subject to which motor cabs may be rented;`
  line
  line `(h) maintenance of records and inspection of such records;`
  line
  line `(i) such other matters as may be necessary to carry out the purposes of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (28349)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 83
  title `Application for private service vehicle permit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28349&sectionno=76&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Regional Transport Authority may, on`
  line `an application made to it, grant a private service vehicle permit in accordance with the application or with`
  line `such modification as it deems fit or refuse to grant such permit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such permit shall be granted in respect of any area or route not specified in the`
  line application.
  line
  line `(2) An application for a permit to use a motor vehicle as a private service vehicle shall contain the`
  line `following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) type and seating capacity of the vehicle;`
  line
  line `(b) the area or the route or routes to which the application relates;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which it is claimed that the purpose of carrying persons otherwise than for hire`
  line `or reward or in connection with the trade or business carried on by the applicant will be served by the`
  line `vehicle; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other particulars which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Regional Transport Authority if it decides to grant the permit may, subject to any rules that`
  line `may be made under this Act, attach to the permit any one or more of the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) that the vehicle be used only in a specified area or on a specified route or routes;`
  line
  line `(ii) the maximum number of persons and the maximum weight of luggage that may be carried;`
  line
  line `(iii) that the Regional Transport Authority may, after giving notice of not less than one month--`
  line
  line `(a) vary the conditions of the permit;`
  line
  line `(b) attach to the permit further conditions;`
  line
  line `(iv) that the conditions of permit shall not be departed from, save with the approval of the`
  line `Regional Transport Authority;`
  line
  line `(v) that specified standards of comforts and cleanliness shall be maintained in the vehicle;`
  line
  line `(vi) that the holder of the permit shall furnish to the Regional Transport Authority such periodical`
  line `returns, statistics and other information as the State Government may, from time to time, specify; and`
  line
  line `(vii) such other conditions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (28350)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 84
  title `Application for goods carriage permit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28350&sectionno=77&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `An application for a permit to use a motor vehicle for`
  line `the carriage of goods for hire or reward or for the carriage of goods for or in connection with a trade or`
  line `business carried on by the applicant (in this Chapter referred to as a goods carriage permit) shall, as far as`
  line `may be, contain the following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the area or the route or routes to which the application relates;`
  line
  line `(b) the type and capacity of the vehicle;`
  line
  line `(c) the nature of the goods it is proposed to carry;`
  line
  line `(d) the arrangements intended to be made for the housing, maintenance and repair of the vehicle`
  line `and for the storage and safe custody of the goods;`
  line
  line `(e) such particulars as the Regional Transport Authority may require with respect to any business`
  line `as a carrier of goods for hire or reward carried on by the applicant at any time before the making of`
  line `the application, and of the rates charged by the applicant;`
  line
  line `(f) particulars of any agreement, or arrangement, affecting in any material respect the provision`
  line `within the region of the Regional Transport Authority of facilities for the transport of goods for hire`
  line `or reward, entered into by the applicant with any other person by whom such facilities are provided,`
  line `whether within or without the region;`
  line
  line `(g) any other particulars which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (28351)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 85
  title `Consideration of application for goods carriage permit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28351&sectionno=78&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `A Regional Transport Authority`
  line `shall, in considering an application for a goods carriage permit, have regard to the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the nature of the goods to be carried with special reference to their dangerous or hazardous`
  line `nature to human life;`
  line
  line `(b) the nature of the chemicals or explosives to be carried with special reference to the safety to`
  line `human life.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (28352)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 86
  title `Grant of goods carriage permit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28352&sectionno=79&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Regional Transport Authority may, on an application`
  line `made to it under section 77, grant a goods carriage permit to be valid throughout the State or in`
  line `accordance with the application or with such modifications as it deems fit or refuse to grant such a permit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such permit shall be granted in respect of any area or route not specified in the`
  line application.
  line
  line `(2) The Regional Transport Authority, if it decides to grant a goods carriage permit, may grant the`
  line `permit and may, subject to any rules that may be made under this Act, attach to the permit any one or`
  line `more of the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) that the vehicle shall be used only in a specified area or on a specified route or routes;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the gross vehicle weight of any vehicle used shall not exceed a specified maximum;`
  line
  line `(iii) that goods of a specified nature shall not be carried;`
  line
  line `(iv) that goods shall be carried at specified rates;`
  line
  line `(v) that specified arrangement shall be made for the housing, maintenance and repair of the`
  line `vehicle and the storage and safe custody of the goods carried;`
  line
  line `(vi) that the holder of the permit shall furnish to the Regional Transport Authority such periodical`
  line `returns, statistics and other information as the State Government may, from time to time, prescribe;`
  line
  line `(vii) that the Regional Transport Authority may, after giving notice of not less than one month,--`
  line
  line `(a) vary the conditions of the permit;`
  line
  line `(b) attach to the permit further conditions;`
  line
  line `(viii) that the conditions of the permit shall not be departed from, save with the approval of the`
  line `Regional Transport Authority;`
  line
  line `(ix) any other conditions which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The conditions referred to in sub-section (2) may include conditions relating to the packaging and`
  line `carriage of goods of dangerous or hazardous nature to human life.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (28353)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 87
  title `Procedure in applying for and granting permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28353&sectionno=80&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for a permit of any kind`
  line `may be made at any time.`
  line
  line `(2) A ^1[Regional Transport Authority, State Transport Authority or any prescribed authority referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1) of section 66] shall not ordinarily refuse to grant an application for permit of any`
  line `kind made at any time under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^1[Regional Transport Authority, State Transport Authority or any prescribed`
  line `authority referred to in sub-section (1) of section 66] may summarily refuse the application if the grant of`
  line `any permit in accordance with the application would have the effect of increasing the number of stage`
  line `carriages as fixed and specified in a notification in the Official Gazette under clause (a) of sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 71 or of contract carriages as fixed and specified in a notification in the Official Gazette under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 74:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where a ^2[Regional Transport Authority, State Transport Authority or any`
  line `prescribed authority referred to in sub-section (1) of section 66] refuses an application for the grant of a`
  line `permit of any kind under this Act, it shall give to the applicant in writing its reasons for the refusal of the`
  line `same and an opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `(3) An application to vary the conditions of any permit, other than a temporary permit, by the`
  line `inclusion of a new route or routes of a new area or by altering the route or routes or area covered by it, or`
  line `in the case of a stage carriage permit by increasing the number of trips above the specified maximum or`
  line `by the variation, extension or curtailment of the route or routes or the area specified in the permit shall be`
  line `treated as an application for the grant of a new permit:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall not be necessary so to treat an application made by the holder of stage carriage`
  line `permit who provides the only service on any route to increase the frequency of the service so provided`
  line `without any increase in the number of vehicles:`
  line
  line `Provided further that,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of variation, the termini shall not be altered and the distance covered by the`
  line `variation shall not exceed twenty-four kilometres;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of extension, the distance covered by extension shall not exceed twenty-four`
  line `kilometres from the termini,`
  line
  line `and any such variation or extension within such limits shall be made only after the transport authority is`
  line `satisfied that such variation will serve the convenience of the public and that it is not expedient to grant a`
  line `separate permit in respect of the original route as so varied or extended or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) A ^2[Regional Transport Authority, State Transport Authority or any prescribed authority referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1) of section 66] may, before such date as may be specified by it in this behalf, replace`
  line `any permit granted by it before the said date by a fresh permit conforming to the provisions of section 72`
  line `or section 74 or section 76 or section 79, as the case may be, and the fresh permit shall be valid for the`
  line `same route or routes or the same area for which the replaced permit was valid:`
  line
  line `Provided that no condition other than a condition which was already attached to the replaced permit`
  line `or which could have been attached thereto under the law in force when that permit was granted shall be`
  line `attached to the fresh permit except with the consent in writing of the holder of the permit.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 81, a permit issued under the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (4) shall be effective without renewal for the remainder of the period during which the`
  line `replaced permit would have been so effective.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 25, for "Regional Transport Authority" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 25, for "Regional Transport Authority" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (28354)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 88
  title `Duration and renewal of permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 26, ibid., for "without renewal" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28354&sectionno=81&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) A permit other than a temporary permit issued under`
  line `section 87 or a special permit issued under sub-section (8) of section 88 shall be effective ^1[from the date`
  line `of issuance or renewal thereof] for a period of five years:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the permit is countersigned under sub-section (1) of section 88, such`
  line `countersignature shall remain effective without renewal for such period so as to synchronise with the`
  line `validity of the primary permit.`
  line
  line `(2) A permit may be renewed on an application made not less than fifteen days before the date of its`
  line expiry.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Regional Transport Authority or the`
  line `State Transport Authority, as the case may be, may entertain an application for the renewal of a permit`
  line `after the last date specified in that sub-section if it is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by good`
  line `and sufficient cause from making an application within the time specified.`
  line
  line `(4) The Regional Transport Authority or the State Transport Authority, as the case may be, may reject`
  line `an application for the renewal of a permit on one or more of the following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the financial condition of the applicant as evidenced by insolvency, or decrees for payment of`
  line `debts remaining unsatisfied for a period of thirty days, prior to the date of consideration of the`
  line application;
  line
  line `(b) the applicant had been punished twice or more for any of the following offences within twelve`
  line `months reckoned from fifteen days prior to the date of consideration of the application committed as a`
  line `result of the operation of a stage carriage service by the applicant, namely:`
  line
  line `(i) plying any vehicle--`
  line
  line `(1) without payment of tax due on such vehicle;`
  line
  line `(2) without payment of tax during the grace period allowed for payment of such tax and`
  line `then stop the plying of such vehicle;`
  line
  line `(3) on any unauthorised route;`
  line
  line `(ii) making unauthorised trips:`
  line
  line `Provided that in computing the number of punishments for the purpose of clause (b), any punishment`
  line `stayed by the order of an appellate authority shall not be taken into account:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no application under this sub-section shall be rejected unless an opportunity of`
  line `being heard is given to the applicant.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a permit has been renewed under this section after the expiry of the period thereof, such`
  line `renewal shall have effect from the date of such expiry irrespective of whether or not a temporary permit has been granted under clause (d) of section 87, and where a temporary permit has been granted, the fee`
  line `paid in respect of such temporary permit shall be refunded.`
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (28355)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 89
  title `Transfer of permit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28355&sectionno=82&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as provided in sub-section (2), a permit shall not be transferable`
  line `from one person to another except with the permission of the transport authority which granted the permit`
  line `and shall not, without such permission, operate to confer on any person to whom a vehicle covered by the`
  line `permit is transferred any right to use that vehicle in the manner authorised by the permit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the holder of a permit dies, the person succeeding to the possession of the vehicle covered`
  line `by the permit may, for a period of three months, use the permit as if it had been granted to himself:`
  line
  line `Provided that such person has, within thirty days of the death of the holder, informed the transport`
  line `authority which granted the permit of the death of the holder and of his own intention to use the permit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no permit shall be so used after the date on which it would have ceased to be`
  line `effective without renewal in the hands of the deceased holder.`
  line
  line `(3) The transport authority may, on application made to it within three months of the death of the`
  line `holder of a permit, transfer the permit to the person succeeding to the possession of the vehicles covered`
  line `by the permit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the transport authority may entertain an application made after the expiry of the said`
  line `period of three months if it is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by good and sufficient cause from`
  line `making an application within the time specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (28356)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 90
  title `Replacement of vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28356&sectionno=83&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `The holder of a permit may, with the permission of the authority by`
  line `which the permit was granted, replace any vehicle covered by the permit by any other vehicle of the same`
  line nature.
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (28357)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 91
  title `General conditions attaching to all permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28357&sectionno=84&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `The following shall be conditions of every`
  line permit--
  line
  line `(a) that the vehicle to which the permit relates carries valid certificate of fitness issued under`
  line `section 56 and is at all times so maintained as to comply with the requirements of this Act and the`
  line `rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) that the vehicle to which the permit relates is not driven at a speed exceeding the speed`
  line `permitted under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) that any prohibition or restriction imposed and any fares or freight fixed by notification made`
  line `under section 67 are observed in connection with the vehicle to which the permit relates;`
  line
  line `(d) that the vehicle to which the permit relates is not driven in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `section 5 or section 113;`
  line
  line `(e) that the provisions of this Act limiting the hours of work of drivers are observed in connection`
  line `with any vehicle or vehicles to which the permit relates;`
  line
  line `(f) that the provisions of Chapters X, XI and XII so far as they apply to the holder of the permit`
  line `are observed; and`
  line
  line `(g) that the name and address of the operator shall be painted or otherwise firmly affixed to every`
  line `vehicle to which the permit relates on the exterior of the body of that vehicle on both sides thereof in`
  line `a colour or colours vividly contrasting to the colour of the vehicle centered as high as practicable`
  line `below the window line in bold letters.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (28358)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 92
  title `General form of permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28358&sectionno=85&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `Every permit issued under this Act shall be complete in itself and`
  line `shall contain all the necessary particulars of the permit and the conditions attached thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (28359)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 93
  title `Cancellation and suspension of permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28359&sectionno=86&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) The transport authority which granted a permit`
  line `may cancel the permit or may suspend it for such period as it thinks fit--`
  line
  line `(a) on the breach of any condition specified in section 84 or of any condition contained in the`
  line `permit, or`
  line
  line `(b) if the holder of the permit uses or causes or allows a vehicle to be used in any manner not`
  line `authorised by the permit, or`
  line
  line `(c) if the holder of the permit ceases to own the vehicle covered by the permit, or`
  line
  line `(d) if the holder of the permit has obtained the permit by fraud or misrepresentation, or`
  line
  line `(e) if the holder of the goods carriage permit, fails without reasonable cause, to use the vehicle for`
  line `the purposes for which the permit was granted, or`
  line
  line `(f) if the holder of the permit acquires the citizenship of any foreign country:`
  line
  line `Provided that no permit shall be suspended or cancelled unless an opportunity has been given to the`
  line `holder of the permit to furnish his explanation.`
  line
  line `(2) The transport authority may exercise the powers conferred on it under sub-section (1) in relation`
  line `to a permit granted by any authority or person to whom power in this behalf has been delegated under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 68 as if the said permit was a permit granted by the transport authority.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a transport authority cancels or suspends a permit, it shall give to the holder in writing its`
  line `reasons for the action taken.`
  line
  line `(4) The powers exercisable under sub-section (1) (other than the power to cancel a permit) by the`
  line `transport authority which granted the permit may be exercised by any authority or person to whom such`
  line `powers have been delegated under sub-section (5) of section 68.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a permit is liable to be cancelled or suspended under clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (e)`
  line `of sub-section (1) and the transport authority is of opinion that having regard to the circumstances of the`
  line `case, it would not be necessary or expedient so to cancel or suspend the permit if the holder of the permit`
  line `agrees to pay a certain sum of money, then, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the`
  line `transport authority may, instead of cancelling or suspending the permit, as the case may be, recover from`
  line `the holder of the permit the sum of money agreed upon.`
  line
  line `(6) The powers exercisable by the transport authority under sub-section (5) may, where an appeal has`
  line `been preferred under section 89, be exercised also by the appellate authority.`
  line
  line `(7) In relation to a permit referred to in sub-section (9) of section 88, the powers exercisable under`
  line `sub-section (1) (other than the power to cancel a permit) by the transport authority which granted the`
  line `permit, may be exercised by any transport authority and any authority or persons to whom power in this`
  line `behalf has been delegated under sub-section (5) of section 68, as if the said permit was a permit granted`
  line `by any such authority or persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (28360)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 94
  title `Temporary permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28360&sectionno=87&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Regional Transport Authority and the State Transport Authority`
  line `may without following the procedure laid down in section 80, grant permits, to be effective for a limited`
  line `period which shall, not in any case exceed four months, to authorise the use of a transport vehicle`
  line temporarily--
  line
  line `(a) for the conveyance of passengers on special occasions such as to and from fairs and religious`
  line `gatherings, or`
  line
  line `(b) for the purposes of a seasonal business, or`
  line
  line `(c) to meet a particular temporary need, or`
  line
  line `(d) pending decision on an application for the renewal of a permit,`
  line
  line `and may attach to any such permit such condition as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Regional Transport Authority or, as the case may be, State Transport Authority may,`
  line `in the case of goods carriages, under the circumstances of an exceptional nature, and for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, grant a permit for a period exceeding four months, but not exceeding one year.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a temporary permit may be granted`
  line `thereunder in respect of any route or area where`
  line
  line `(i) no permit could be issued under section 72 or section 74 or section 76 or section 79 in respect`
  line `of that route or area by reason of an order of a court or other competent authority restraining the issue of the same, for a period not exceeding the period for which the issue of the permit has been so`
  line `restrained; or`
  line
  line `(ii) as a result of the suspension by a court or other competent authority of the permit of any`
  line `vehicle in respect of that route or area, there is no transport vehicle of the same class with a valid`
  line `permit in respect of that route or area, or there is no adequate number of such vehicles in respect of`
  line `that route or area, for a period not exceeding the period of such suspension.`
  line
  line `Provided that the number of transport vehicles in respect of which temporary permits are so granted`
  line `shall not exceed the number of vehicles in respect of which the issue of the permits have been restrained`
  line `or, as the case may be, the permit has been suspended:`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (28361)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 95
  title `Validation of permits for use outside region in which granted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28361&sectionno=88&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as may be`
  line `otherwise prescribed, a permit granted by the Regional Transport Authority of any one region shall not be`
  line `valid in any other region, unless the permit has been countersigned by the Regional Transport Authority`
  line `of that other rigion, and a permit granted in any one State shall not be valid in any other State unless`
  line `countersigned by the State Transport Authority of that other State or by the Regional Transport Authority`
  line `concerned:`
  line
  line `Provided that a goods carriage permit, granted by the Regional Transport Authority of any one region,`
  line `for any area in any other region or regions within the same State shall be valid in that area without the`
  line `countersignature of the Regional Transport Authority of the other region or of each of the other regions`
  line `concerned:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where both the starting point and the terminal point of a route are situate within`
  line `the same State, but part of such route lies in any other State and the length of such part does not exceed`
  line `sixteen kilometres, the permit shall be valid in the other State in respect of that part of the route which is`
  line `in that other State notwithstanding that such permit has not been countersigned by the State Transport`
  line `Authority or the Regional Transport Authority of that other State:`
  line
  line `Provided also that--`
  line
  line `(a) where a motor vehicle covered by a permit granted in one State is to be used for the purposes`
  line `of defence in any other State, such vehicle shall display a certificate, in such form, and issued by such`
  line `Authority, as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify, to the effect that the vehicle shall be used for the period specified therein exclusively for the purposes of`
  line `defence; and`
  line
  line `(b) any such permit shall be valid in that other State notwithstanding that such permit has not`
  line `been countersigned by the State Transport Authority or the Regional Transport Authority of that other`
  line State.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a permit granted or countersigned by a`
  line `State Transport Authority shall be valid in the whole State or in such regions within the State as may be`
  line `specified in the permit.`
  line
  line `(3) A Regional Transport Authority when countersigning the permit may attach to the permit any`
  line `condition which it might have imposed if it had granted the permit and may likewise vary any condition`
  line `attached to the permit by the authority by which the permit was granted.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this Chapter relating to the grant, revocation and suspension of permits shall`
  line `apply to the grant, revocation and suspension of countersignatures of permits:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall not be necessary to follow the procedure laid down in section 80 for the grant of`
  line `countersignatures of permits, where the permits granted in any one State are required to be countersigned`
  line `by the State Transport Authority of another State or by the Regional Transport Authority concerned as a`
  line `result of any agreement arrived at between the States after complying with the requirements of`
  line `sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `(5) Every proposal to enter into an agreement between the States to fix the number of permits which`
  line `is proposed to be granted or countersigned in respect of each route or area, shall be published by each of`
  line `the State Governments concerned in the Official Gazette and in any one or more of the newspapers in`
  line `regional language circulating in the area or route proposed to be covered by the agreement together with a`
  line `notice of the date before which representations in connection therewith may be submitted, and the date`
  line `not being less than thirty days from the date of publication in the Official Gazette, on which, and the`
  line `authority by which, and the time and place at which, the proposal and any representation received in`
  line `connection therewith will be considered.`
  line
  line `(6) Every agreement arrived at between the States shall, in so far as it relates to the grant of`
  line `countersignature of permits, be published by each of the State Governments concerned in the Official`
  line `Gazette and in any one or more of the newspapers in the regional language circulating in the area or route`
  line `covered by the agreement and the State Transport Authority of the State and the Regional Transport`
  line `Authority concerned shall give effect to it.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a Regional Transport Authority of one`
  line `region may issue a temporary permit under section 87 to be valid in another region or State with the`
  line `concurrence, given generally or for the particular occasion, of the Regional Transport Authority of that`
  line `other region or of the State Transport Authority of that other State, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), but subject to any rules that may be made`
  line `under this Act by the Central Government, the Regional Transport Authority of any one region or, as the`
  line `case may be, the State Transport Authority, may, for the convenience of the public, ^1[grant a special`
  line `permit to any public service vehicle including any vehicle covered] by a permit issued under section 72`
  line `(including a reserve stage carriage) or under section 74 or under sub-section (9) of this section for`
  line `carrying a passenger or passengers for hire or reward under a contract, express or implied, for the use of`
  line `the vehicle as a whole without stopping to pick up or set down along the line of route passengers not`
  line `included in the contract, and in every case where such special permit is granted, the Regional Transport`
  line `Authority shall assign to the vehicle, for display thereon, a special distinguishing mark in the form and`
  line `manner specified by the Central Government and such special permit shall be valid in any other region or`
  line `State without the countersignature of the Regional Transport Authority of the other region or of the State`
  line `Transport Authority of the other State, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(9) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) but subject to any rules that may be made`
  line `by the Central Government under sub-section (14), any State Transport Authority may, for the purpose of`
  line `promoting tourism, grant permits in respect of tourist vehicles valid for the whole of India, or in such`
  line `contiguous States not being less than three in number including the State in which the permit is issued as`
  line `may be specified in such permit in accordance with the choice indicated in the application and the`
  line `provisions of sections 73, 74, 80, 81, 82, 83, 84, 85, 86 ^2[clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 87 and`
  line `section 89] shall, as far as may be, apply in relation to such permits.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(11) The following shall be conditions of every permit granted under sub-section (9), namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) every motor vehicle in respect of which such permit is granted shall conform to such`
  line `description, requirement regarding the seating capacity, standards of comforts, amenities and other`
  line `matters, as the Central Government may specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(ii) every such motor vehicle shall be driven by a person having such qualifications and satisfying`
  line `such conditions as may be specified by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(iii) such other conditions as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(12) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), but, subject to the rules that may be made`
  line `by the Central Government under sub-section (14), the appropriate authority may, for the purpose of`
  line `encouraging long distance inter-State road transport, grant in a State, national permits in respect of goods`
  line `carriages and the provisions of sections 69, 77, 79, 80, 81, 82, 83, 84, 85, 86 ^2[clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 87 and section 89] shall, as far as may be, apply to or in relation to the grant of`
  line `national permits.`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(14) (a) The Central Government may make rules for carrying out the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(b) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the authorisation fee payable for the issue of a permit referred to in sub-sections (9) and (12);`
  line
  line `(ii) the fixation of the laden weight of the motor vehicle;`
  line
  line `(iii) the distinguishing particulars or marks to be carried or exhibited in or on the motor vehicle;`
  line
  line `(iv) the colour or colours in which the motor vehicle is to be painted;`
  line
  line `(v) such other matters as the appropriate authority shall consider in granting a national permit.`
  line `Explanation.-- In this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appropriate authority", in relation to a national permit, means the authority which is`
  line `authorised under this Act to grant a goods carriage permit;`
  line
  line `(b) "authorisation fee" means the annual fee, not exceeding one thousand rupees, which may be`
  line `charged by the appropriate authority of a State to enable a motor vehicle, covered by the permit`
  line `referred to in sub-sections (9) and (12) to be used in other States subject to the payment of taxes or`
  line `fees, if any, levied by the States concerned;`
  line
  line `(c) "national permit" means a permit granted by the appropriate authority to goods carriages to`
  line `operate throughout the territory of India or in such contiguous States, not being less than four in`
  line `number, including the State in which the permit is issued as may be specified in such permit in`
  line `accordance with the choice indicated in the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 27, for "grant a special permit in relation to a vehicle covered" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 27 for "and 89" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (10) omitted by s. 27, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (13) omitted by s. 27, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_88_a:
  sectionId (49497)
  sectionNo 88A
  orderNo 96
  title `Power of Central Government to make schemes for national, multimodal and inter-State transport of passengers and goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).br`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49497&sectionno=88A&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_88_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[88A. Power of Central Government to make schemes for national, multimodal and inter-State`
  line `transport of passengers and goods.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, modify any permit issued under this Act or`
  line `make schemes for national, multimodal and inter-State transportation of goods or passengers, and issue or`
  line `modify licences under, such scheme for the following purposes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) last mile connectivity;`
  line
  line `(b) rural transport;`
  line
  line `(c) improving the movement of freight, and logistics;`
  line
  line `(d) better utilisation of transportation assets;`
  line
  line `(e) the enhancement to the economic vitality of the area, especially by enabling competitiveness,`
  line `productivity and efficiency;`
  line
  line `(f) the increase in the accessibility and mobility of people;`
  line
  line `(g) the protection and enhancement of the environment;`
  line
  line `(h) the promotion of energy conservation;`
  line
  line `(i) improvement of the quality of life;`
  line
  line `(j) enhancement of the integration and connectivity of the transportation system, across and`
  line `between modes of transport; and`
  line
  line `(k) such other matters as the Central Government may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, before taking any action under this sub-section seek`
  line `concurrence of the State Governments.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), two or more States may make schemes for`
  line `the operation within such States for the inter-State transportation of goods or passengers:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the event of any repugnancy between the schemes made by the Central Government`
  line `under sub-section (1) and schemes made by two or more States under this sub-section, the schemes made`
  line `under sub-section (1) shall prevail.]`
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (28362)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 97
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28362&sectionno=89&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person--`
  line
  line `(a) aggrieved by the refusal of the State or a Regional Transport Authority to grant a permit, or by`
  line `any condition attached to a permit granted to him, or`
  line
  line `(b) aggrieved by the revocation or suspension of the permit or by any variation of the conditions`
  line `thereof, or`
  line
  line `(c) aggrieved by the refusal to transfer the permit under section 82, or`
  line
  line `(d) aggrieved by the refusal of the State or a Regional Transport Authority to countersign a`
  line `permit, or by any condition attached to such countersignature, or`
  line
  line `(e) aggrieved by the refusal of renewal of a permit, or`
  line
  line `(f) aggrieved by the refusal to grant permission under section 83, or`
  line
  line `(g) aggrieved by any other order which may be prescribed, may, within the prescribed time and in`
  line `the prescribed manner, appeal to the State Transport Appellate Tribunal constituted under`
  line `sub-section (2), who shall, after giving such person and the original authority an opportunity of being`
  line `heard, give a decision thereon which shall be final.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The State Government shall constitute such number of Transport Appellate Tribunals as`
  line `it thinks fit and each such Tribunal shall consist of a judicial officer who is not below the rank of a District Judge or who is qualified to be a Judge of the High Court and it shall exercise jurisdiction`
  line `within such area as may be notified by that Government.]`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub- section (2), every appeal pending`
  line `at the commencement of this Act, shall continue to be proceeded with and disposed of as if this Act had`
  line `not been passed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that when any order is made by the`
  line `State Transport Authority or the Regional Transport Authority in pursuance of a direction issued by the`
  line `Inter-State Transport Commission under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 63A of the Motor`
  line `Vehicles Act, 1939 (4 of 1939), as it stood immediately before the commencement of this Act, and any`
  line `person feels aggrieved by such order on the ground that it is not in consonance with such direction, he`
  line `may appeal under sub-section (1) to the State Transport Appellate Tribunal against such order but not`
  line `against the direction so issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (28363)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 98
  title Revision.
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28363&sectionno=90&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `The State Transport Appellate Tribunal may, on an application made to it, call for the`
  line `record of any case in which an order has been made by a State Transport Authority or Regional Transport`
  line `Authority against which no appeal lies, and if it appears to the State Transport Authority Appellate Tribunal that the`
  line `order made by the State Transport Authority or Regional Transport Authority is improper or illegal, the`
  line `State Transport Appellate Tribunal may pass such order in relation to the case as it deems fit and every`
  line `such order shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Transport Appellate Tribunal shall not entertain any application from a person`
  line `aggrieved by an order of a State Transport Authority or Regional Transport Authority, unless the`
  line `application is made within thirty days from the date of the order:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the State Transport Appellate Tribunal may entertain the application after the`
  line `expiry of the said period of thirty days, if it is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by good and`
  line `sufficient cause from making the application in time:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the State Transport Appellate Tribunal shall not pass an order under this section`
  line `prejudicial to any person without giving him a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (28364)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 99
  title `Restriction of hours of work of drivers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 29, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28364&sectionno=91&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) The hours of work of any person engaged for`
  line `operating a transport vehicle shall be such as provided in the Motor Transport Workers Act, 1961 (27 of`
  line `1961).]`
  line
  line `(2) A State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, grant such exemptions from the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1) as it thinks fit, to meet cases of emergency or of delays by reason of`
  line `circumstances which could not be foreseen.`
  line
  line `(3) A State Government or, if authorised in this behalf by the State Government by rules made under`
  line `section 96, the State or a Regional Transport Authority may require persons employing any person whose`
  line `work is subject to any of the provisions of sub-section (1) to fix beforehand the hours of work of such`
  line `persons so as to conform to those provisions, and may provide for the recording of the hours so fixed.`
  line
  line `(4) No person shall work or shall cause or allow any other person to work outside the hours fixed or`
  line `recorded for the work of such persons under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) A State Government may prescribe the circumstances under which and the period during which`
  line `the driver of a vehicle although not engaged in work is required to remain on or near the vehicle may be`
  line `deemed to be an interval for rest within the meaning of sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (28365)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 100
  title `Voidance of contracts restrictive of liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 35, for "stage carriage or contract carriage, in respect of which a permit" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28365&sectionno=92&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `Any contract for the conveyance of a passenger`
  line `in a ^1[transport vehicle, in respect of which a permit or licence] has been issued under this Chapter, shall,`
  line `so far as it purports to negative or restrict the liability of any person in respect of any claim made against`
  line `that person in respect of the death of, or bodily injury to, the passenger while being carried in, entering or alighting from the vehicle, or purports to impose any conditions with respect to the enforcement of any`
  line `such liability, be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (28366)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 101
  title `Agent or canvasser or aggregator to obtain licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28366&sectionno=93&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `^1[Agent or canvasser or aggregator to obtain licence.]--(1) No person shall engage himself--`
  line
  line `(i) as an agent or a canvasser, in the sale of tickets for travel by public service vehicles or in`
  line `otherwise soliciting custom for such vehicles, or`
  line
  line `(ii) as an agent in the business of collecting, forwarding or distributing goods carried by goods`
  line carriages,
  line
  line `^2[(iii) as an aggregator,]`
  line
  line `unless he has obtained a licence from such authority and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed`
  line `by the State Government.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that while issuing the licence to an aggregator the State Government may follow such`
  line `guidelines as may be issued by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every aggregator shall comply with the provisions of the Information`
  line `Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000) and the rules and regulations made there under.]`
  line
  line `(2) The conditions referred to in sub-section (1) may include all or any of the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the period for which a licence may be granted or renewed;`
  line
  line `(b) the fee payable for the issue or renewal of the licence;`
  line
  line `(c) the deposit of security--`
  line
  line `(i) of a sum not exceeding rupees fifty thousand in the case of an agent in the business of`
  line `collecting, forwarding or distributing goods carried by goods carriages;`
  line
  line `(ii) of a sum not exceeding rupees five thousand in the case of any other agent or canvasser,`
  line `and the circumstances under which the security may be forfeited;`
  line
  line `(d) the provision by the agent of insurance of goods in transit;`
  line
  line `(e) the authority by which and the circumstances under which the licence may be suspended or`
  line revoked;
  line
  line `(f) such other conditions as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be a condition of every licence that no agent or canvasser to whom the licence is granted`
  line `shall advertise in any newspaper, book, list, classified directory or other publication unless there is`
  line `contained in such advertisement appearing in such newspapers, book, list, classified directory or other`
  line `publication the licence number, the date of expiry of licence and the particulars of the authority which`
  line `granted the licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 36, for "Agent or canvasser to obtain licence" (w.e.f. 27-11-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 36, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-11-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (28367)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 102
  title `Bar on jurisdiction of Civil Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28367&sectionno=94&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `No Civil Court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any`
  line `question relating to the grant of a permit ^1[or licence issued under any scheme] under this Act, and no`
  line `injunction in respect of any action taken or to be taken by the duly constituted authorities under this Act`
  line `with regard to the grant of a permit ^1[or licence issued under any scheme], shall be entertained by any`
  line `Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (28368)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 103
  title `Power of State Government to make rules as to stage carriages and contract carriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28368&sectionno=95&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `A State Government may make rules to regulate, in respect of stage carriages and contract carriages and`
  line `the conduct of passengers in such vehicles.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, such rules may--`
  line
  line `(a) authorise the removal from such vehicle of any person contravening the rules by the driver or`
  line `conductor of the vehicle, or, on the request of the driver or conductor, or any passenger, by any police`
  line officer;
  line
  line `(b) require a passenger who is reasonably suspected by the driver or conductor of contravening`
  line `the rules to give his name and address to a police officer or to the driver or conductor on demand;`
  line
  line `(c) require a passenger to declare, if so demanded by the driver or conductor, the journey he`
  line `intends to take or has taken in the vehicle and to pay the fare for the whole of such journey and to`
  line `accept any ticket issued therefor;`
  line
  line `(d) require, on demand being made for the purpose by the driver or conductor or other person`
  line `authorised by the owners of the vehicle, production during the journey and surrender at the end of the`
  line `journey by the holder thereof of any ticket issued to him;`
  line
  line `(e) require a passenger, if so requested by the driver or conductor, to leave the vehicle on the`
  line `completion of the journey the fare for which he has paid;`
  line
  line `(f) require the surrender by the holder thereof on the expiry of the period for which it is issued of`
  line `a ticket issued to him;`
  line
  line `(g) require a passenger to abstain from doing anything which is likely to obstruct or interfere with`
  line `the working of the vehicle or to cause damage to any part of the vehicle or its equipment or to cause`
  line `injury or discomfort to any other passenger;`
  line
  line `(h) require a passenger not to smoke in any vehicle on which a notice prohibiting smoking is`
  line exhibited;
  line
  line `(i) require the maintenance of complaint books in stage carriages and prescribe the conditions`
  line `under which passengers can record any complaints in the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (28369)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 104
  title `Power of State Government to make rules for the purposes of this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28369&sectionno=96&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State`
  line `Government may make rules for the purpose of carrying into effect the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, rules under this section may be made`
  line `with respect to all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the period of appointment and the terms of appointment of and the conduct of business by`
  line `Regional and State Transport Authorities and the reports to be furnished by them;`
  line
  line `(ii) the conduct of business by any such authority in the absence of any member (including the`
  line `Chairman) thereof and the nature of business which, the circumstances under which and the manner`
  line `in which, business could be so conducted;`
  line
  line `(iii) the conduct and hearing of appeals that may be preferred under this Chapter, the fees to be`
  line `paid in respect of such appeals and the refund of such fees;`
  line
  line `(iv) the forms to be used for the purposes of this Chapter, including the forms of permits;`
  line
  line `(v) the issue of copies of permits in place of permits lost, destroyed or multilated;`
  line
  line `(vi) the documents, plates and marks to be carried by transport vehicles, the manner in which they`
  line `are to be carried and the languages in which any such documents are to be expressed;`
  line
  line `(vii) the fees to be paid in respect of applications for permits, duplicate permits and plates;`
  line
  line `(vii) the exemption of prescribed persons or prescribed classes of persons from payment of all or`
  line `any or any portion of the fees payable under this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(ix) the custody, production and cancellation on revocation or expiration of permits, and the`
  line `return of permits which have been cancelled;`
  line
  line `(x) the conditions subject to which, and the extent to which, a permit granted in another State`
  line `shall be valid in the State without countersignature;`
  line
  line `(xi) the conditions subject to which, and the extent to which, a permit granted in one region shall`
  line `be valid in another region within the State without countersignature;`
  line
  line `(xii) the conditions to be attached to permits for the purpose of giving effect to any agreement`
  line `such as is referred to in clause (iii) of sub-section (1) of section 67;`
  line
  line `(xiii) the authorities to whom, the time within which and the manner in which appeals may be`
  line made;
  line
  line `(xiv) the construction and fittings of, and the equipment to be carried by, stage and contract`
  line `carriage, whether generally or in specified areas;`
  line
  line `(xv) the determination of the number of passengers a stage or contract carriage is adapted to carry`
  line `and the number which may be carried;`
  line
  line `(xvi) the conditions subject to which goods may be carried on stage and contract carriages partly`
  line `or wholly in lieu of passengers;`
  line
  line `(xvii) the safe custody and disposal of property left in a stage or contract carriage;`
  line
  line `(xviii) regulating the painting or marking of transport vehicles and the display of advertising`
  line `matter thereon, and in particular prohibiting the painting or marking of transport vehicles in such`
  line `colour or manner as to induce any person to believe that the vehicle is used for the transport of mails;`
  line
  line `(xix) the conveyance in stage or contract carriages of corpses or persons suffering from any`
  line `infectious or contagious disease or goods likely to cause discomfort or injury to passengers and the`
  line `inspection and disinfection of such carriage; if used for such purposes;`
  line
  line `(xx) the provision of taxi meters on motor cabs requiring approval or standard types of taxi meters`
  line `to be used and examining testing and sealing taxi meters;`
  line
  line `(xxi) prohibiting the picking up or setting down of passengers by stage or contract carriages at`
  line `specified places or in specified areas or at places other than duly notified stands or halting places and`
  line `requiring the driver of a stage carriage to stop and remain stationary for a reasonable time when so`
  line `required by a passenger desiring to board or alight from the vehicle at a notified halting place;`
  line
  line `(xxii) the requirements which shall be complied with in the construction or use of any duly`
  line `notified stand or halting place, including the provision of adequate equipment and facilities for the`
  line `convenience of all users thereof; the fees, if any, which may be charged for the use of such facilities,`
  line `the records which shall be maintained at such stands or places, the staff to be employed thereat, and`
  line `the duties and conduct of such staff, and generally for maintaining such stands and places in a`
  line `serviceable and clean condition;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) the regulation of motor cab ranks;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) requiring the owners of transport vehicles to notify any change of address or to report the`
  line `failure of or damage to any vehicle used for the conveyance of passengers for hire or reward;`
  line
  line `(xxv) authorising specified persons to enter at all reasonable times and inspect all premises used`
  line `by permit holders for the purposes of their business;`
  line
  line `(xxvi) requiring the person in charge of a stage carriage to carry any person tendering the legal or`
  line `customary fare;`
  line
  line `(xxvii) the conditions under which and the types of containers or vehicles in which animals or`
  line `birds may be carried and the seasons during which animals or birds may or may not be carried;`
  line
  line `(xxviii) the licensing of and the regulation of the conduct of agents or canvassers who engage in`
  line `the sale of tickets for travel by public service vehicles or otherwise solicit custom for such vehicles;`
  line
  line `(xxix) the licensing of agents engaged in the business of collecting for forwarding and distributing`
  line `goods carried by goods carriages;`
  line
  line `(xxx) the inspection of transport vehicles and their contents and of the permits relating to them;`
  line
  line `(xxxi) the carriage of persons other than the driver in goods carriages;`
  line
  line `(xxxii) the records to be maintained and the returns to be furnished by the owners of transport`
  line `vehicles; and`
  line
  line `^1[(xxxiia) framing of schemes under sub-section (3) of section 67;`
  line
  line `(xxxiib) the promotion of effective competition, passenger convenience and safety, competitive`
  line `fares and prevention of overcrowding;]`
  line
  line `(xxxiii) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (28370)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 105
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28370&sectionno=97&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, "road transport service"`
  line `means a service of motor vehicles carrying passengers or goods or both by road for hire or reward.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (28371)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 106
  title `Chapter to override Chapter V and other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28371&sectionno=98&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Chapter and the rules`
  line `and orders made thereunder shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained`
  line `in Chapter V or in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument having effect by virtue of`
  line `any such law.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (28372)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 107
  title `Preparation and publication of proposal regarding road transport service of a State transport undertaking.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28372&sectionno=99&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)] Where any State Government is of opinion that for the purpose of`
  line `providing an efficient, adequate, economical and properly co-ordinated road transport service, it is`
  line `necessary in the public interest that road transport services in general or any particular class of such`
  line `service in relation to any area or route or portion thereof should be run and operated by the State transport`
  line `undertaking, whether to the exclusion, complete or partial, of other persons or otherwise, the State`
  line `Government may formulate a proposal regarding a scheme giving particulars of the nature of the services`
  line `proposed to be rendered, the area or route proposed to be covered and other relevant particulars respecting`
  line `thereto and shall publish such proposal in the Official Gazette of the State formulating such proposal and`
  line `in not less than one newspaper in the regional language circulating in the area or route proposed to be`
  line `covered by such scheme and also in such other manner as the State Government formulating such`
  line `proposal deem fit.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), when a proposal is published under that`
  line `sub-section, then from the date of publication of such proposal, no permit shall be granted to any person,`
  line `except a temporary permit during the pendency of the proposal and such temporary permit shall be valid`
  line `only for a period of one year from the date of its issue of till the date of final publication of the scheme`
  line `under section 100, whichever is earlier.]`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 99 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act of 54 of 1994, s. 30 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 30, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (28373)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 108
  title `Objection to the proposal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28373&sectionno=100&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the publication of any proposal regarding a scheme in the`
  line `Official Gazette and in not less than one newspaper in the regional language circulating in the area or`
  line `route which is to be covered by such proposal any person may, within thirty days from the date of its`
  line `publication in the Official Gazette, file objections to it before the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, after considering the objections and after giving an opportunity to the`
  line `objector or his representatives and the representatives of the State transport undertaking to be heard in the`
  line `matter, if they so desire, approve or modify such proposal.`
  line
  line `(3) The scheme relating to the proposal as approved or modified under sub-section (2) shall then be`
  line `published in the Official Gazette by the State Government making such scheme and in not less than one`
  line `newspaper in the regional language circulating in the area or route covered by such scheme and the same`
  line `shall thereupon become final on the date of its publication in the Official Gazette and shall be called the`
  line `approved scheme and the area or route to which it relates shall be called the notified area or notified`
  line `route:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such scheme which relates to any inter-State route shall be deemed to be an`
  line `approved scheme unless it has the previous approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, where a scheme is not published as an`
  line `approved scheme under sub-section (3) in the Official Gazette within a period of one year from the date`
  line `of publication of the proposal regarding the scheme in the Official Gazette under sub-section (1), the`
  line `proposal shall be deemed to have lapsed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In computing the period of one year referred to in this sub-section, any period or`
  line `periods during which the publication of the approved scheme under sub-section (3) was held up on`
  line `account of any stay or injunction by the order of any court shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (28374)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 109
  title `Operation of additional services by a State transport undertaking in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28374&sectionno=101&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 87, a State transport undertaking may,`
  line `in the public interest operate additional services for the conveyance of the passengers on special occasions`
  line `such as to and from fairs and religious gatherings:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State transport undertaking shall inform about the operation of such additional`
  line `services to the concerned Transport Authority without delay.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (28375)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 110
  title `Cancellation or modification of scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28375&sectionno=102&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, at any time, if it`
  line `considers necessary, in the public interest so to do, modify any approved scheme after giving--`
  line
  line `(i) the State transport undertaking; and`
  line
  line `(ii) any other person who, in the opinion of the State Government, is likely to be affected by the`
  line `proposed modification,`
  line
  line `an opportunity of being heard in respect of the proposed modification.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall publish any modification proposed under sub-section (1) in the`
  line `Official Gazette and in one of the newspapers in the regional languages circulating in the area in which it`
  line `is proposed to be covered by such modification, together with the date, not being less than thirty days`
  line `from such publication in the Official Gazette, and the time and place at which any representation received`
  line `in this behalf will be heard by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (28376)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 111
  title `Issue of permits to State transport undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28376&sectionno=103&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in pursuance of an approved`
  line `scheme, any State transport undertaking applies in such manner as may be prescribed by the State`
  line `Government in this behalf for a stage carriage permit or a goods carriage permit or a contract carriage`
  line `permit in respect of a notified area or notified route, the State Transport Authority in any case where the`
  line `said area or route lies in more than one region and the Regional Transport Authority in any other case`
  line `shall issue such permit to the State transport undertaking, notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in Chapter V.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of giving effect to the approved scheme in respect of a notified area or notified`
  line `route, the State Transport Authority or, as the case may be, the Regional Transport Authority concerned`
  line `may, by order,--`
  line
  line `(a) refuse to entertain any application for the grant or renewal of any other permit or reject any`
  line `such application as may be pending;`
  line
  line `(b) cancel any existing permit;`
  line
  line `(c) modify the terms of any existing permit so as to--`
  line
  line `(i) render the permit ineffective beyond a specified date;`
  line
  line `(ii) reduce the number of vehicles authorised to be used under the permit;`
  line
  line `(iii) curtail the area or route covered by the permit in so far as such permit relates to the`
  line `notified area or notified route.`
  line
  line `(3) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that no appeal shall lie against any action taken, or`
  line `order passed, by the State Transport Authority or any Regional Transport Authority under sub-section (1)`
  line `or sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 103.--In section 103 of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988 (Central Act 59 of`
  line `1988), after sub-section (1), the following shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1A) It shall be lawful for the State Transport undertaking to operate on any route as stage carriage`
  line `under any permit issued therefor to such undertaking under sub-section (1), any vehicle placed at the`
  line `disposal and under the control of such undertaking by the owner of such vehicle under any arrangement`
  line `entered into between such owner and the undertaking for the use of the said vehicle by the undertaking.]`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 11 of 1996, sec. 2].`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (28377)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 112
  title `Restriction on grant of permits in respect of a notified area or notified route.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28377&sectionno=104&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `Where a`
  line `scheme has been published under sub-section (3) of section 100 in respect of any notified area or notified`
  line `route, the State Transport Authority or the Regional Transport Authority, as the case may be, shall not`
  line `grant any permit except in accordance with the provisions of the scheme:`
  line
  line `Provided that where no application for a permit has been made by the State transport undertaking in`
  line `respect of any notified area or notified route in pursuance of an approved scheme, the State Transport`
  line `Authority or the Regional Transport Authority, as the case may be, may grant temporary permits to any`
  line `person in respect of such notified area or notified route subject to the condition that such permit shall`
  line `cease to be effective on the issue of a permit to the State transport undertaking in respect of that area or`
  line route.
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (28378)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 113
  title `Principles and method of determining compensation and payment thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28378&sectionno=105&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in`
  line `exercise of the powers conferred by clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 103, any existing`
  line `permit is cancelled or the terms thereof are modified, there shall be paid by the State transport`
  line `undertaking to the holder of the permit, compensation, the amount of which shall be determined in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-section (4) or sub-section (5), as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), no compensation shall be payable on`
  line `account of the cancellation of any existing permit or any modification of the terms thereof, when a permit for an alternative route or area in lieu thereof has been offered by the State Transport Authority or the`
  line `Regional Transport Authority, as the case may be and accepted by the holder of the permit.`
  line
  line `(3) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that no compensation shall be payable on account`
  line `of the refusal to renew a permit under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 103.`
  line
  line `(4) Where, in exercise of the powers conferred by clause (b) or sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (ii) of`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 103, any existing permit is cancelled or the terms thereof are`
  line `modified so as to prevent the holder of the permit from using any vehicle authorised to be used thereunder`
  line `for the full period from which the permit, would otherwise have been effective, the compensation payable`
  line `to the holder of the permit for each vehicle affected by such cancellation or modification shall be`
  line `computed as follows:--`
  line
  line `(a) for every complete month or part of a month exceeding`
  line `fifteen days of the unexpired period of the permit`
  line
  line `Two hundred rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) for part of a month not exceeding fifteen days of the`
  line `unexpired period of the permit`
  line
  line `One hundred rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of compensation shall, in no case, be less than four hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(5) Where, in exercise of the powers conferred by sub-clause (iii) of clause (c) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 103, the terms of an existing permit are modified so as to curtail the area or route of any vehicle`
  line `authorised to be used thereunder, the compensation payable to the holder of the permit on account of such`
  line `curtailment shall be an amount computed in accordance with the following formula, namely:--`
  line
  line YA/
  line R
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this formula,--`
  line
  line `(i) "Y" means the length or area by which the route or area covered by the permit is curtailed;`
  line
  line `(ii) "A" means the amount computed in accordance with sub-section (4);`
  line
  line `(iii) "R" means the total length of the route or the total area covered by the permit.`
  line
  line `(6) The amount of compensation payable under this section shall be paid by the State transport`
  line `undertaking to the person or persons entitled thereto within one month from the date on which the`
  line `cancellation or modification of the permit becomes effective:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the State transport undertaking fails to make the payment within the said period`
  line `of one month, it shall pay interest at the rate of seven per cent. per annum from the date on which it falls`
  line due.
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (28379)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 114
  title `Disposal of article found in vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28379&sectionno=106&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `Where any article found in any transport vehicle`
  line `operated by the State transport undertaking is not claimed by its owner within the prescribed period, the`
  line `State transport undertaking may sell the article in the prescribed manner and the sale proceeds thereof,`
  line `after deducting the costs incidental to sale, shall be paid to the owner on demand.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (28380)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 115
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28380&sectionno=107&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may make rules for`
  line `the purpose of carrying into effect the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form in which any proposal regarding a scheme may be published under section 99;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which objections may be filed under sub-section (1) of section 100;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which objections may be considered and disposed of under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 100;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which any approved scheme may be published under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 100;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which application under sub-section (1) of section 103 may be made;`
  line
  line `(f) the period within which the owner may claim any article found left in any transport vehicle`
  line `under section 106 and the manner of sale of such article;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of service of orders under this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (28381)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 116
  title `Certain powers of State Government exercisable by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28381&sectionno=108&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `The powers`
  line `conferred on the State Government under this Chapter shall, in relation to a corporation or company`
  line `owned or controlled by the Central Government or by the Central Government and one or more State`
  line `Governments, be exercisable only by the Central Government in relation to an inter-State route or area.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (28382)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 117
  title `General provision regarding construction and maintenance of vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 31 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28382&sectionno=109&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every motor`
  line `vehicle shall be so constructed and so maintained as to be at all times under the effective control of the`
  line `person driving the vehicle.`
  line
  line `(2) Every motor vehicle shall be so constructed as to have right hand steering control unless it is`
  line `equipped with a mechanical or electrical signalling device of a prescribed nature.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(3) If the Central Government is of the opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to do`
  line `in the public interest, it may by order published in the Official Gazette, notify that any article or`
  line `process used by a manufacturer shall conform to such standard as may be specified in that order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (28383)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 118
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28383&sectionno=110&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may make rules`
  line `regulating the construction, equipment and maintenance of motor vehicles and trailers with respect to all`
  line `or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the width, height, length and overhang of vehicles and of the loads carried;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) the size, nature, maximum retail price and condition of tyres, including embossing thereon`
  line `of date and year of manufacture and the maximum load carrying capacity;]`
  line
  line `(c) brakes and steering gear;`
  line
  line `(d) the use of safety glasses including prohibition of the use of tinted safety glasses;`
  line
  line `(e) signalling appliances, lamps and reflectors;`
  line
  line `(f) speed governors;`
  line
  line `(g) the emission of smoke, visible vapour, sparks, ashes, grit or oil;`
  line
  line `(h) the reduction of noise emitted by or caused by vehicles;`
  line
  line `(i) the embossment of chassis number and engine number and the date of manufacture;`
  line
  line `(j) safety belts, handle bars of motor cycles, auto-dippers and other equipments essential for`
  line `safety of drivers, passengers and other road users;`
  line
  line `(k) standards of the components ^2[including software] used in the vehicle as inbuilt safety`
  line devices;
  line
  line `(l) provision for transportation of goods of dangerous or hazardous nature to human life;`
  line
  line `(m) standardsfor emission of air pollutants;`
  line
  line `^3[(n) installation of catalytic convertors in the class of vehicles to be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(o) the placement of audio-visual or radio or tape recorder type of device in public vehicles;`
  line
  line `(p) warranty after sale of vehicle and norms therefor:]`
  line
  line `Provided that any rules relating to the matters dealing with the protection of environment, so far as`
  line `may be, shall be made after consultation with the Ministry of the Government of India dealing with`
  line environment.
  line
  line `(2) Rules may be made under sub-section (1) governing the matters mentioned therein, including the`
  line `manner of ensuring the compliance with such matters and the maintenance of motor vehicles in respect of`
  line `such matters, either generally in respect of motor vehicles or trailers or in respect of motor vehicles or`
  line `trailers of a particular class or in particular circumstances ^2[and such rules may lay down the procedure`
  line `for investigation, the officers empowered to conduct such investigations, the procedure for hearing of`
  line `such matters and the penalties to be levied thereunder.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) Persons empowered under sub-section (2) to conduct investigations referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) shall have all the powers of a civil court, while trying a suit under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavit; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government may exempt any class of motor vehicles from the provisions of this`
  line Chapter;
  line
  line `(b) a State Government may exempt any motor vehicle or any class or description of motor`
  line `vehicles from the rules made under sub-section (1) subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for clause (@i/i@) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 32. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_110_a:
  sectionId (50174)
  sectionNo 110A
  orderNo 119
  title `Recall of motor vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=50174&sectionno=110A&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_110_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[110A. Recall of motor vehicles. --(1) The Central Government may, by order, direct a`
  line `manufacturer to recall motor vehicles of a particular type or its variants, if--`
  line
  line `(a) a defect in that particular type of motor vehicle may cause harm to the environment or to the`
  line `driver or occupants of such motor vehicle or other road users; and`
  line
  line `(b) a defect in that particular type of motor vehicle has been reported to the Central Government`
  line by--
  line
  line `(i) such percentage of owners, as the Central Government, may by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a testing agency; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the defect referred to in sub-section (1) lies in a motor vehicle component, the Central`
  line `Government may, by order, direct a manufacturer to recall all motor vehicles which contain such`
  line `component, regardless of the type or variants of such motor vehicle.`
  line
  line `(3) A manufacturer whose vehicles are recalled under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), shall--`
  line
  line `(a) reimburse the buyers for the full cost of the motor vehicle, subject to any hire-purchase or`
  line `lease-hypothecation agreement; or`
  line
  line `(b) replace the defective motor vehicle with another motor vehicle of similar or better`
  line `specifications which complies with the standards specified under this Act or repair it; and`
  line
  line `(c) pay such fines and other dues in accordance with sub-section (6).`
  line
  line `(4) Where a manufacturer notices a defect in a motor vehicle manufactured by him, he shall inform`
  line `the Central Government of the defect and initiate recall proceedings and in such case the manufacturer`
  line `shall not be liable to pay fine under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may authorise any officer to conduct investigation under this section`
  line `who shall have all the powers of a civil court, while trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908) in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavit; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may make rules for regulating the recall of motor vehicles, of a`
  line `particular type or its variants, for any defect which in the opinion of the Central Government, may cause`
  line `harm to the environment or to the driver or occupants of such motor vehicle or to other road users.]`
obj_root_law_sections_110_b:
  sectionId (50175)
  sectionNo 110B
  orderNo 120
  title `Type of approval certificate and testing agencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=50175&sectionno=110B&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_110_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[110B. Type approval certificate and testing agencies.-- (1) No motor vehicle, including a trailer or`
  line `semi-trailer or modular hydraulic trailer or side car shall be sold or delivered or offered for sale or`
  line `delivery or used in a public place in India unless a type-approval certificate referred to in sub-section (2)`
  line `has been issued in respect of such vehicle:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, extend the`
  line `requirement of type-approval certificate to other vehicles drawn or intended to be drawn by a motor`
  line `vehicle:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such certificate shall not be required for vehicles which are--`
  line
  line `(a) intended for export or display or demonstration or exhibition; or`
  line
  line `(b) used by a manufacturer of motor vehicles or motor vehicle components or a research and`
  line `development centre or a test by agency for testing and validation or for data collection, inside factory`
  line `premises or in a non-public place; or`
  line
  line `(c) exempted by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The manufacturer or importer of motor vehicles including trailers, semi-trailers, modular`
  line `hydraulic trailers and side cars shall submit the prototype of the vehicle to be manufactured or imported`
  line `for test to a testing agency for obtaining a type-approval certificate by such agency.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall make rules for the accreditation, registration and regulation of`
  line `testing agencies.`
  line
  line `(4) The testing agencies shall conduct tests on vehicles drawn from the production line of the`
  line `manufacturer or obtained otherwise to verify the conformity of such vehicles to the provisions of this`
  line `Chapter and the rules and regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the motor vehicle having a type-approval certificate is recalled under section 110A, the`
  line `testing agency which granted the certificate to such motor vehicle shall be liable for its accreditation and`
  line `registration to be cancelled.]`
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (28384)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 121
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28384&sectionno=111&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Government may make rules`
  line `regulating the construction, equipment and maintenance of motor vehicles and trailers with respect to all`
  line `matters other than the matters specified in sub-section (1) of section 110.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, rules may be made under this section`
  line `governing all or any of the following matters either generally in respect of motor vehicles or trailers or in`
  line `respect of motor vehicles or trailers of a particular class or description or in particular circumstances,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) seating arrangements in public service vehicles and the protection of passengers against the`
  line weather;
  line
  line `(b) prohibiting or restricting the use of audible signals at certain times or in certain places;`
  line
  line `(c) prohibiting the carrying of appliances likely to cause annoyance or danger;`
  line
  line `(d) the periodical testing and inspection of vehicles by prescribed authorities ^1[and fees to be`
  line `charged for such test];`
  line
  line `(e) the particulars other than registration marks to be exhibited by vehicles and the manner in`
  line `which they shall be exhibited;`
  line
  line `(f) the use of trailers with motor vehicles; and`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 33, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (g) omitted by s. 33, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (28385)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 122
  title `Limits of speed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28385&sectionno=112&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall drive a motor vehicle or cause or allow a motor vehicle to`
  line `be driven in any public place at a speed exceeding the maximum speed or below the minimum speed`
  line `fixed for the vehicle under this Act or by or under any other law for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `Provided that such maximum speed shall in no case exceed the maximum fixed for any motor vehicle`
  line `or class or description of motor vehicles by the Central Government by notification in the Official`
  line Gazette.
  line
  line `(2) The State Government or any authority authorised in this behalf by the State Government may, if`
  line `satisfied that it is necessary to restrict the speed of motor vehicles in the interest of public safety or`
  line `convenience or because of the nature of any road or bridge, by notification in the Official Gazette, and by`
  line `causing appropriate traffic signs to be placed or erected under section 116 at suitable places, fix such maximum speed limits or minimum speed limits as it thinks fit for motor vehicles or any specified class`
  line `or description of motor vehicles or for motor vehicles to which a trailer is attached, either generally or in a`
  line `particular area or on a particular road or roads:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such notification is necessary if any restriction under this section is to remain in`
  line `force for not more than one month.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall apply to any vehicle registered under section 60 while it is being used`
  line `in the execution of military manoeuvres within the area and during the period specified in the notification`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Manoeuvres, Field Firing and Artillery Practice Act, 1938`
  line `(5 of 1938).`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (28386)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 123
  title `Limits of weight and limitations on use.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 34, for "heavy goods vehicles or heavy passenger motor vehicles" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28386&sectionno=113&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may prescribe the`
  line `conditions for the issue of permits for ^1`
  line `[transport vehicles] by the State or Regional Transport Authorities`
  line `and may prohibit or restrict the use of such vehicles in any area or route.`
  line
  line `(2) Except as may be otherwise prescribed, no person shall drive or cause or allow to be driven in any`
  line `public place any motor vehicle which is not fitted with pneumatic tyres.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall drive or cause or allow to be driven in any public place any motor vehicle or`
  line trailer--
  line
  line `(a) the unladen weight of which exceeds the unladen weight specified in the certificate of`
  line `registration of the vehicle, or`
  line
  line `(b) the laden weight of which exceeds the gross vehicle weight specified in the certificate of`
  line registration.
  line
  line `(4) Where the driver or person in charge of a motor vehicle or trailer driven in contravention of`
  line `sub-section (2) or clause (a) of sub-section (3) is not the owner, a Court may presume that the offence was`
  line `committed with the knowledge of or under the orders of the owner of the motor vehicle or trailer.`
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (28387)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 124
  title `Power to have vehicle weighed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 35, ibid., for certain words and figures (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28387&sectionno=114&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1`
  line `[Any officer of the Motor Vehicles Department`
  line `authorized in this behalf by the State Government shall, if he has reason to believe that a goods vehicle or`
  line `trailor is being used in contravention of section 113] require the driver to convey the vehicle to a`
  line `weighing device, if any, within a distance of ten kilometres from any point on the forward route or within`
  line `a distance of twenty kilometres from the destination of the vehicle for weighment; and if on such`
  line `weighment the vehicle is found to contravene in any respect the provisions of section 113 regarding`
  line `weight, he may, by order in writing, direct the driver to off-load the excess weight at his own risk and not`
  line `to remove the vehicle or trailer from that place until the laden weight has been reduced or the vehicle or`
  line `trailer has otherwise been dealt with so that it complies with section 113 and on receipt of such notice, the`
  line `driver shall comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the person authorised under sub-section (1) makes the said order in writing, he shall also`
  line `endorse the relevant details of the overloading on the goods carriage permit and also intimate the fact of`
  line `such endorsement to the authority which issued that permit.`
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (28388)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 125
  title `Power to restrict the use of vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28388&sectionno=115&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `The State Government or any authority authorised in`
  line `this behalf by the State Government, if satisfied that it is necessary in the interest of public safety or`
  line `convenience, or because of the nature of any road or bridge, may by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `prohibit or restrict, subject to such exceptions and conditions as may be specified in notification, the`
  line `driving of motor vehicles or of any specified class or description of motor vehicles or the use of trailers`
  line `either generally in a specified area or on a specified road and when any such prohibition or restriction is`
  line `imposed, shall cause appropriate traffic signs to be placed or erected under section 116 at suitable places:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any prohibition or restriction under this section is to remain in force for not more`
  line `than one month, notification thereof in the Official Gazette shall not be necessary, but such local publicity`
  line `as the circumstances may permit, shall be given of such prohibition or restriction.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (28389)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 126
  title `Power to erect traffic signs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28389&sectionno=116&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `(1) (a) The State Government or any authority authorised in this`
  line `behalf by the State Government may cause or permit traffic signs to be placed or erected in any public`
  line `place for the purpose of bringing to public notice any speed limits fixed under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 112 or any prohibitions or restrictions imposed under section 115 or generally for the purpose of`
  line `regulating motor vehicle traffic.`
  line
  line `(b) A State Government or any authority authorised in this behalf by the State Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette or by the erection at suitable places of the appropriate traffic sign`
  line `referred to in Part A of the Schedule, designate certain roads as main roads for the purposes of the driving`
  line `regulations made by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the National Highways Authority of`
  line `India constituted under the National Highways Authority of India Act, 1988 (68 of 1988) or any other`
  line `agency authorised by the Central Government, may cause or permit traffic signs, as provided in the First`
  line `Schedule, to be placed or erected or removed on national highways for the purpose of regulating motor`
  line `vehicle traffic and may order the removal of any sign or advertisement which in its opinion is so placed as`
  line `to obscure any traffic sign from view or is so similar in appearance to a traffic sign as to mislead or is`
  line `likely to distract the attention or concentration of the driver:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of this sub-section, the National Highway Authority of India or any`
  line `other agency authorised by the Central Government may seek assistance from the authorities of the State`
  line `Government and the said State Government shall provide such assistance.]`
  line
  line `(2) Traffic signs placed or erected under sub-section (1) for any purpose for which provision is made`
  line `in the Schedule shall be of the size, colour and type and shall have the meanings set forth in the Schedule,`
  line `but the State Government or any authority empowered in this behalf by the State Government may make`
  line `or authorise the addition to any sign set forth in the said Schedule, of transcriptions of the words, letters or`
  line `figures thereon in such script as the State Government may think fit, provided that the transcriptions shall`
  line `be of similar size and colour to the words, letters or figures set forth in the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(3) Except as provided by sub-section (1)`
  line `^2[or sub-section (1A)], no traffic sign shall, after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, be placed or erected on or near any road; but all traffic signs placed or erected`
  line `prior to the commencement of this Act by any competent authority shall for the purpose of this Act be`
  line `deemed to be traffic signs placed or erected under the provisions of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) A State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, empower any police officer not`
  line `below the rank of a Superintendent of Police to remove or cause to be removed any sign or advertisement`
  line `which is so placed in his opinion as to obscure any traffic sign from view or any sign or advertisement`
  line `which is in his opinion so similar in appearance to a traffic sign as to be misleading or which in his`
  line `opinion is likely to distract the attention or concentration of the driver.`
  line
  line `(5) No person shall wilfully remove, alter, deface, or in any way tamper with, any traffic signs placed`
  line `or erected under this section.`
  line
  line `(6) If any person accidentally causes such damage to a traffic sign as renders it useless for the purpose`
  line `for which it is placed or erected under this section, he shall report the circumstances of the occurrence to a`
  line `police officer or at a police station as soon as possible, and in any case within twenty-four hours of the`
  line occurrence.
  line
  line `(7) For the purpose of bringing the signs set forth in ^2[the First Schedule] in conformity with any`
  line `International Convention relating to motor traffic to which the Central Government is for the time being a`
  line `party, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make any addition or`
  line `alteration to any such sign and on the issue of any such notification, ^2[the First Schedule] shall be deemed`
  line `to be amended accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (28390)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 127
  title `Parking places and halting stations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28390&sectionno=117&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `The State Government or any authority authorised in`
  line `this behalf by the State Government may, in consultation with the local authority having jurisdiction in`
  line `the area concerned, determine places at which motor vehicles may stand either indefinitely or for a`
  line `specified period of time, and may determine the places at which public service vehicles may stop for a`
  line `longer time than is necessary for the taking up and setting down of passengers.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the State Government or the authorised authority shall, give primacy to the safety of`
  line `road users and the free flow of traffic in determining such places:`
  line
  line `Provided further that for the purpose of this section the National Highways Authority of India,`
  line `constituted under the National Highways Authority of India Act, 1988 (68 of 1988) or any other agency`
  line `authorised by the Central Government, may also determine such places.]`
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (28391)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 128
  title `Driving regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28391&sectionno=118&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make regulations for the driving of motor vehicles.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (28392)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 129
  title `Duty to obey traffic signs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28392&sectionno=119&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every driver of a motor vehicle shall drive the vehicle in`
  line `conformity with any indication given by mandatory traffic sign and in conformity with the driving`
  line `regulations made by the Central Government, and shall comply with all directions given to him by any`
  line `police officer for the time being engaged in the regulation of traffic in any public place.`
  line
  line `(2) In this section "mandatory traffic sign" means a traffic sign included in Part A of the Schedule, or`
  line `any traffic sign of similar form (that is to say, consisting of or including a circular disc diplaying a device, word or figure and having a red ground or border) placed or erected for the purpose of regulating motor`
  line `vehicle traffic under sub-section (1) of section 116.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (28393)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 130
  title `Vehicles with left hand control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28393&sectionno=120&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `No person shall drive or cause or allow to be driven in any`
  line `public place any motor vehicle with a left-hand steering control unless it is equipped with a mechanical or`
  line `electrical signalling device of a prescribed nature and in working order.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (28394)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 131
  title `Signals and signalling devices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28394&sectionno=121&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `The driver of a motor vehicle shall make such signals and on`
  line `such occasions as may be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the signal of an intention to turn to the right or left or to stop--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a motor vehicle with a right-hand steering control, may be given by a`
  line `mechanical or electrical device of a prescribed nature affixed to the vehicle; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a motor vehicle with a left hand steering control, shall be given by a mechanical`
  line `or electrical device of a prescribed nature affixed to the vehicle:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the State Government may, having regard to the width and condition of the`
  line `roads in any area or route, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt subject to such conditions as`
  line `may be specified therein any motor vehicle or class or description of motor vehicles from the operation of`
  line `this section for the purpose of plying in that area or route.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (28395)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 132
  title `Leaving vehicle in dangerous position.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28395&sectionno=122&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `No person in charge of a motor vehicle shall cause or`
  line `allow the vehicle or any trailer to be abandoned or to remain at rest on any public place in such a position`
  line `or in such a condition or in such circumstances as to cause or likely to cause danger, obstruction or undue`
  line `inconvenience to other users of the public place or to the passengers.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (28396)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 133
  title `Riding on running board, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28396&sectionno=123&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person driving or in charge of a motor vehicle shall`
  line `carry any person or permit any person to be carried on the running board or otherwise than within the`
  line `body of the vehicle.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall travel on the running board or on the top or on the bonnet of a motor vehicle.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (28397)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 134
  title `Prohibition against travelling without pass or ticket.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28397&sectionno=124&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `No person shall enter or remain in any`
  line `stage carriage for the purposes of travelling therein unless he has with him a proper pass or ticket:`
  line
  line `Provided that where arrangements for the supply of tickets are made in the stage carriage by which a`
  line `person has to travel, a person may enter such stage carriage but as soon as may be after his entry therein,`
  line `be shall make the payment of his fare to the conductor or the driver who performs the functions of a`
  line `conductor and obtain from such conductor or driver, as the case may be, a ticket for his journey.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "pass" means a duty, privilege or courtesy pass entitling the person to whom it is given to`
  line `travel in a stage carriage gratuitously and includes a pass issued on payment for travel in a stage`
  line `carriage for the period specified therein;`
  line
  line `(b) "ticket" includes a single ticket, a return ticket or a season ticket.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (28398)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 135
  title `Obstruction of driver.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28398&sectionno=125&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `No person driving a motor vehicle shall allow any person to stand or`
  line `sit or to place anything in such a manner or position as to hamper the driver in his control of the vehicle.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (28399)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 136
  title `Stationary vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28399&sectionno=126&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `No person driving or in charge of a motor vehicle shall cause or allow the`
  line `vehicle to remain stationary in any public place, unless there is in the driver's seat a person duly licensed`
  line `to drive the vehicle or unless the mechanism has been stopped and a brake or brakes applied or such other`
  line `measures taken as to ensure that the vehicle cannot accidentally be put in motion in the absence of the`
  line driver.
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (28400)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 137
  title `Removal of motor vehicles abandoned or left unattended on a public place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28400&sectionno=127&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Where`
  line `any motor vehicle is abandoned, or left unattended, on a public place for ten hours or more or is parked in`
  line `a place where parking is legally prohibited, its removal by a towing service or its immobilisations by any`
  line `means including wheel clamping may be authorised by a police officer in uniform having jurisdiction.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where an abandoned, unattended, wrecked, burnt or partially dismantled vehicle is creating a`
  line `traffic hazard, because of its position in relation to the ^2[public place], or its physical appearance is`
  line `causing the impediment to the traffic, its immediate removal from the ^1[public place] by a towing service`
  line `may be authorised by a police officer having jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a vehicle is authorised to be removed under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) by a police`
  line `officer, the owner of the vehicle shall be responsible for all towing costs, besides any other penalty.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 37, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 37, ibid., for "highway" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (28401)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 138
  title `Safety measures for drivers and pillion riders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28401&sectionno=128&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `(1) No driver of a two-wheeled motor cycle`
  line `shall carry more than one person in addition to himself on the motor cycle and no such person shall be`
  line `carried otherwise than sitting on a proper seat securely fixed to the motor cycle behind the driver's seat`
  line `with appropriate safety measures.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the safety measures mentioned in sub-section (1), the Central Government may,`
  line `prescribe other safety measures for the drivers of two-wheeled motor cycles and pillion riders thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (28402)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 139
  title `Wearing of protective headgear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 44, for section 129 (w.e.f. 15-02-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28402&sectionno=129&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `^1[129. Wearing of protective headgear.-- Every person, above four years of age, driving or riding`
  line `or being carried on a motorcycle of any class or description shall, while in a public place, wear protective`
  line `headgear conforming to such standards as may be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this section shall not apply to a person who is a Sikh, if, while driving`
  line `or riding on the motorcycle, in a public place, he is wearing a turban:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may by rules provide for measures for the safety of`
  line `children below four years of age riding or being carried on a motorcycle.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- "Protective headgear" means a helmet which,--`
  line
  line `(a) by virtue of its shape, material and construction, could reasonably be expected to afford to the`
  line `person driving or riding on a motorcycle a degree of protection from injury in the event of an`
  line `accident; and`
  line
  line `(b) is securely fastened to the head of the wearer by means of straps or other fastenings provided`
  line `on the headgear.]`
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (28403)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 140
  title `Duty to produce licence and certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28403&sectionno=130&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `(1) The driver of a motor vehicle in`
  line `any public place shall, on demand by any police officer in uniform, produce his licence for examination:`
  line
  line `Provided that the driver may, if his licence has been submitted to, or has been seized by, any officer`
  line `or authority under this or any other Act, produce in lieu of the licence a receipt or other acknowledgment`
  line `issued by such officer or authority in respect thereof and thereafter produce the licence within such`
  line `period, in such manner as the Central Government may prescribe to the police officer making the demand.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The conductor, if any, of a motor vehicle on any public place shall on demand by any officer of`
  line `the Motor Vehicles Department authorised in this behalf, produce the licence for examination.]`
  line
  line `^2[(3) The owner of a motor vehicle (other than a vehicle registered under section 60), or in his`
  line `absence the driver or other person in charge of the vehicle, shall, on demand by a registering authority or`
  line `any other officer of the Motor Vehicles Department duly authorised in this behalf, produce the certificate`
  line `of insurance of the vehicle and, where the vehicle is a transport vehicle, also the certificate of fitness`
  line `referred to in section 56 and the permit; and if any or all of the certificates or the permit are not in his`
  line `possession, he shall, within fifteen days from the date of demand, submit photo copies of the same, duly`
  line `attested in person or send the same by registered post to the officer who demanded it.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, "certificate of insurance" means the certificate`
  line `issued under sub-section (3) of section 147.]`
  line
  line `(4) If the licence referred to in sub-section (2) or the certificates or permit referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3), as the case may be, are not at the time in the possession of the person to whom demand is`
  line `made, it shall be a sufficient compliance with this section if such person produces the licence or`
  line `certificates or permit within such period in such manner as the Central Government may prescribe, to the`
  line `police officer or authority making the demand:`
  line
  line `Provided that, except to such extent and with such modifications as may be prescribed, the provisions`
  line `of this sub-section shall not apply to any person required to produce the certificate of registration or the`
  line `certificate of fitness of a transport vehicle.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (28404)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 141
  title `Duty of the driver to take certain precautions at unguarded railway level crossing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28404&sectionno=131&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line Every
  line `driver of a motor vehicle at the approach of any unguarded railway level crossing shall cause the vehicle`
  line `to stop and the driver of the vehicle shall cause the conductor or cleaner or attendant or any other person`
  line `in the vehicle to walk up to the level crossing and ensure that no train or trolley is approaching from either`
  line `side and then pilot the motor vehicle across such level crossing, and where no conductor or cleaner or`
  line `attendant or any other person is available in the vehicle, the driver of the vehicle shall get down from the`
  line `vehicle himself to ensure that no train or trolley is approaching from either side before the railway track is`
  line crossed.
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (28405)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 142
  title `Duty of driver to stop in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28405&sectionno=132&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `(1) The driver of a motor vehicle shall cause the`
  line `vehicle to stop and remain stationary so long as ^1[may for such reasonable time as may be necessary, but`
  line `not exceeding twenty-four hours]--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) when required to do so by any police officer not below the rank of a Sub-Inspector`
  line `in uniform, in the event of the vehicle being involved in the occurrence of an accident to a person,`
  line `animal or vehicle or of damage to property, or]`
  line
  line `(b) when required to do so by any person in charge of an animal if such person apprehends that`
  line `the animal is, or being alarmed by the vehicle will become, unmanageable, or`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `and he shall give his name and address and the name and address of the owner of the vehicle to any`
  line `person affected by any such accident or damage who demands it provided such person also furnishes his`
  line `name and address.`
  line
  line `(2) The driver of a motor vehicle shall, on demand by a person giving his own name and address and`
  line `alleging that the driver has committed an offence punishable under section 184 give his name and address`
  line `to that person.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section the expression "animal" means any horse, cattle, elephant, camel, ass, mule, sheep`
  line `or goat.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 40, for "may reasonably be necessary" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 40, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (c) omitted by s. 40, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (28406)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 143
  title `Duty of owner of motor vehicle to give information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28406&sectionno=133&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `The owner of a motor vehicle, the`
  line `driver or conductor of which is accused of any offence under this Act shall, on the demand of any police`
  line `officer authorised in this behalf by the State Government, give all information regarding the name and`
  line `address of, and the licence held by, the driver or conductor which is in his possession or could by`
  line `reasonable diligence be ascertained by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (28407)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 144
  title `Duty of driver in case of accident and injury to a person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28407&sectionno=134&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `When any person is injured or any`
  line `property of a third party is damaged, as a result of an accident in which a motor vehicle is involved, the`
  line `driver of the vehicle or other person in charge of the vehicle shall--`
  line
  line `(a) unless it is not practicable to do so on account of mob fury or any other reason beyond his`
  line `control, take all reasonable steps to secure medical attention for the injured person, ^1[by conveying`
  line `him to the nearest medical practitioner or hospital, and it shall be the duty of every registered medical`
  line `practitioner or the doctor on the duty in the hospital immediately to attend to the injured person and`
  line `render medical aid or treatment without waiting for any procedural formalities], unless the injured`
  line `person or his guardian, in case he is a minor, desires otherwise;`
  line
  line `(b) give on demand by a police officer any information required by him, or, if no police officer is`
  line `present, report the circumstances of the occurrence, including the circumstances, if any, for not taking`
  line `reasonable steps to secure medical attention as required under clause (a), at the nearest police station`
  line `as soon as possible, and in any case within twenty-four hours of the occurrence.`
  line
  line `^2[(c) give the following information in writing to the insurer, who has issued the certificates of`
  line `insurance, about the occurrence of the accident, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) insurance policy number and period of its validity;`
  line
  line `(ii) date, time and place of accident;`
  line
  line `(iii) particulars of the persons injured or killed in the accident;`
  line
  line `(iv) name of the driver and the particulars of his driving licence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section the expression driver includes the owner of the`
  line vehicle.]
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 41, ibid., for "and if necessary, convey him to the nearest hospital" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 41 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_134_a:
  sectionId (50176)
  sectionNo 134A
  orderNo 145
  title `Protection of Good Samaritans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-10-2020)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=50176&sectionno=134A&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_134_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[134A. Protection of Good Samaritans. --(1) A Good Samaritan shall not be liable for any civil or`
  line `criminal action for any injury to or death of the victim of an accident involving a motor vehicle, where`
  line `such injury or death resulted from the Good Samaritan’s negligence in acting or failing to act while`
  line `rendering emergency medical or non-medical care or assistance.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may by rules provide for the procedure for questioning or examination`
  line `of the Good Samaritan, disclosure of personal information of the Good Samaritan and such other related`
  line matters.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "Good Samaritan" means a person, who in good faith,`
  line `voluntarily and without expectation of any reward or compensation renders emergency medical or nonmedical care or assistance at the scene of an accident to the victim or transports such victim to the`
  line hospital.]
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (28408)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 146
  title `Schemes to be framed for the investigation of accident cases and wayside amenities, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28408&sectionno=135&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make one or more schemes to`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) an in depth study on causes and analysis of motor vehicle accidents;`
  line
  line `(b) wayside amenities on highways;`
  line
  line `(c) traffic aid posts on highways; ^1***`
  line
  line `(d) truck parking complexes along ^2[highways; and].`
  line
  line `^3[(e) any other amenities in the interests of the safety and the convenience of the public.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every scheme made under this section by any State Government shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before the State Legislature.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make one or more`
  line `schemes to conduct in-depth studies on the causes and analysis of road accidents.]`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word “and” omitted by Act 32 of 2019, s. 46 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 46, ibid., for 'highways" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 46, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (28409)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 147
  title `Inspection of vehicle involved in accident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 42, for "without unnecessary delay" (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28409&sectionno=136&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `When any accident occurs in which a motor`
  line `vehicle is involved, any person authorised in this behalf by the State Government may, on production if`
  line `so required of his authority, inspect the vehicle and for that purpose may enter at any reasonable time any`
  line `premises where the vehicle may be, and may remove the vehicle for examination:`
  line
  line `Provided that the place to which the vehicle is so removed shall be intimated to the owner of the`
  line `vehicle and the vehicle shall be returned ^1[after completion of the formalities to the owner, driver or the`
  line `person in charge of the vehicle within twenty-four hours].`
obj_root_law_sections_136_a:
  sectionId (50177)
  sectionNo 136A
  orderNo 148
  title `Electronic monitoring and enforcement of road safety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 47 (w.e.f. 15-7-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=50177&sectionno=136A&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_136_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[136A. Electronic monitoring and enforcement of road safety. --(1) The State Government shall`
  line `ensure electronic monitoring and enforcement of road safety in the manner provided under sub-section (2)`
  line `on national highways, state highways, roads or in any urban city within a State which has a population up`
  line `to such limits as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall make rules for the electronic monitoring and enforcement of road`
  line `safety including speed cameras, closed-circuit television cameras, speed guns, body wearable cameras`
  line `and such other technology.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section the expression "body wearable camera" means a`
  line `mobile audio and video capture device worn on the body or uniform of a person authorised by the State`
  line Government.]
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (28410)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 149
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 48 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28410&sectionno=137&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may make rules to`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the occasions on which signals shall be made by drivers of motor vehicles and such signals`
  line `under section 121;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) providing for the standards of protective headgear and measures for the safety of children`
  line `below the age of four years riding under section 129;]`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which the licences and certificates may be produced to the police officer under`
  line `section 130.`
  line
  line `^1[(c) providing for limits of urban city by the State Governments under sub-section (1) of section`
  line `136A; and`
  line
  line `(d) providing for electronic monitoring and enforcement under sub-section (2) of section 136A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (28411)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 150
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 49, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28411&sectionno=138&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may make rules for`
  line `the purpose of carrying into effect the provisions of this Chapter other than the matters specified in`
  line `section 137.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) The State Government may, in the interest of road safety, make rules for the purposes of`
  line `regulating the activities and access of non-mechanically propelled vehicles and pedestrians to public`
  line `places and national highways:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of national highways, such rules shall be framed in consultation with the`
  line `National Highways Authority of India.]`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the removal and the safe custody of vehicles including their loads which have broken down or`
  line `which have been left standing or have been abandoned on roads;`
  line
  line `(b) the installation and use of weighing devices;`
  line
  line `(c) the maintenance and management of wayside amenities complexes;`
  line
  line `(d) the exemption from all or any of the provisions of this Chapter of fire brigade vehicles,`
  line `ambulances and other special classes or descriptions of vehicle, subject to such conditions as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(e) the maintenance and management of parking places and stands and the fees, if any, which may`
  line `be charged for their use;`
  line
  line `(f) prohibiting the driving downhill of a motor vehicle with the gear disengaged either generally`
  line `or in a specified place;`
  line
  line `(g) prohibiting the taking hold of or mounting of a motor vehicle in motion;`
  line
  line `(h) prohibiting the use of foot-paths or pavements by motor vehicles;`
  line
  line `(i) generally, the prevention of danger, injury or annoyance to the public or any person, or of`
  line `danger or injury to property or of abstruction to traffic; and`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (28412)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 151
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28412&sectionno=139&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for all or any of the following purposes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the grant and authentication of travelling passes, certificates or authorisations to persons`
  line `temporarily taking motor vehicles out of India to any place outside India or to persons temporarily`
  line `proceeding out of India to any place outside India and desiring to drive a motor vehicle during their`
  line `absence from India;`
  line
  line `(b) prescribing the conditions subject to which motor vehicles brought temporarily into India`
  line `from outside India by persons intending to make a temporary stay in India may be possessed and used`
  line `in India; and`
  line
  line `(c) prescribing the conditions subject to which persons entering India from any place outside`
  line `India for a temporary stay in India may drive motor vehicles in India.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of facilitating and regulating the services of motor vehicles operating between`
  line `India and any other country under any reciprocal arrangement and carrying passengers or goods or both`
  line `by road for hire or reward, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make`
  line `rules with respect to all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the conditions subject to which motor vehicles carrying on such services may be brought into`
  line `India from outside India and possessed and used in India;`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions subject to which motor vehicles may be taken from any place in India to any`
  line `place outside India;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions subject to which persons employed as drivers and conductors of such motor`
  line `vehicles may enter or leave India;`
  line
  line `(d) the grant and authentication of travelling passes, certificates or authorisations to person`
  line `employed as drivers and conductors of such motor vehicles;`
  line
  line `(e) the particulars (other than registration marks) to be exhibited by such motor vehicles and the`
  line `manner in which such particulars are to be exhibited;`
  line
  line `(f) the use of trailers with such motor vehicles;`
  line
  line `(g) the exemption of such motor vehicles and their drivers and conductors from all or any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act other than those referred to in sub-section (4) or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(h) the identification of the drivers and conductors of such motor vehicles;`
  line
  line `(i) the replacement of the travelling passes, certificates or authorisations, permits, licences or any`
  line `other prescribed documents lost or defaced, on payment of such fee as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(j) the exemption from the provisions of such laws as relate to customs, police or health with a`
  line `view to facilitate such road transport services;`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) No rule made under this section shall operate to confer on any person any immunity in any State`
  line `from the payment of any tax levied in that State on motor vehicles or their users.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this Act or in any rule made thereunder by a State Government relating to:--`
  line
  line `(a) the registration and identification of motor vehicles, or`
  line
  line `(b) the requirements as to construction, maintenance and equipment of motor vehicles, or`
  line
  line `(c) the licensing and the qualifications of drivers and conductors of motor vehicles,`
  line
  line `shall apply--`
  line
  line `(i) to any motor vehicle to which or to any driver of a motor vehicle to whom any rules made`
  line `under clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (1) or under sub-section (2) apply; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to any conductor of a motor vehicle to whom any rules made under sub-section (2) apply.`
