obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (28418)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 157
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28418&sectionno=145&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `^1[Definitions.--In this Chapter,--`
  line
  line `(a) "authorised insurer" means an insurer for the time being carrying on general insurance`
  line `business in India and granted a certificate of registration by the Insurance Regulatory and`
  line `Development Authority of India established under section 3 of the Insurance Regulatory and`
  line `Development Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999) and any Government insurance fund authorised to do`
  line `general insurance business under the General Insurance Business (Nationalisation) Act, 1972 (57 of`
  line `1972);`
  line
  line `(b) "certificate of insurance" means a certificate issued by an authorised insurer in pursuance of`
  line `section 147 and includes a cover note complying with such requirements as may be prescribed, and`
  line `where more than one certificate has been issued in connection with a policy, or where a copy of a`
  line `certificate has been issued, all those certificates or that copy, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(c) "grievous hurt" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 320 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(d) "hit and run motor accident" means an accident arising out of the use of a motor vehicle or`
  line `motor vehicles the identity whereof cannot be ascertained in spite of reasonable efforts for the`
  line purpose;
  line
  line `(e) "Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority" means the Insurance Regulatory and`
  line `Development Authority established under section 3 of the Insurance Regulatory and Development`
  line `Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999);`
  line
  line `(f) "policy of insurance" includes certificate of insurance;`
  line
  line `(g) "property" includes roads, bridges, culverts, causeways, trees, posts, milestones and baggage`
  line `of passengers and goods carried in any motor vehicle;`
  line
  line `(h) "reciprocating country" means any such country as may on the basis of reciprocity be notified`
  line `by the Central Government in the Official Gazette to be a reciprocating country for the purposes of`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "third party" includes the Government, the driver and any other co-worker on a transport`
  line vehicle.]
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (28419)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 158
  title `Necessity for insurance against third party risk.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for CHAPTER XI’ (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28419&sectionno=146&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `^1[146. Necessity for insurance against third party risks. --(1) No person shall use, except as a`
  line `passenger, or cause or allow any other person to use, a motor vehicle in a public place, unless there is in`
  line `force, in relation to the use of the vehicle by that person or that other person, as the case may be, a policy`
  line `of insurance complying with the requirements of this Chapter:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a vehicle carrying, or meant to carry, dangerous or hazardous goods, there`
  line `shall also be a policy of insurance under the Public Liability Insurance Act, 1991 (6 of 1991).`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, a person driving a motor vehicle merely as a paid`
  line `employee, while there is in relation to the use of the vehicle no such policy in force as is required by this`
  line `sub-section, shall not be deemed to act in contravention of the sub-section unless he knows or has reason`
  line `to believe that there is no such policy in force.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply to any vehicle owned by the Central Government`
  line `or a State Government and used for purposes not connected with any commercial enterprise.`
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government may, by order, exempt from the operation of sub-section (1), any`
  line `vehicle owned by any of the following authorities, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government or a State Government, if the vehicle is used for purposes connected`
  line `with any commercial enterprise;`
  line
  line `(b) any local authority;`
  line
  line `(c) any State Transport Undertaking:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made in relation to any such authority unless a fund has been`
  line `established and is maintained by that authority in such manner as may be prescribed by appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "appropriate Government" means the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government, as the case may be, and--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to any corporation or company owned by the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government, means the Central Government or that State Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any corporation or company owned by the Central Government and one or`
  line `more State Governments, means the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to any other State Transport Undertaking or any local authority, means that`
  line `Government which has control over that undertaking or authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (28420)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 159
  title `Requirements of policies and limits of liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for CHAPTER XI’ (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28420&sectionno=147&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `^1[Requirement of policies and limits of liability. -- (1) In order to comply with the requirements`
  line `of this Chapter, a policy of insurance must be a policy which--`
  line
  line `(a) is issued by a person who is an authorised insurer; and`
  line
  line `(b) insures the person or classes of persons specified in the policy to the extent specified in`
  line `sub-section (2)--`
  line
  line `(i) against any liability which may be incurred by him in respect of the death of or bodily injury`
  line `to any person including owner of the goods or his authorised representative carried in the motor`
  line `vehicle or damage to any property of a third party caused by or arising out of the use of the motor`
  line `vehicle in a public place;`
  line
  line `(ii) against the death of or bodily injury to any passenger of a transport vehicle, except`
  line `gratuitous passengers of a goods vehicle, caused by or arising out of the use of the motor vehicle in`
  line `a public place.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the death of or bodily injury`
  line `to any person or damage to any property of a third party shall be deemed to have been caused by or to`
  line `have arisen out of, the use of a vehicle in a public place, notwithstanding that the person who is dead`
  line `or injured or the property which is damaged was not in a public place at the time of the accident, if`
  line `the act or omission which led to the accident occurred in a public place.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained under any other law for the time being in force, for the`
  line `purposes of third party insurance related to either death of a person or grievous hurt to a person, the`
  line `Central Government shall prescribe a base premium and the liability of an insurer in relation to such`
  line `premium for an insurance policy under sub-section (1) in consultation with the Insurance Regulatory`
  line `and Development Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) A policy shall be of no effect for the purposes of this Chapter unless and until there is issued`
  line `by the insurer in favour of the person by whom the policy is effected, a certificate of insurance in the`
  line `prescribed form and containing the prescribed particulars of any condition subject to which the policy`
  line `is issued and of any other prescribed matters; and different forms, particulars and matters may be`
  line `prescribed in different cases.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, a policy of Insurance issued before the`
  line `commencement of the Motor Vehicles (Amendment) Act, 2019 shall be continued on the existing`
  line `terms under the contract and the provisions of this Act shall apply as if this Act had not been`
  line `amended by the said Act.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a cover note issued by the insurer under the provisions of this Chapter or the rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder is not followed by a policy of insurance within the specified time, the`
  line `insurer shall, within seven days of the expiry of the period of the validity of the cover note, notify the`
  line `fact to the registering authority or to such other authority as the State Government may prescribe.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, an insurer`
  line `issuing a policy of insurance under this section shall be liable to indemnify the person or classes of`
  line `persons specified in the policy in respect of any liability which the policy purports to cover in the case`
  line `of that person or those classes of persons.]`
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (28421)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 160
  title `Validity of policies of insurance issued in reciprocating countries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for CHAPTER XI’ (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28421&sectionno=148&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `^1[ Validity of policies of insurance issued in reciprocating countries. -- Where, in pursuance of`
  line `an arrangement between India and any reciprocating country, the motor vehicle registered in the`
  line `reciprocating country operates on any route or within any area common to the two countries and there is`
  line `in force in relation to the use of the vehicle in the reciprocating country, a policy of insurance complying`
  line `with the requirements of the law of insurance for the time being in force in that country, then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in section 147 but subject to any rules which may be made under`
  line `section 164B such policy of insurance shall be effective throughout the route or area in respect of which`
  line `the arrangement has been made, as if the policy of insurance had complied with the requirements of this`
  line `Chapter. ]`
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (28422)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 161
  title `Settlement by insurance company and procedure therefor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28422&sectionno=149&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `^1[Settlement by insurance company and procedure therefor. -- (1) The insurance company`
  line `shall, upon receiving information of the accident, either from claimant or through accident information`
  line `report or otherwise, designate an officer to settle the claims relating to such accident.`
  line
  line `(2) An officer designated by the insurance company for processing the settlement of claim of`
  line `compensation may make an offer to the claimant for settlement before the Claims Tribunal giving such`
  line `details, within thirty days and after following such procedure as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) If, the claimant to whom the offer is made under sub-section (2),--`
  line
  line `(a) accepts such offer,--`
  line
  line `(i) the Claims Tribunal shall make a record of such settlement, and such claim shall be`
  line `deemed to be settled by consent; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the payment shall be made by the insurance company within a maximum period of thirty`
  line `days from the date of receipt of such record of settlement;`
  line
  line `(b) rejects such offer, a date of hearing shall be fixed by the Claims Tribunal to adjudicate such`
  line `claim on merits.]`
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (28423)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 162
  title `Duty of insurers to satisfy judgments and awards against persons insured in respect of third party risks`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28423&sectionno=150&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `^1[Duty of insurers to satisfy judgments and awards against persons insured in respect of`
  line `third party risks. -- (1) If, after a certificate of insurance has been issued under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 147 in favour of the person by whom a policy has been effected, judgment or award in respect of`
  line `any such liability as is required to be covered by a policy under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section`
  line `147 (being a liability covered by the terms of the policy) or under the provisions of section 164 is`
  line `obtained against any person insured by the policy, then, notwithstanding that the insurer may be entitled`
  line `to avoid or cancel or may have avoided or cancelled the policy, the insurer shall, subject to the provisions`
  line `of this section, pay to the person entitled to the benefit of the award any sum not exceeding the sum`
  line `assured payable thereunder, as if that person were the decree holder, in respect of the liability, together`
  line `with any amount payable in respect of costs and any sum payable in respect of interest on that sum by`
  line `virtue of any enactment relating to interest on judgments.`
  line
  line `(2) No sum shall be payable by an insurer under sub-section (1) in respect of any judgment or award`
  line `unless, before the commencement of the proceedings in which the judgment or award is given the insurer`
  line `had notice through the court or, as the case may be, the Claims Tribunal of the bringing of the`
  line `proceedings, or in respect of such judgment or award so long as its execution is stayed pending an appeal;`
  line `and an insurer to whom notice of the bringing of any such proceedings is so given shall be entitled to be`
  line `made a party thereto, and to defend the action on any of the following grounds, namely:-`
  line
  line `(a) that there has been a breach of a specified condition of the policy, being one of the following`
  line `conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) a condition excluding the use of the vehicle--`
  line
  line `(A) for hire or reward, where the vehicle is on the date of the contract of insurance a vehicle`
  line `not covered by a permit to ply for hire or reward; or`
  line
  line `(B) for organised racing and speed testing; or`
  line
  line `(C) for a purpose not allowed by the permit under which the vehicle is used, where the`
  line `vehicle is a transport vehicle; or`
  line
  line `(D) without side-car being attached where the vehicle is a two-wheeled vehicle; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a condition excluding driving by a named person or by any person who is not duly licenced or`
  line `by any person who has been disqualified for holding or obtaining a driving licence during the period`
  line `of disqualification or driving under the influence of alcohol or drugs as laid down in section 185; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a condition excluding liability for injury caused or contributed to by conditions of war, civil`
  line `war, riot or civil commotion; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the policy is void on the ground that it was obtained by nondisclosure of any material fact or`
  line `by representation of any fact which was false in some material particular; or`
  line
  line `(c) that there is non-receipt of premium as required under section 64VB of the Insurance Act, 1938`
  line `(4 of 1938).`
  line
  line `(3) Where any such judgment or award as is referred to in sub-section (1) is obtained from a court in a`
  line `reciprocating country and in the case of a foreign judgment is, by virtue of the provisions of section 13 of`
  line `the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) conclusive as to any matter adjudicated upon by it, the`
  line `insurer (being an insurer registered under the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938) and whether or not that person is registered under the corresponding law of the reciprocating country) shall be liable to the person`
  line `entitled to the benefit of the decree in the manner and to the extent specified in sub-section (1), as if the`
  line `judgment or award were given by a court in India:`
  line
  line `Provided that no sum shall be payable by the insurer in respect of any such judgment or award unless,`
  line `before the commencement of the proceedings in which the judgment or award is given, the insurer had`
  line `notice through the court concerned of the bringing of the proceedings and the insurer to whom notice is so`
  line `given is entitled under the corresponding law of the reciprocating country, to be made a party to the`
  line `proceedings and to defend the action on grounds similar to those specified in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Where a certificate of insurance has been issued under sub-section (3) of section 147 to the person`
  line `by whom a policy has been effected, so much of the policy as purports to restrict the insurance of the`
  line `persons insured thereby, by reference to any condition other than those in sub-section (2) shall, as`
  line `respects such liabilities as are required to be covered by a policy under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 147, be of no effect.`
  line
  line `(5) No insurer to whom the notice referred to in sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) has been given`
  line `shall be entitled to avoid his liability to any person entitled to the benefit of any such judgment or award`
  line `as is referred to in sub-section (1) or in such judgment as is referred to in sub-section (3) otherwise than in`
  line `the manner provided for in sub-section (2) or in the corresponding law of the reciprocating country, as the`
  line `case may be.`
  line
  line `(6) If on the date of filing of any claim, the claimant is not aware of the insurance company with`
  line `which the vehicle had been insured, it shall be the duty of the owner of the vehicle to furnish to the`
  line `tribunal or court the information as to whether the vehicle had been insured on the date of the accident,`
  line `and if so, the name of the insurance company with which it is insured.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "award" means an award made by the Claims Tribunal under section 168;`
  line
  line `(b) "Claims Tribunal" means a Claims Tribunal constituted under section 165;`
  line
  line `(c) "liability covered by the terms of the policy" means the liability which is covered by the`
  line `policy or which would be so covered but for the fact that the insurer is entitled to avoid or cancel or`
  line `has avoided or cancelled the policy; and`
  line
  line `(d) "material fact" and "material particular" mean, respectively, a fact or particular of such a`
  line `nature as to influence the judgment of a prudent insurer in determining whether he shall take the risk`
  line `and, if so, at what premium and on what conditions.]`
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (28424)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 163
  title `Rights of third party against insurers on insolvency of insured`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28424&sectionno=151&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `^1[Rights of third party against insurers on insolvency of insured. ] --(1) Where under any`
  line `contract of insurance affected in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter, a person is insured`
  line `against liabilities which he may incur to third party, then--`
  line
  line `(a) in the event of the person becoming insolvent or making a composition or arrangement with`
  line `his creditors; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the insured person is a company, in the event of a winding-up order being made or a`
  line `resolution for a voluntary winding-up being passed with respect to the company or of a receiver or`
  line `manager of the companys business or undertaking being duly appointed, or of possession being taken`
  line `by or on behalf of the holders of any debentures secured by a floating charge of any property`
  line `comprised in or subject to the charge, if, either before or after that event, any such liability is incurred`
  line `by the insured person his rights against the insurer under the contract in respect of the liability shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything to the contrary in any provision of law, be transferred to and vest in the third`
  line `party to whom the liability was so incurred.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an order for the administration of the estate of a deceased debtor is made according to the`
  line `law of insolvency, then, if any debt provable in insolvency is owing by the deceased in respect of a`
  line `liability to a third party against which he was insured under a contract of insurance in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter, the deceased debtors rights against the insurer in respect of that liability shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything to the contrary in any provision of law, be transferred to and vest in the person`
  line `to whom the debt is owing.`
  line
  line `(3) Any condition in a policy issued for the purposes of this Chapter purporting, either directly or`
  line `indirectly, to avoid the policy or to alter the rights of the parties thereunder upon the happening to the`
  line `insured person of any of the events specified in clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1) or upon the making of an order for the administration of the estate of a deceased debtor according to the law of`
  line `insolvency, shall be of no effect.`
  line
  line `(4) Upon a transfer under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the insurer shall be under the same`
  line `liability to the third party as he would have been to the insured person, but--`
  line
  line `(a) if the liability of the insurer to the insured person exceeds the liability of the insured person to`
  line `the third party, nothing in this Chapter shall affect the rights of the insured person against the insurer`
  line `in respect of the excess amount; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the liability of the insurer to the insured person is less than the liability of the insured person`
  line `to the third party, nothing in this Chapter shall affect the rights of the third party against the insured`
  line `person in respect of the balance amount.]`
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (28425)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 164
  title `Duty to give information as to insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28425&sectionno=152&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `^1[Duty to give information as to insurance. --(1) No person against whom a claim is made in`
  line `respect of any liability referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 147 shall, on demand by or on`
  line `behalf of the person making the claim, refuse to state whether or not he was insured in respect of that`
  line `liability by any policy issued under the provisions of this Chapter, or would have been so insured if the`
  line `insurer had not avoided or cancelled the policy, nor shall he refuse, if he was or would have been so`
  line `insured, to give such particulars with respect to that policy as were specified in the certificate of insurance`
  line `issued in respect thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of any person becoming insolvent or making an arrangement with his creditors or in`
  line `the event of an order being made for the administration of the estate of a deceased person according to the`
  line `law of insolvency, or in the event of a winding-up order being made or a resolution for a voluntary`
  line `winding-up being passed with respect to any company or of a receiver or manager of the companys`
  line `business or undertaking being duly appointed or of possession being taken by or on behalf of the holders`
  line `of any debentures secured by a floating charge on any property comprised in or subject to the charge, it`
  line `shall be the duty of the insolvent debtor, personal representative of the deceased debtor or company, as`
  line `the case may be, or the official assignee or receiver in insolvency, trustee, liquidator, receiver or manager,`
  line `or person in possession of the property to give, on the request of any person claiming that the insolvent`
  line `debtor, deceased debtor or company is under such liability to him as is covered by the provision of this`
  line `Chapter, such information as may reasonably be required by him for the purpose of ascertaining whether`
  line `any rights have been transferred to and vested in him by section 151 and for the purpose of enforcing such`
  line `rights, if any, and any such contract of insurance as purports whether directly or indirectly to avoid the`
  line `contract or to alter the rights of the parties thereunder upon the giving of such information in the events`
  line `aforesaid, or otherwise to prohibit or prevent the giving thereof in the said events, shall be of no effect.`
  line
  line `(3) If, from the information given to any person in pursuance of sub-section (2) or otherwise, he has`
  line `reasonable ground for supporting that there have or may have been transferred to him under this Chapter`
  line `rights against any particular insurer, that insurer shall be subject to the same duty as is imposed by the`
  line `said sub-section on the persons therein mentioned.`
  line
  line `(4) The duty to give the information imposed by this section shall include a duty to allow all contracts`
  line `of insurance, receipts for premiums, and other relevant documents in the possession or power of the`
  line `person on whom the duty is so imposed to be inspected and copies thereof to be taken.]`
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (28426)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 165
  title `Settlement between insurers and insured persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28426&sectionno=153&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `^1[Settlement between insurers and insured persons. --- (1) No settlement made by an insurer in`
  line `respect of any claim which might be made by a third party in respect of any liability of the nature referred`
  line `to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 147 shall be valid unless such third party is a party to the`
  line settlement.
  line
  line `(2) The Claims Tribunal shall ensure that the settlement is bona fide and was not made under undue`
  line `influence and the compensation is made in accordance with the payment schedule referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 164.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person who is insured under a policy issued for the purpose of this Chapter has become`
  line `insolvent, or where, if such insured person is a company, a winding-up order has been made or a`
  line `resolution for a voluntary winding-up has been passed with respect to the company, no agreement made`
  line `between the insurer and the insured person after the liability has been incurred to a third party and after`
  line `the commencement of the insolvency or winding-up, as the case may be, nor any waiver, assignment or other disposition made by or payment made to the insured person after the commencement aforesaid,`
  line `shall be effective to defeat the rights transferred to the third party under this Chapter; but those rights`
  line `shall be the same as if no such agreement, waiver, assignment or disposition or payment has been made.]`
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (28427)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 166
  title `Saving in respect of sections 151, 152 and 153.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28427&sectionno=154&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `^1[Saving in respect of sections 151, 152 and 153. -- (1) For the purposes of sections 151, 152`
  line `and 153, a reference to "liabilities to third parties" in relation to a person insured under any policy of`
  line `insurance shall not include a reference to any liability of that person in the capacity of insurer under some`
  line `other policy of insurance.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sections 151, 152 and 153 shall not apply where a company is wound-up`
  line `voluntarily merely for the purposes of reconstruction or of an amalgamation with another company.`
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (28428)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 167
  title `Effect of death on certain causes of action.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28428&sectionno=155&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `^1[Effect of death on certain causes of action. --Notwithstanding anything contained in section`
  line `306 of the Indian Succession Act, 1925, (39 of 1925) the death of a person in whose favour a certificate`
  line `of insurance had been issued, if it occurs after the happening of an event which has given rise to a claim`
  line `under the provisions of this Chapter, shall not be a bar to the survival of any cause of action arising out of`
  line `such event against his estate or against the insurer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (28429)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 168
  title `Effect of certificate of insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28429&sectionno=156&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `^1[Effect of certificate of insurance. -- When an insurer has issued a certificate of insurance in`
  line `respect of a contract of insurance between the insurer and the insured person, then--`
  line
  line `(a) if and so long as the policy described in the certificate has not been issued by the insurer to`
  line `the insured, the insurer shall, as between himself and any other person except the insured, be deemed`
  line `to have issued to the insured person a policy of insurance conforming in all respects with the`
  line `description and particulars stated in such certificate; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the insurer has issued to the insured the policy described in the certificate, but the actual`
  line `terms of the policy are less favourable to persons claiming under or by virtue of the policy against the`
  line `insurer either directly or through the insured than the particulars of the policy as stated in the`
  line `certificate, the policy shall, as between the insurer and any other person except the insured, be`
  line `deemed to be in terms conforming in all respects with the particulars stated in the said certificate.]`
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (28430)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 169
  title `Transfer of certificate of insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28430&sectionno=157&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `^1[Transfer of certificate of insurance. -- (1) Where a person, in whose favour the certificate of`
  line `insurance has been issued in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter, transfers to another person`
  line `the ownership of the motor vehicle in respect of which such insurance was taken together with the policy`
  line `of insurance relating thereto, the certificate of insurance and the policy described in the certificate shall be`
  line `deemed to have been transferred in favour of the person to whom the motor vehicle is transferred with`
  line `effect from the date of its transfer.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that such deemed transfer shall include`
  line `transfer of rights and liabilities of the said certificate of insurance and policy of insurance.`
  line
  line `(2) The transferee shall apply within fourteen days from the date of transfer in the prescribed form to`
  line `the insurer for making necessary changes in regard to the fact of transfer in the certificate of insurance`
  line `and the policy described in the certificate in his favour, and the insurer shall make the necessary changes`
  line `in the certificate and the policy of insurance in regard to the transfer of insurance.]`
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (28431)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 170
  title `Production of certain certificates, licence and permit in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28431&sectionno=158&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `^[Production of certain certificates, licence and permit in certain cases. --(1) Any person`
  line `driving a motor vehicle in any public place shall, on being so required by a police officer in uniform`
  line `authorised in this behalf by the State Government, produce.`
  line
  line `(a) the certificate of insurance;`
  line
  line `(b) the certificate of registration;`
  line
  line `(c) the pollution under control certificate;`
  line
  line `(d) the driving licence;`
  line
  line `(e) in the case of a transport vehicle, also the certificate of fitness referred to in section 56, and`
  line `the permit; and`
  line
  line `(f) any certificate or authorisation of exemption that has been granted under this Act, relating to`
  line `the use of the vehicle.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, owing to the presence of a motor vehicle in a public place, an accident occurs involving`
  line `death or bodily injury to another person, if the driver of the vehicle does not at that time produce the`
  line `required certificate, driving licence and permit referred to in sub-section (1) to a police officer, he or the`
  line `owner shall produce the said certificates, licence and permit at the police station at which the driver`
  line `makes the report required by section 134.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall be liable to conviction for offences under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) by`
  line `reason of the failure to produce the required certificate if, within seven days from the date on which its`
  line `production was required under sub-section (1), or as the case may be, from the date of occurrence of the`
  line `accident, he produces the certificate at such police station as may have been specified by him to the police`
  line `officer who required its production or, as the case may be, to the police officer at the site of the accident`
  line `or to the officer-in-charge of the police station at which he reported the accident:`
  line
  line `Provided that except to such extent and with such modifications as may be prescribed, the provisions`
  line `of this sub-section shall not apply to the driver of a transport vehicle.`
  line
  line `(4) The owner of a motor vehicle shall give such information as he may be required by or on behalf of`
  line `a police officer empowered in this behalf by the State Government for the purpose of determining`
  line `whether the vehicle was or was not being driven in contravention of section 146 and on any occasion`
  line `when the driver was required under this section to produce the certificate of insurance.`
  line
  line `(5) In this section, the expression "produce the certificate of insurance" means production for`
  line `examination the relevant certificate of insurance or such other evidence as may be prescribed to prove`
  line `that the vehicle was not being driven in contravention of section 146.]`
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (28432)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 171
  title `Information to be given regarding accident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28432&sectionno=159&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `^1[Information to be given regarding accident.-- The police officer shall, during the`
  line `investigation, prepare an accident information report to facilitate the settlement of claim in such form and`
  line `manner, within three months and containing such particulars and submit the same to the Claims Tribunal`
  line `and such other agency as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (28433)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 172
  title `Duty to furnish particulars of vehicle involved in accident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28433&sectionno=160&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `^1[Duty to furnish particulars of vehicle involved in accident. --A registering authority or the`
  line `officer-in-charge of a police station shall, if so required by a person who alleges that he is entitled to`
  line `claim compensation in respect of an accident arising out of the use of a motor vehicle, or if so required by`
  line `an insurer against whom a claim has been made in respect of any motor vehicle, furnish to that person or`
  line `to that insurer, as the case may be, on payment of the prescribed fee, any information at the disposal of`
  line `the said authority or the said police officer relating to the identification marks and other particulars of the`
  line `vehicle and the name and address of the person who was using the vehicle at the time of the accident or`
  line `was injured by it and the property, if any, damaged in such form and within such time as the Central`
  line `Government may prescribe.]`
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (28434)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 173
  title `Special provisions as to compensation in case of hit and run motor accident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28434&sectionno=161&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `^1[Special provisions as to compensation in case of hit and run motor accident. -- (1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or any instrument having`
  line `the force of law, the Central Government shall provide for paying in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this Act and the scheme made under sub-section (3), compensation in respect of the death of, or grievous`
  line `hurt to, persons resulting from hit and run motor accidents.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the scheme made under sub-section (3), there shall be`
  line `paid as compensation,--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of the death of any person resulting from a hit and run motor accident, a fixed sum`
  line `of two lakh rupees or such higher amount as may be prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of grievous hurt to any person resulting from a hit and run motor accident, a fixed`
  line `sum of fifty thousand rupees or such higher amount as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make a scheme specifying`
  line `the manner in which the scheme shall be administered by the Central Government or General Insurance`
  line `Council, the form, manner and the time within which applications for compensation may be made, the officers or authorities to whom such applications may be made, the procedure to be followed by such`
  line `officers or authorities for considering and passing orders on such applications, and all other matters`
  line `connected with, or incidental to, the administration of the scheme and the payment of compensation under`
  line `this section.`
  line
  line `(4) A scheme made under sub-section (3) may provide that,--`
  line
  line `(a) a payment of such sum as may be prescribed by the Central Government as interim relief to`
  line `any claimant under such scheme;`
  line
  line `(b) a contravention of any provision thereof shall be punishable with imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to two years, or with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but may`
  line `extend to five lakh rupees or with both;`
  line
  line `(c) the powers, functions or duties conferred or imposed on any officer or authority by such`
  line `scheme may be delegated with the prior approval in writing of Central Government, by such officer`
  line `or authority to any other officer or authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (28435)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 174
  title `Scheme for golden hour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28435&sectionno=162&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `^1[Scheme for golden hour. -- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the General Insurance`
  line `Companies (Nationalisation) Act, 1972 (57 of 1972) or any other law for the time being in force or any`
  line `instrument having the force of law, the insurance companies for the time being carrying on general`
  line `insurance business in India shall provide in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the schemes`
  line `made under this Act for treatment of road accident victims, including during the golden hour.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall make a scheme for the cashless treatment of victims of the accident`
  line `during the golden hour and such scheme may contain provisions for creation of a fund for such treatment.`
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (28436)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 175
  title `Refund in certain cases of compensation paid under section 161.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28436&sectionno=163&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `^1[Refund in certain cases of compensation paid under section 161. -- (1) The payment of`
  line `compensation in respect of the death of, or grievous hurt to, any person under section 161 shall be subject`
  line `to the condition that if any compensation (hereafter in this sub-section referred to as the other`
  line `compensation) or other amount in lieu of or by way of satisfaction of a claim for compensation is`
  line `awarded or paid in respect of such death or grievous hurt under any other provision of this Act or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force or otherwise, so much of the other compensation or other amount`
  line `aforesaid as is equal to the compensation paid under section 161, shall be refunded to the insurer.`
  line
  line `(2) Before awarding compensation in respect of an accident involving the death of, or bodily injury`
  line `to, any person arising out of the use of a motor vehicle under any provision of this Act other than`
  line `section 161 or any other law for the time being in force, the Claims Tribunal, court or other authority`
  line `awarding such compensation shall verify as to whether in respect of such death or bodily injury`
  line `compensation has already been paid under section 161 or an application for payment of compensation is`
  line `pending under that section, and such Tribunal, court or other authority shall--`
  line
  line `(a) if compensation has already been paid under section 161, direct the person liable to pay the`
  line `compensation awarded by it to refund to the insurer, so much thereof as is required to be refunded in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) if an application for payment of compensation is pending under section 161 forward the`
  line `particulars as to the compensation awarded by it to the insurer.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-section, an application for compensation under section 161`
  line `shall be deemed to be pending--`
  line
  line `(i) if such application has been rejected, till the date of the rejection of the application; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, till the date of payment of compensation in pursuance of the`
  line application.]
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (28439)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 176
  title `Payment of compensation in case of death or grevious hurt, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for 'CHAPTER XI' (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28439&sectionno=164&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `^1[Payment of compensation in case of death or grevious hurt, etc. -- (1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force or instrument having the`
  line `force of law, the owner of the motor vehicle or the authorised insurer shall be liable to pay in the case of`
  line `death or grievous hurt due to any accident arising out of the use of motor vehicle, a compensation, of a sum of five lakh rupees in case of death or of two and a half lakh rupees in case of grievous hurt to the`
  line `legal heirs or the victim, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) In any claim for compensation under sub-section (1), the claimant shall not be required to plead or`
  line `establish that the death or grievous hurt in respect of which the claim has been made was due to any`
  line `wrongful act or neglect or default of the owner of the vehicle or of the vehicle concerned or of any other`
  line person.
  line
  line `(3) Where, in respect of death or grievous hurt due to an accident arising out of the use of motor`
  line `vehicle, compensation has been paid under any other law for the time being in force, such amount of`
  line `compensation shall be reduced from the amount of compensation payable under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_164_a:
  sectionId (50182)
  sectionNo 164A
  orderNo 177
  title `Scheme for interim relief for claimants`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for ‘CHAPTER XI’ (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=50182&sectionno=164A&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_164_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[164A. Scheme for interim relief for claimants. -- (1) The Central Government, may make schemes`
  line `for the provision of interim relief to claimants praying for compensation under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) A scheme made under sub-section (1) shall also provide for procedure to recover funds`
  line `disbursed under such scheme from the owner of the motor vehicle, where the claim arises out of the`
  line `use of such motor vehicle or other sources as may be prescribed by the Central Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_164_b:
  sectionId (50179)
  sectionNo 164B
  orderNo 178
  title `Motor Vehicle Accident Fund`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for ‘CHAPTER XI’ (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=50179&sectionno=164B&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_164_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[164B. Motor Vehicle Accident Fund. -- (1) The Central Government shall constitute a Fund to be`
  line `called the Motor Vehicle Accident Fund and thereto shall be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) payment of a nature notified and approved by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) any grant or loan made to the Fund by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) the balance of the Fund created under scheme framed under section 163, as it stood immediately`
  line `before the commencement of the Motor Vehicles (Amendment) Act, 2019; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other source of income as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be constituted for the purpose of providing compulsory insurance cover to all road`
  line `users in the territory of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Fund shall be utilised for the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) treatment of the persons injured in road accidents in accordance with the scheme framed by the`
  line `Central Government under section 162;`
  line
  line `(b) compensation to representatives of a person who died in hit and run motor accident in`
  line `accordance with schemes framed under section 161;`
  line
  line `(c) compensation to a person grievously hurt in a hit and run motor accident in accordance with`
  line `schemes framed under section 161; and`
  line
  line `(d) compensation to such persons as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The maximum liability amount that shall be paid in each case shall be such as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) In all cases specified in clause (a) of sub-section (3), when the claim of such person becomes`
  line `payable, where amount has been paid out of this Fund to any person, the same amount shall be deductible`
  line `from the claim received by such person from the insurance company.`
  line
  line `(6) The Fund shall be managed by such authority or agency as the Central Government may specify`
  line `having regard to the following:--`
  line
  line `(a) knowledge of insurance business of the agency;`
  line
  line `(b) capability of the agency to manage funds; and`
  line
  line `(c) any other criteria as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(7) The Central Government shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records and prepare an`
  line `annual statement of accounts of the Fund in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government`
  line `in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(8) The accounts of the Fund shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at such`
  line `intervals as may be specified by him.`
  line
  line `(9) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any person appointed by him in connection with`
  line `the audit of the accounts of the Fund under this Act shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `any of the offices of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(10) The accounts of the Fund, as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon, shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and the Central Government shall cause the same to be laid before`
  line `each House of the Parliament.`
  line
  line `(11) Any scheme framed under sub-section (3) of section 161, as it stood immediately before the`
  line `commencement of the Motor Vehicles (Amendment) Act, 2019, shall be discontinued and all rights and`
  line `liabilities accruing thereunder shall be met out of the Fund with effect from the date of commencement of`
  line `this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_164_c:
  sectionId (50180)
  sectionNo 164C
  orderNo 179
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for ‘CHAPTER XI’ (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=50180&sectionno=164C&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_164_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[164C. Power of Central Government to make rules. -- (1) The Central Government may make`
  line `rules for the purposes of carrying into effect, the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the forms to be used for the purposes of this Chapter including,--`
  line
  line `(i) the form of the insurance policy and the particulars it shall contain as referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 147;`
  line
  line `(ii) the form for making changes in regard to the fact of transfer in the certificate of insurance`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 157;`
  line
  line `(iii) the form in which the accident information report may be prepared, the particulars it shall`
  line `contain, the manner and the time for submitting the report to the Claims Tribunal and the other`
  line `agency under section 159;`
  line
  line `(iv) the form for furnishing information under section 160; and`
  line
  line `(v) the form of the annual statement of accounts for the Motor Vehicle Accident Fund under`
  line `sub-section (7) of section 164B;`
  line
  line `(b) the making of applications for and the issue of certificates of insurance;`
  line
  line `(c) the issue of duplicates to replace certificates of insurance lost, destroyed or mutilated;`
  line
  line `(d) the custody, production, cancellation and surrender of certificates of insurance;`
  line
  line `(e) the records to be maintained by insurers of policies of insurance issued under this`
  line Chapter;
  line
  line `(f) the identification by certificates or otherwise of persons or vehicles exempted from the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(g) the furnishing of information respecting policies of insurance by insurers;`
  line
  line `(h) adopting the provisions of this Chapter to vehicles brought into India by persons making`
  line `only a temporary stay therein or to vehicles registered in a reciprocating country and operating`
  line `on any route or within any area in India by applying those provisions with prescribed`
  line modifications;
  line
  line `(i) the requirements which a certificate of insurance is required to comply with as referred to`
  line `in clause (b) of section 145;`
  line
  line `(j) administration of the Fund established under sub-section (3) of section 146;`
  line
  line `(k) the minimum premium and the maximum liability of an insurer under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 147;`
  line
  line `(l) the conditions subject to which an insurance policy shall be issued and other matters`
  line `related thereto as referred to in sub-section (3) of section 147;`
  line
  line `(m) the details of settlement, the time limit for such settlement and the procedure thereof`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 149;`
  line
  line `(n) the extent of exemptions and the modifications under the proviso to sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 158;`
  line
  line `(o) the other evidence under sub-section (5) of section 158;`
  line
  line `(p) such other agency to which the accident information report as referred to in section 159`
  line `may be submitted;`
  line
  line `(q) the time limit and fee for furnishing information under section 160;`
  line
  line `(r) the higher amount of compensation in respect of death under clause (a) of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 161;`
  line
  line `(s) a sum to be paid as interim relief as referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 161;`
  line
  line `(t) the procedure for payment of compensation under sub-section (1) of section 164;`
  line
  line `(u) such other sources from which funds may be recovered for the scheme as referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 164A;`
  line
  line `(v) any other source of income that may be credited into the Motor Vehicle Accident Fund`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 164B;`
  line
  line `(w) the persons to whom compensation may be paid under clause (d) of sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 164B;`
  line
  line `(x) the maximum liability amount under sub-section (4) of section 164B;`
  line
  line `(y) the other criteria under clause (c) of sub-section (6) of section 164B;`
  line
  line `(z) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of which provision is`
  line `to be made by rules.]`
obj_root_law_sections_164_d:
  sectionId (50181)
  sectionNo 164D
  orderNo 180
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 51, for ‘CHAPTER XI’ (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=50181&sectionno=164D&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_164_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[164D. Power of State Government to make rules. -- (1) The State Government may make rules for`
  line `the purposes of carrying into effect, the provisions of this Chapter other than the matters specified in`
  line `section 164C.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the other authority under sub-section (5) of section 147; and`
  line
  line `(b) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made by rules.]`
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (28440)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 182
  title `Claims Tribunals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 52, for "section 140 and section 163A" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28440&sectionno=165&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `constitute one or more Motor Accidents Claims Tribunals (hereafter in this Chapter referred to as Claims`
  line `Tribunal) for such area as may be specified in the notification for the purpose of adjudicating upon claims`
  line `for compensation in respect of accidents involving the death of, or bodily injury to, persons arising out of`
  line `the use of motor vehicles, or damages to any property of a third party so arising, or both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the expression "claims for`
  line `compensation in respect of accidents involving the death of or bodily injury to persons arising out of the`
  line `use of motor vehicles" includes claims for compensation under ^1[section 164].`
  line
  line `(2) A Claims Tribunal shall consist of such number of members as the State Government may think`
  line `fit to appoint and where it consists of two or more members, one of them shall be appointed as the`
  line `Chairman thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a member of a Claims Tribunal unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or has been, a Judge of a High Court, or`
  line
  line `(b) is, or has been, a District Judge, or`
  line
  line `(c) is qualified for appointment as a Judge of a High Court ^2[or as a District Judge].`
  line
  line `(4) Where two or more Claims Tribunals are constituted for any area, the State Government, may by`
  line `general or special order, regulate the distribution of business among them.`
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (28441)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 183
  title `Application for compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28441&sectionno=166&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for compensation arising out of an accident`
  line `of the nature specified in sub-section (1) of section 165 may be made--`
  line
  line `(a) by the person who has sustained the injury; or`
  line
  line `(b) by the owner of the property; or`
  line
  line `(c) where death has resulted from the accident, by all or any of the legal representatives of the`
  line `deceased; or`
  line
  line `(d) by any agent duly authorised by the person injured or all or any of the legal representatives of`
  line `the deceased, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that where all the legal representatives of the deceased have not joined in any such`
  line `application for compensation, the application shall be made on behalf of or for the benefit of all the legal`
  line `representatives of the deceased and the legal representatives who have not so joined, shall be impleaded`
  line `as respondents to the application.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that where a person accepts compensation under section 164 in accordance with`
  line `the procedure provided under section 149, his claims petition before the Claims Tribunal shall lapse.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be made, at the option of the claimant, either to the`
  line `Claims Tribunal having jurisdiction over the area in which the accident occurred or to the Claims`
  line `Tribunal within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the claimant resides or carries on business or within`
  line `the local limits of whose jurisdiction the defendant resides, and shall be in such form and contain such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *.]`
  line
  line `^4[(3) No application for compensation shall be entertained unless it is made within six months of the`
  line `occurrence of the accident.]`
  line
  line `^5[(4) The Claims Tribunal shall treat any report of accidents forwarded to it under ^6[section 159] as an`
  line `application for compensation under this Act.]`
  line
  line `^7[(5) Notwithstanding anything in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, the right of a`
  line `person to claim compensation for injury in an accident shall, upon the death of the person injured, survive`
  line `to his legal representatives, irrespective of whether the cause of death is relatable to or had any nexus with`
  line `the injury or not.]`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 53, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Proviso omitted by Act 32 of 2019, s. 53, (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 53, (w.e.f. 1-4-2022), Earlier sub-section (3) omitted by Act 54 of 1994, s. 53, (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 53, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 53, for "sub-section (6) of section 158" (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 53, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (28442)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 184
  title `Option regarding claims for compensation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28442&sectionno=167&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Workmen's Compensation Act, 1923 (8 of 1923), where the death of, or bodily injury to,`
  line `any person gives rise to a claim for compensation under this Act and also under the Workmen's`
  line `Compensation Act, 1923, the person entitled to compensation may without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `Chapter X claim such compensation under either of those Acts but not under both.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (28443)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 185
  title `Award of the Claims Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28443&sectionno=168&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of an application for compensation made`
  line `under section 166, the Claims Tribunal shall, after giving notice of the application to the insurer and after`
  line `giving the parties (including the insurer) an opportunity of being heard, hold an inquiry into the claim or,`
  line `as the case may be, each of the claims and, subject to the provisions of ^1[section 163] may make an award`
  line `determining the amount of compensation which appears to it to be just and specifying the person or`
  line `persons to whom compensation shall be paid and in making the award the Claims Tribunal shall specify`
  line `the amount which shall be paid by the insurer or owner or driver of the vehicle involved in the accident or`
  line `by all or any of them, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) The Claims Tribunal shall arrange to deliver copies of the award to the parties concerned`
  line `expeditiously and in any case within a period of fifteen days from the date of the award.`
  line
  line `(3) When an award is made under this section, the person who is required to pay any amount in terms`
  line `of such award shall, within thirty days of the date of announcing the award by the Claims Tribunal,`
  line `deposit the entire amount awarded in such manner as the Claims Tribunal may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 54, ibid, for "section 162" (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Proviso omitted by s. 54, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (28444)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 186
  title `Procedure and powers of Claims Tribunals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 55, (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28444&sectionno=169&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `(1) In holding any inquiry under section 168,`
  line `the Claims Tribunal may, subject to any rules that may be made in this behalf, follow such summary`
  line `procedure as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Claims Tribunal shall have all the powers of a Civil Court for the purpose of taking evidence`
  line `on oath and of enforcing the attendance of witnesses and of compelling the discovery and production of`
  line `documents and material objects and for such other purposes as may be prescribed; and the Claims Tribunal shall be deemed to be a Civil Court for all the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to any rules that may be made in this behalf, the Claims Tribunal may, for the purpose of`
  line `adjudicating upon any claim for compensation, choose one or more persons possessing special knowledge`
  line `of any matter relevant to the inquiry to assist it in holding the inquiry.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) For the purpose of enforcement of its award, the Claims Tribunal shall also have all the powers`
  line `of a Civil Court in the execution of a decree under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908, as if the award`
  line `were a decree for the payment of money passed by such court in a civil suit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (28445)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 187
  title `Impleading insurer in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 56, ibid., for "section 149" (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28445&sectionno=170&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `Where in the course of any inquiry, the Claims Tribunal`
  line `is satisfied that--`
  line
  line `(a) there is collusion between the person making the claim and the person against whom the`
  line `claim is made, or`
  line
  line `(b) the person against whom the claim is made has failed to contest the claim,`
  line
  line `it may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, direct that the insurer who may be liable in respect of such`
  line `claim, shall be impleaded as a party to the proceeding and the insurer so impleaded shall thereupon have,`
  line `without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (2) of ^1[section 150], the right to contest the`
  line `claim on all or any of the grounds that are available to the person against whom the claim has been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (28446)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 188
  title `Award of interest where any claim is allowed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28446&sectionno=171&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `Where any Claims Tribunal allows a claim`
  line `for compensation made under this Act, such Tribunal may direct that in addition to the amount of`
  line `compensation simple interest shall also be paid at such rate and from such date not earlier than the date of`
  line `making the claim as it may specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (28447)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 189
  title `Award of compensatory costs in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28447&sectionno=172&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Claims Tribunal adjudicating upon`
  line `any claim for compensation under this Act, may in any case where it is satisfied for reasons to be`
  line `recorded by it in writing that--`
  line
  line `(a) the policy of insurance is void on the ground that it was obtained by representation of fact`
  line `which was false in any material particular, or`
  line
  line `(b) any party or insurer has put forward a false or vexatious claim or defence,`
  line
  line `such Tribunal may make an order for the payment, by the party who is guilty of mis-representation or by`
  line `whom such claim or defence has been put forward of special costs by way of compensation to the insurer`
  line `or, as the case may be, to the party against whom such claim or defence has been put forward.`
  line
  line `(2) No Claims Tribunal shall pass an order for special costs under sub-section (1) for any amount`
  line `exceeding one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) No person or insurer against whom an order has been made under this section shall, by reason`
  line `thereof be exempted from any criminal liability in respect of such mis-representation, claim or defence as`
  line `is referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) Any amount awarded by way of compensation under this section in respect of any misrepresentation,`
  line `claim or defence, shall be taken into account in any subsequent suit for damages for`
  line `compensation in respect of such mis-representation, claim or defence.`
obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (28448)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 190
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 56, for "ten thousand" (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28448&sectionno=173&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), any person aggrieved by an award of`
  line `a Claims Tribunal may, within ninety days from the date of the award, prefer an appeal to the High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appeal by the person who is required to pay any amount in terms of such award shall`
  line `be entertained by the High Court unless he has deposited with it twenty-five thousand rupees or fifty per`
  line `cent. of the amount so awarded, whichever is less, in the manner directed by the High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the High Court may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `ninety days, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from preferring the`
  line `appeal in time.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall lie against any award of a Claims Tribunal if the amount in dispute in the appeal`
  line `is less than ^1[one lakh] rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (28449)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 191
  title `Recovery of money from insurer as arrear of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28449&sectionno=174&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `Where any amount is due from`
  line `any person under an award, the Claims Tribunal may, on an application made to it by the person entitled to the amount, issue a certificate for the amount to the Collector and the Collector shall proceed to recover`
  line `the same in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (28450)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 192
  title `Bar on jurisdiction of Civil Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28450&sectionno=175&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `Where any Claims Tribunal has been constituted for any`
  line `area, no Civil Court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any question relating to any claim for`
  line `compensation which may be adjudicated upon by the Claims Tribunal for that area, and no injunction in`
  line `respect of any action taken or to be taken by or before the Claims Tribunal in respect of the claim for`
  line `compensation shall be granted by the Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (28451)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 193
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28451&sectionno=176&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `A State Government may make rules for the`
  line `purpose of carrying into effect the provisions of sections 165 to 174, and in particular, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form of application for claims for compensation and the particulars it may contain, and the`
  line `fees, if any, to be paid in respect of such applications;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed by a Claims Tribunal in holding an inquiry under this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(c) the powers vested in a Civil Court which may be exercised by a Claims Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(d) the form and the manner in which and the fees (if any) on payment of which an appeal may be`
  line `preferred against an award of a Claims Tribunal; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (28452)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 194
  title `General provision for punishment of offences.`
  content `Whoever contravenes any provision of this Act or of any rule, regulation or notification made thereunder shall, if no penalty is provided for the offence be punishable for the first offence with fine which may extend to ^1"five hundred rupees/", and for any second or subsequent offence with fine which may extend to ^2"one thousand and five hundred rupees"..`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28452&sectionno=177&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 58, for one hundred rupees (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 58, ibid., for three hundred rupees (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_177_a:
  sectionId (49498)
  sectionNo 177A
  orderNo 195
  title `Penalty for contravention of regulations under section 118.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 59, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49498&sectionno=177A&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_177_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[177A. Penalty for contravention of regulations under section 118.--Whoever contravenes the`
  line `regulations made under section 118, shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than five`
  line `hundred rupees, but may extend to one thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (28453)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 196
  title `Penalty for travelling without pass or ticket and for dereliction of duty on the part of conductor and refusal to ply contract carriage, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes `31. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 60, for "two hundred rupees" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28453&sectionno=178&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever travels in a stage carriage without`
  line `having a proper pass or ticket with him or being in or having alighted from a stage carriage fails or refuses`
  line `to present for examination or to deliver up his pass or ticket immediately on a requisition being made`
  line `therefor, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "pass" and "ticket" have the meanings respectively assigned to them in`
  line `section 124.`
  line
  line `(2) If the conductor of a stage carriage, or the driver of a stage carriage performing the functions of a`
  line `conductor in such stage carriage, whose duty is--`
  line
  line `(a) to supply a ticket to a person travelling in a stage carriage on payment of fare by such person,`
  line `either wilfully or negligently,--`
  line
  line `(i) fails or refuses to accept the fare when tendered, or`
  line
  line `(ii) fails or refuses to supply a ticket, or`
  line
  line `(iii) supplies an invalid ticket, or`
  line
  line `(iv) supplies a ticket of a lesser value, or`
  line
  line `(b) to check any pass or ticket, either wilfully or negligently fails or refuses to do so,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) If the holder of a permit or the driver of a contract carriage refuses, in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or rules made thereunder, to ply the contract carriage or to carry the passengers, he`
  line shall,--
  line
  line `(a) in the case of two-wheeled or three-wheeled motor vehicles, be punishable with fine which`
  line `may extend to fifty rupees; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, be punishable with fine which may extend to ^1[five hundred rupees]`
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (28454)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 197
  title `Disobedience of orders, obstruction and refusal of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 61, ibid., for "five hundred rupees" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28454&sectionno=179&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever wilfully`
  line `disobeys any direction lawfully given by any person or authority empowered under this Act to give such`
  line `direction, or obstructs any person or authority in the discharge of any functions which such person or`
  line `authority is required or empowered under this Act to discharge, shall, if no other penalty is provided for`
  line `the offence be punishable with fine which may extend to ^1[two thousand rupees].`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, being required by or under this Act to supply any information, wilfully withholds such`
  line `information or gives information which he known to be false or which he does not believe to be true,`
  line `shall, if no other penalty is provided for the offence, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to one month, or with fine which may extend to ^1[two thousand rupees], or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (28455)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 198
  title `Allowing unauthorised persons to drive vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 62, ibid., for "which may extend to one thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28455&sectionno=180&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `Whenever, being the owner or person in`
  line `charge of a motor vehicle, causes, or permits, any other person who does not satisfy the provisions of`
  line `section 3 or section 4 to drive the vehicle shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three months, or with fine ^1[of five thousand rupees], or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (28456)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 199
  title `Driving vehicles in contravention of section 3 or section 4.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 63, ibid., for "which may extend to five hundred rupees" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28456&sectionno=181&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, drives a motor vehicle`
  line `in contravention of section 3 or section 4 shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three months, or with fine ^1[of five thousand rupees], or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (28457)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 200
  title `Offences relating to licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28457&sectionno=182&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, being disqualified under this Act for holding or`
  line `obtaining a driving licence drives a motor vehicle in a public place or in any other place, or applies for or`
  line `obtains a driving licence or, not being entitled to have a driving licence issued to him free of endorsement,`
  line `applies for or obtains a driving licence without disclosing the endorsement made on a driving licence`
  line `previously held by him shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `months, or with fine ^1[of ten thousand rupees] or with both, and any driving licence so obtained by him`
  line `shall be of no effect.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, being disqualified under this Act for holding or obtaining a conductors licence, acts as`
  line `a conductor of a stage carriage in a public place or applies for or obtains a conductors licence or, not`
  line `being entitled to have a conductors licence issued to him free of endorsement, applies for or obtains a`
  line `conductors licence without disclosing the endorsements made on a conductors licence previously held`
  line `by him, shall be punishable with improsonment for a term which may extend to one month, or with fine`
  line `which may extend to ^2[ten thousand rupees], or with both, and any conductors licence so obtained by him`
  line `shall be of no effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 64, ibid., for which may extend to five hundred rupees (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 64, ibid., for one hundred rupees (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_182_a:
  sectionId (28458)
  sectionNo 182A
  orderNo 201
  title `Punishment for offences relating to construction, maintenance, sale and alteration of motor vehicles and components.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 65, ibid., for section 182A (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28458&sectionno=182A&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_182_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[182A. Punishment for offences relating to construction, maintenance, sale and alteration of`
  line `motor vehicles and components.-- (1) Whoever, being a manufacturer, importer or dealer of motor`
  line `vehicles, sells or delivers or alters or offers to sell or deliver or alter, a motor vehicle that is in contravention of the provisions of Chapter VII or the rules and regulations made thereunder, shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine of one lakh rupees`
  line `per such motor vehicle or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be convicted under this section if he proves that, at the time of sale or`
  line `delivery or alteration or offer of sale or delivery or alteration of such motor vehicle, he had disclosed to`
  line `the other party the manner in which such motor vehicle was in contravention of the provisions of Chapter`
  line `VII or the rules and regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, being a manufacturer of motor vehicles, fails to comply with the provisions of Chapter`
  line `VII or the rules and regulations made thereunder, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one year or with fine which may extend to one hundred crore rupees or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever, sells or offers to sell, or permits the sale of any component of a motor vehicle which has`
  line `been notified as a critical safety component by the Central Government and which does not comply with`
  line `Chapter VII or the rules and regulations made thereunder shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to one year or with fine of one lakh rupees per such component or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever, being the owner of a motor vehicle, alters a motor vehicle, including by way of`
  line `retrofitting of motor vehicle parts, in a manner not permitted under the Act or the rules and regulations`
  line `made thereunder shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or`
  line `with fine of five thousand rupees per such alteration or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_182_b:
  sectionId (49499)
  sectionNo 182B
  orderNo 202
  title `Punishment for contravention of section 62A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 65, ibid., for section 182A (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49499&sectionno=182B&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_182_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[182B. Punishment for contravention of section 62A.--Whoever contravenes the provisions of`
  line `section 62A, shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than five thousand rupees, but may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (28459)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 203
  title `Driving at excessive speed, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28459&sectionno=183&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, drives ^1[or causes any person who is employed`
  line `by him or subjects someone under his control to drive] a motor vehicle in contravention of the speed`
  line `limits referred to in section 112 shall be punishable ^2[in the following manner, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) where such motor vehicle is a light motor vehicle with fine which shall not be less than one`
  line `thousand rupees but may extend to two thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(ii) where such motor vehicle is a medium goods vehicle or a medium passenger vehicle or a`
  line `heavy goods vehicle or a heavy passenger vehicle with fine which shall not be less than two thousand`
  line `rupees, but may extend to four thousand rupees; and`
  line
  line `(iii) for the second or any subsequent offence under this sub-section the driving licence of such`
  line `driver shall be impounded as per the provisions of the sub-section (4) of section 206.]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall be convicted of an offence punishable under sub-section (1) solely on the`
  line `evidence of one witness to the effect that in the opinion of the witness such person was driving at a speed`
  line `which was unlawful, unless that opinion is shown to be based on an estimate obtained by the use of some`
  line `mechanical ^4[or electronic] device.`
  line
  line `(4) The publication of a time table under which, or the giving of any direction that, any journey or`
  line `part of a journey is to be completed within a specified time shall, if in the opinion of the Court it is not`
  line `practicable in the circumstances of the case for that journey or part of a journey to be completed in the`
  line `specified time without contravening the speed limits referred to in section 112 be prima facie evidence`
  line `that the person who published the time table or gave the direction has committed an offence punishable`
  line `under ^5[sub-section (1)].`
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for the certain words (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (2) omitted by s. 66, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 66, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for “sub-section (2)” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (28460)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 204
  title `Driving dangerously.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28460&sectionno=184&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, drives a motor vehicle at a speed or in a manner which is`
  line `dangerous to the public ^1[or which causes a sense of alarm or distress to the occupants of the vehicle,other road users, and persons near roads,] having regard to all the circumstances of case including the`
  line `nature, condition and use of the place where the vehicle is driven and the amount of traffic which actually`
  line `is at the time or which might reasonably be expected to be in the place, shall be punishable for the first`
  line `offence with imprisonment for a term ^2[which may extend to one year but shall not be less than six`
  line `months or with fine which shall not be less than one thousand rupees but may extend to five thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both], and for any second or subsequent offence if committed within three years of the`
  line `commission of a previous similar offence with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years,`
  line `or with fine ^3[of ten thousand rupees], or with both.`
  line
  line `^4[Explanation.-- For the purpose of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) jumping a red light;`
  line
  line `(b) violating a stop sign;`
  line
  line `(c) use of handheld communications devices while driving;`
  line
  line `(d) passing or overtaking other vehicles in a manner contrary to law;`
  line
  line `(e) driving against the authorised flow of traffic; or`
  line
  line `(f) driving in any manner that falls far below what would be expected of a competent and careful`
  line `driver and where it would be obvious to a competent and careful driver that driving in that manner would`
  line `be dangerous,`
  line `shall amount to driving in such manner which is dangerous to the public.]`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 67, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 67, for “which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 67, ibid., for “which may extend to two thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 67, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (28461)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 205
  title `Driving by a drunken person or by a person under the influence of drugs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28461&sectionno=185&orderno=205&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, while`
  line `driving, or attempting to drive, a motor vehicle,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) has, in his blood, alcohol exceeding 30 mg. per 100 ml. of blood detected in a test by a`
  line `breath analyser, ^2[or in any other test including a laboratory test,] or]`
  line
  line `(b) is under the influence of a drug to such an extent as to be incapable of exercising proper`
  line `control over the vehicle.`
  line
  line `shall be punishable for the first offence with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or`
  line `with fine ^3[of ten thousand rupees], or with both; and for a second or subsequent offence, ^4*** with`
  line `imprisonment for term which may extend to two years, or with fine ^5[of fifteen thousand rupees], or with`
  line both.
  line
  line `^6[Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the expression drug means any intoxicant other`
  line `than alcohol, natural or synthetic, or any natural material or any salt, or preparation of such substance or`
  line `material as may be notified by the Central Government under this Act and includes a narcotic drug and`
  line `psychotropic substance as defined in clause (xiv) and clause (xxiii) of section 2 of the Narcotic Drugs and`
  line `Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985).]`
obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 55, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 68, ibid., for which may extend to two thousand rupees (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. The words if committed within three years of the commission of the previous similar offence, omitted by s. 68, ibid. (w.e.f.`
  line `1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 68, ibid., for which may extend to three thousand rupees (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 68, ibid., for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (28462)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 206
  title `Driving when mentally or phycically unfit to drive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28462&sectionno=186&orderno=206&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `Whoever drives a motor vehicle in any`
  line `public place when he is to his knowledge suffering from any disease or disability calculated to cause his`
  line `driving of the vehicle to be a source of danger to the public, shall be punishable for the first offence with`
  line `fine which may extend to ^1[one thousand rupees] and for a second or subsequent offence with fine which`
  line `may extend to ^2[two thousand rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 69, for “two hundred rupees” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 69, ibid., for “five hundred rupees” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (28463)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 207
  title `Punishment for offences relating to accident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28463&sectionno=187&orderno=207&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `Whoever fails to comply with the provisions`
  line `of clause ^1[(a)] of sub-section (1) of section 132 or section 133 or section 134 shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to ^2[six months], or with fine ^3[of five thousand rupees], or`
  line `with both or, if having been previously convicted of an offence under this section, he is again convicted of`
  line `an offence under this section, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ^4[one year], or with fine`
  line `^5[of ten thousand rupees], or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 70, ibid., for “(c)” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 70, ibid., for “three months” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 70, ibid., for “which may extend to five hundred rupees” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 70, ibid., for “six months” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 70, ibid., for “which may extend to one thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (28464)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 208
  title `Punishment for abetment of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28464&sectionno=188&orderno=208&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets the commission of an offence`
  line `under section 184, section 185 or section 186 shall be punishable with the punishment provided for the`
  line offence.
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (28465)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 209
  title `Racing and trials of speed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28465&sectionno=189&orderno=209&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `Whoever without the written consent of the State Government`
  line `permits or takes part in a race or trial of speed of any kind between motor vehicles in any public place`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ^1[three months], or with fine ^2[of`
  line `five thousand rupees], or with both ^3[and for a subsequent offence shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine of ten thousand rupees; or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 71, ibid., for “one month” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 71, ibid., for “which may extend to five hundred rupees” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 71, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (28466)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 210
  title `Using vehicle in unsafe condition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28466&sectionno=190&orderno=210&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who drives or causes or allows to be driven`
  line `in any public place a motor vehicle or trailer while the vehicle or trailer has any defect, which such person`
  line `knows of or could have discovered by the exercise of ordinary care and which is calculated to render the`
  line `driving of the vehicle a source of danger to persons and vehicles using such place, shall be punishable`
  line `with fine ^1[of one thousand five hundred rupees] or, if as a result of such defect an accident is caused`
  line `causing bodily injury or damage to property, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `months or with fine ^2[of five thousand rupees], or with both ^3[and for a subsequent offence shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with a fine of ten thousand`
  line `rupees for bodily injury or damage to property].`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who drives or causes or allows to be driven, in any public place a motor vehicle,`
  line `which violates the standards prescribed in relation to road safety, control of noise and air-pollution, shall`
  line `be punishable for the first offence with ^4[imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees or with both and he shall be disqualified for holding`
  line `licence for a period of three months] and for any second or subsequent offence with ^5[imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees or with`
  line both].
  line
  line `(3) Any person who drives or causes or allows to be driven, in any public place a motor vehicle which`
  line `violates the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder relating to the carriage of goods which are`
  line `of dangerous or hazardous nature to human life, shall be punishable for the first offence ^6[with a fine of`
  line `ten thousand rupees and he shall be disqualified for holding licence for a period of three months], or with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with both, and for any second or subsequent`
  line `offence with fine ^7[of twenty thousand rupees], or with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `three years, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for which may extend to two hundred and fifty rupees (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for which may extend to one thousand rupees (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 72, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for a fine of one thousand rupees (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for a fine of two thousand rupees (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for which may extend to three thousand rupees (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 72, for “which may extend to five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
