obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (28468)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 212
  title `Using vehicle without registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28468&sectionno=192&orderno=212&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `^1[192. Using vehicle without registration.--(1) Whoever drives a motor vehicle or causes or allows`
  line `a motor vehicle to be used in contravention of the provisions of section 39 shall be punishable for the first`
  line `offence with a fine which may extend to five thousand rupees but shall not be less than two thousand`
  line `rupees for a second or subsequent offence with imprisonment which may extend to one year or with fine`
  line `which may extend to ten thousand rupees but shall not be less than five thousand rupees or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for reasons to be recorded, impose a lesser punishment.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall apply to the use of a motor vehicle in an emergency for the`
  line `conveyance of persons suffering from sickness or injuries or for the transport of food or materials to`
  line `relieve distress or of medical supplies for a like purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that the persons using the vehicle reports about the same to the Regional Transport`
  line `Authority within seven days from the date of such use.`
  line
  line `(3) The court to which an appeal lies from any conviction in respect of an offence of the nature`
  line `specified in sub-section (1), may set aside or vary any order made by the court below, notwithstanding`
  line `that no appeal lies against the conviction in connection with which such order was made.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.--Use of a motor vehicle in contravention of the provisions of section 56 shall be`
  line `deemed to be a contravention of the provisions of section 39 and shall be punishable in the same manner`
  line `as provided in sub-section (1).]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 192, Central Act 59 of 1988.In Section 192 of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988 (Central`
  line `Act 59 of 1988), in its application to the State of Rajasthan, hereinafter referred to as the Principal Act,-`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), for the expression with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees as occurring`
  line `between the expression punishable for the first offence and the expression and for any second or subsequent`
  line `offence, the expression with fine which shall not be less than five thousand rupees and for the expression with`
  line `fine which may extend to three thousand rupees as occurring between the expression which may extend to six`
  line `months or and the expression or with both, the expression with fine which shall not be less than ten thousand`
  line `rupees shall be substituted, and`
  line
  line `(b) After sub-section (1) as so amended, the following proviso shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `Provided that, in a`
  line `case of contravention of the provision of section 39 or of any condition of the permit relating to the maximum`
  line `number of passengers or maximum weight of luggage that may be carried on the vehicle, the court may for any`
  line `adequate or special reason to be mentioned in the judgment, impose a fine less than that laid down in this subsection.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 2 of 1993, s. 2.]`
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 56, for section 192 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-10-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_192_a:
  sectionId (28469)
  sectionNo 192A
  orderNo 213
  title `Using vehicle without permit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28469&sectionno=192A&orderno=213&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_192_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[192A. Using vehicle without permit--- (1) Whoever drives a motor vehicle or causes or allows a`
  line `motor vehicle to be used in contravention of the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 66 or in`
  line `contravention of any condition of a permit relating to the route on which or the area in which or the`
  line `purpose for which the vehicle may be used, shall be punishable for the first offence with`
  line
  line `^2[imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months ^3[ a fine of ten thousand rupees, or with both]] and for any subsequent`
  line `offence with imprisonment which may extend to one year but shall not be less than ^4[six months] or with`
  line `fine ^5[of ten thousand rupees] or with both:`
  line
  line ^6******
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall apply to the use of a motor vehicle in an emergency for the`
  line `conveyance of persons suffering from sickness or injury or for the transport of materials for repair or for`
  line `the transport of food or materials to relieve distress or of medical supplies for a like purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person using the vehicle reports about the same to the Regional Transport Authority`
  line `within seven days from the date of such use.`
  line
  line `(3) The court to which an appeal lies from any conviction in respect of an offence of the nature`
  line `specified in sub-section (1), may set aside or vary any order made by the court below, notwithstanding`
  line `that no appeal lies against the conviction in connection with which such order was made.]`
obj_root_law_sections_192_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 56, for section 192 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2.. Ins. by s. 75, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for "and a fine of ten thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 13-01-2025).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 75,ibid., for "three months" (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 75, ibid., for "which may extend to ten thousand rupees but shall not be less than five thousand rupees"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Proviso omitted by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 13-01-2025).`
obj_root_law_sections_192_b:
  sectionId (50183)
  sectionNo 192B
  orderNo 214
  title `Offences relating to registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 76 (w.e.f. 1-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=50183&sectionno=192B&orderno=214&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_192_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[192B. Offences relating to registration.--- (1) Whoever, being the owner of a motor vehicle, fails to`
  line `make an application for registration of such motor vehicle under sub-section (1) of section 41 shall be`
  line `punishable with fine of five times the annual road tax or one-third of the lifetime tax of the motor vehicle`
  line `whichever is higher.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, being a dealer, fails to make an application for the registration of a new motor vehicle`
  line `under the second proviso to sub-section (1) of section 41 shall be punishable with fine of fifteen times the`
  line `annual road tax or the lifetime tax of the motor vehicle whichever is higher.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever, being the owner of a motor vehicle, obtains a certificate of registration for such vehicle`
  line `on the basis of documents which were, or by representation of facts which was, false in any material`
  line `particular, or the engine number or the chassis number embossed thereon are different from such number`
  line `entered in the certificate of registration shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not`
  line `be less than six months but may extend to one year and with fine equal to ten times the amount of the`
  line `annual road tax or two-third the lifetime tax of the motor vehicle, whichever is higher.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever, being a dealer, obtains a certificate of registration for such vehicle on the basis of`
  line `documents which were, or by representation of facts which was, false in any material particular, or the`
  line `engine number or the chassis number embossed thereon are different from such number entered in the`
  line `certificate of registration shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six`
  line `months but may extend to one year and with fine equal to ten times the amount of annual road tax or twothird the lifetime tax of the motor vehicle, whichever is higher.]`
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (28470)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 215
  title `Punishment of agents, canvassers and aggregators without proper authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28470&sectionno=193&orderno=215&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `193. Punishment of ^1[agents, canvassers and aggregators] without proper authority.--Whoever`
  line `engages himself as an agent or canvasser in contravention of the provisions of section 93 or of any rules`
  line `made thereunder shall be punishable for the first offence with fine ^2[of one thousand rupees] and for any`
  line `second or subsequent offence with imprisonment which may extend to six months, or with fine ^3[of two`
  line `thousand rupees], or with both.`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Whoever engages himself as an aggregator in contravention of the provisions of section 93 or of`
  line `any rules made there under shall be punishable with fine up to one lakh rupees but shall not be less than`
  line `twenty-five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever, while operating as an aggregator contravenes a condition of the licence granted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 93, not designated by the State Government as a material condition, shall be`
  line `punishable with fine of five thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 77, ibid., for "agents and canvassers " (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 77, ibid., for "which may extend to one thousand rupees " (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 77, ibid., for "which may extend to two thousand rupees " (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 77, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (28471)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 216
  title `Driving vehicle exceeding permissible weight.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28471&sectionno=194&orderno=216&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Whoever drivers a motor vehicle or`
  line `causes or allows a motor vehicle to be drives in contravention of the provisions of section 113 or section`
  line `114 or section 115 shall be punishable with ^2*** fine ^3[of twenty thousand rupees and an additional`
  line `amount of two thousand rupees per tonne of excess load], together with the liability to pay charges for`
  line `off-loading of the excess load.]`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that such motor vehicle shall not be allowed to move before such excess load is removed`
  line `or is caused or allowed to be removed by the person in control of such motor vehicle.]`
  line
  line `^4[(1A) Whoever drives a motor vehicle or causes or allows a motor vehicle to be driven when such`
  line `motor vehicle is loaded in such a manner that the load or any part thereof or anything extends laterally`
  line `beyond the side of the body or to the front or to the rear or in height beyond the permissible limit shall be`
  line `punishable with a fine of twenty thousand rupees, together with the liability to pay charges for off-loading`
  line `of such load:`
  line
  line `Provided that such motor vehicle shall not be allowed to move before such load is arranged in a`
  line `manner such that there is no extension of the load laterally beyond the side of the body or to the front or`
  line `to the rear or in height beyond the permissible limit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this sub-section shall apply when such motor vehicle has been given`
  line `an exemption by the competent authority authorised in this behalf, by the State Government or the Central`
  line `Government, allowing the carriage of a particular load.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any driver of a vehicle who refuses to stop and submit his vehicle to weighing after being`
  line `directed to do so by an officer authorised in this behalf under section 114 or removes or causes the`
  line `removal of the load or part of it prior to weighing shall be punishable with fine 5`
  line `[of forty thousand`
  line rupees].
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 57, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `2. The word minimum omitted by Act 32 of 2019, s. 78 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 78, ibid., for of two thousand rupees and an additional amount of one thousand rupees per tonne of excess load`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 78. ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 78, ibid., for which may extend to three thousand rupees (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_194_a:
  sectionId (49500)
  sectionNo 194A
  orderNo 217
  title `Carriage of excess passengers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 79, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49500&sectionno=194A&orderno=217&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_194_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[194A. Carriage of excess passengers.-- Whoever drives a transport vehicle or causes or allows a`
  line `transport vehicle to be driven while carrying more passengers than is authorised in the registration`
  line `certificate of such transport vehicle or the permit conditions applicable to such transport vehicle shall be`
  line `punishable with a fine of two hundred rupees per excess passenger:`
  line
  line `Provided that such transport vehicle shall not be allowed to move before the excess passengers are`
  line `off-loaded and an alternative transport is arranged for such passengers.]`
obj_root_law_sections_194_b:
  sectionId (49501)
  sectionNo 194B
  orderNo 218
  title `Use of safety belts and the seating of children.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 79, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49501&sectionno=194B&orderno=218&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_194_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[194B. Use of safety belts and the seating of children.-- (1) Whoever drives a motor vehicle without`
  line `wearing a safety belt or carries passengers not wearing seat belts shall be punishable with a fine of one`
  line `thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government, may by notification in the Official Gazette, exclude the`
  line `application of this sub-section to transport vehicles to carry standing passengers or other specified classes`
  line `of transport vehicles.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever drives a motor vehicle or causes or allows a motor vehicle to be driven with a child who,`
  line `not having attained the age of fourteen years, is not secured by a safety belt or a child restraint system`
  line `shall be punishable with a fine of one thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_194_c:
  sectionId (49502)
  sectionNo 194C
  orderNo 219
  title `Penalty for violation of safety measures for motor cycle drivers and pillion riders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 79, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49502&sectionno=194C&orderno=219&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_194_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[194C. Penalty for violation of safety measures for motor cycle drivers and pillion riders.--`
  line `Whoever drives a motor cycle or causes or allows a motor cycle to be driven in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of section 128 or the rules or regulations made thereunder shall be punishable with a fine of`
  line `one thousand rupees and he shall be disqualified for holding licence for a period of three months.]`
obj_root_law_sections_194_d:
  sectionId (49504)
  sectionNo 194D
  orderNo 220
  title `Penalty for not wearing protective headgear`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 79, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49504&sectionno=194D&orderno=220&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_194_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[194D. Penalty for not wearing protective headgear.-- Whoever drives a motor cycle or causes or`
  line `allows a motor cycle to be driven in contravention of the provisions of section 129 or the rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder shall be punishable with a fine of one thousand rupees and he shall be`
  line `disqualified for holding licence for a period of three months.]`
obj_root_law_sections_194_e:
  sectionId (49505)
  sectionNo 194E
  orderNo 221
  title `Failure to allow free passage to emergency vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 79, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49505&sectionno=194E&orderno=221&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_194_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[194E. Failure to allow free passage to emergency vehicles.-- Whoever while driving a motor`
  line `vehicle fails to draw to the side of the road, on the approach of a fire service vehicle or of an ambulance`
  line `or other emergency vehicle as may be specified by the State Government, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with a fine of ten thousand rupees or with`
  line both.]
obj_root_law_sections_194_f:
  sectionId (49506)
  sectionNo 194F
  orderNo 222
  title `Use of horns and silence zones.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 79, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49506&sectionno=194F&orderno=222&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_194_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[194F. Use of horns and silence zones.-- Whoever--`
  line
  line `(a) while driving a motor vehicle--`
  line
  line `(i) sounds the horn needlessly or continuously or more than necessary to ensure safety, or`
  line
  line `(ii) sounds the horn in an area with a traffic sign prohibiting the use of a horn, or`
  line
  line `(b) drives a motor vehicle which makes use of a cut-out by which exhaust gases are released other`
  line `than through the silencer,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with a fine of one thousand rupees and for a second or subsequent offence with a fine`
  line `of two thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_195:
  sectionId (28472)
  sectionNo (195)
  orderNo 223
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_195_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28472&sectionno=195&orderno=223&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_195_content:
  string
  line `195. [Imposition of minimum fine under certain circumstances.]--Omitted by Act The Motor Vehicles`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2019 (32 of 2019), s. 80 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_196:
  sectionId (28473)
  sectionNo (196)
  orderNo 224
  title `Driving uninsured vehicle.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_196_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28473&sectionno=196&orderno=224&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line `Whoever drives a motor vehicle or causes or allows a motor`
  line `vehicle to be driven in contravention of the provisions of section 146 shall be punishable ^1[for the first`
  line `offence] with imprisonment which may extend to three months, or with fine ^2[of two thousand rupees], or`
  line `with both ^1[, and for a subsequent offence shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three months, or with fine of four thousand rupees, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 81. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 81, ibid., for “which may extend to one thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  sectionId (28474)
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 225
  title `Taking vehicle without authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28474&sectionno=197&orderno=225&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever takes and drives away any motor vehicle`
  line `without having either the consent of the owner thereof or other lawful authority shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to three months or with fine ^1[of five thousand rupees], or with both.`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be convicted under this section if the Court is satisfied that such person`
  line `acted in the reasonable belief that he had lawful authority or in the reasonable belief that the owner would`
  line `in the circumstances of the case have given his consent if he had been asked therefor.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, unlawfully by force or threat of force or by any other form of intimidation, seizes or`
  line `exercises control of a motor vehicle, shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three`
  line `months, or with fine ^1[of five thousand rupees], or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever attempts to commit any of the acts referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) in`
  line `relation to any motor vehicle, or abets the commission of any such act, shall also be deemed to have`
  line `committed an offence under sub-section (1) or, as the case may be, sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 82, ibid., for "which may extend to five hundred rupees” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 83, ibid., for “with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees” (w.e.f 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  sectionId (28475)
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 226
  title `Unauthorised interference with vehicle.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 83, ibid., for “with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees” (w.e.f 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28475&sectionno=198&orderno=226&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line `Whoever otherwise than with lawful authority or`
  line `reasonable execuse enters or mounts any stationary motor vehicle or tampers with the brake or any part of`
  line `the mechanism of a motor vehicle shall be punishable ^1[with fine of one thousand rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_198_a:
  sectionId (49507)
  sectionNo 198A
  orderNo 227
  title `Failure to comply with standards for road design, construction and maintenance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 84, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49507&sectionno=198A&orderno=227&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_198_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[198A. Failure to comply with standards for road design, construction and maintenance.--(1)`
  line `Any designated authority, contractor, consultant or concessionaire responsible for the design or construction or maintenance of the safety standards of the road shall follow such design, construction and`
  line `maintenance standards, as may be prescribed by the Central Government from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) Where failure on the part of the designated authority, contractor, consultant or concessionaire`
  line `responsible under sub-section (1) to comply with standards for road design, construction and`
  line `maintenance, results in death or disability, such authority or contractor or concessionaire shall be`
  line `punishable with a fine which may extend to one lakh rupees and the same shall be paid to the Fund`
  line `constituted under section 164B.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of sub-section (2), the court shall in particular have regard to the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the characteristics of the road, and the nature and type of traffic which was reasonably`
  line `expected to use it as per the design of road;`
  line
  line `(b) the standard of maintenance norms applicable for a road of that character and use by such`
  line traffic;
  line
  line `(c) the state of repair in which road users would have expected to find the road;`
  line
  line `(d) whether the designated authority responsible for the maintenance of the road knew, or could`
  line `reasonably have been expected to know, that the condition of the part of the road to which the action`
  line `relates was likely to cause danger to the road users;`
  line
  line `(e) whether the designated authority responsible for the maintenance of the road could not`
  line `reasonably have been expected to repair that part of the road before the cause of action arose;`
  line
  line `(f) whether adequate warning notices through road signs, of its condition had been displayed; and`
  line
  line `(g) such other matters as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the term “contractor” shall include sub-contractors`
  line `and all such persons who are responsible for any stage in the design, construction and maintenance of a`
  line `stretch of road.]`
obj_root_law_sections_199:
  sectionId (28476)
  sectionNo (199)
  orderNo 228
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28476&sectionno=199&orderno=228&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_199_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company, for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the contravention and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any punishment`
  line `provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company, and it is proved that the offence was committed with the consent or connivance`
  line `of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the`
  line `company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_199_a:
  sectionId (49508)
  sectionNo 199A
  orderNo 229
  title `Offences by juveniles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 85 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49508&sectionno=199A&orderno=229&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_199_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[199A. Offences by juveniles.--(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `juvenile, the guardian of such juvenile or the owner of the motor vehicle shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `the contravention and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall render such guardian or owner liable to any punishment`
  line `provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the Court shall presume that the use of the motor`
  line `vehicle by the juvenile was with the consent of the guardian of such juvenile or the owner of the motor`
  line `vehicle, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the penalty under sub-section (1), such guardian or owner shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and with a fine of twenty-five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) and sub-section (2) shall not apply to such guardian or owner if`
  line `the juvenile committing the offence had been granted a learner's licence under section 8 or a driving`
  line `licence and was operating a motor vehicle which such juvenile was licensed to operate.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a juvenile, the registration of the motor`
  line `vehicle used in the commission of the offence shall be cancelled for a period of twelve months.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a juvenile, then, notwithstanding`
  line `section 4 or section 7, such juvenile shall not be eligible to be granted a driving licence under section 9 or`
  line `a learner's licence under section 8 until such juvenile has attained the age of twenty-five years.`
  line
  line `(6) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a juvenile, then such juvenile shall be`
  line `punishable with such fines as provided in the Act while any custodial sentence may be modified as per the`
  line `provisions of the Juvenile Justice Act, 2000 (56 of 2000).]`
obj_root_law_sections_199_b:
  sectionId (49509)
  sectionNo 199B
  orderNo 230
  title `Revision of fines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 85 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49509&sectionno=199B&orderno=230&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_199_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[199B. Revision of fines.-- The fines as provided in this Act shall be increased by such amount not`
  line `exceeding ten per cent. in value of the existing fines, on an annual basis on 1st day of April of each year`
  line `from the date of commencement of the Motor Vehicles (Amendment) Act, 2019(32 of 2018), as may be notified by`
  line `the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_200:
  sectionId (28477)
  sectionNo (200)
  orderNo 231
  title `Composition of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_200_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28477&sectionno=200&orderno=231&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_200_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Any offence whether committed before or after the`
  line `commencement of this Act punishable under section 177, section 177A, section 178, section 179, section`
  line `180, section 181, section 182, sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of section 182A,`
  line `section 182B, sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 183, clause (c) of the Explanation to section`
  line `184, section 186, section 189, sub-section (2) of section 190, section 192, section 192A, sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 192B, section 194, section 194A, section 194B, section 194C, section 194D, section 194E, section`
  line `194F, section 196, section 198 and section 201, may, either before or after the institution of the`
  line `prosecution, be compounded by such officers or authorities and for such amount as the State Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf.]`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the State Government may, in addition to such amount, require the offender to`
  line `undertake a period of community service.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where an offence has been compounded under sub-section (1), the offender, if in custody, shall be`
  line `discharged and no further proceedings shall be taken against him in respect of such offence:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that notwithstanding compounding under this section, such offence shall be deemed to be`
  line `a previous commission of the same offence for the purpose of determining whether a subsequent offence`
  line `has been committed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that compounding of an offence will not discharge the offender from proceedings`
  line `under sub-section (4) of section 206 or the obligation to complete a driver refresher training course, or the`
  line `obligation to complete community service, if applicable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 13-01-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 86, (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_201:
  sectionId (28478)
  sectionNo (201)
  orderNo 232
  title `Penalty for causing obstruction to free flow of traffic.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_201_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28478&sectionno=201&orderno=232&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_201_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever keeps a ^1*** vehicle on`
  line `any public place, in such a manner, so as to cause impediment to the free flow of traffic, shall be liable for`
  line `penalty up to ^2[five hundred rupees], so long as it remains in that position:`
  line
  line `Provided that the vehicle involved in accidents shall be liable for penalty only from the time of`
  line `completion of inspection formalities under the law.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that where the vehicle is removed by ^4[an agency authorised by the Central`
  line `Government or State Government, removal charges] shall be recovered from the vehicle owner or person`
  line `in-charge of such vehicle.]`
  line
  line `^5[(2) Penalties or ^6[removal charges] under this section shall be recovered by such officer or authority`
  line `as the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, authorise.]`
  line
  line `^7[(3) sub-section (1) shall not apply where the motor vehicle has suffered an unforeseen breakdown`
  line `and is in the process of being removed.]`
  line
  line `^8[Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, “removal charges” includes any costs involved in`
  line `the removal of the motor vehicle from one location to another and also includes any costs related to`
  line `storage of such motor vehicle.]`
obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word “disabled” omitted by s. 87, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 87, ibid., for “fifty rupees per hour” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 59 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 87, for “a Government agency, towing charges” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 59, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 87, for “towing charges” (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 87, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_202:
  sectionId (28479)
  sectionNo (202)
  orderNo 233
  title `Power to arrest without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_202_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 60, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28479&sectionno=202&orderno=233&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_202_content:
  string
  line `(1) A police officer in uniform may arrest without warrant`
  line `any person who in his presence commits an offence punishable under section 184 or section 185 or`
  line `section 197:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person so arrested in connection with an offence punishable under section 185`
  line `shall, within two hours of his arrest, be subjected to a medical examination referred to in sections 203 and`
  line `204 by a registered medical practitioner failing which he shall be released from custody.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) A police officer in uniform may arrest without warrant any person, who has committed an`
  line `offence under this Act, if such person refuses to give his name and address.]`
  line
  line `(3) A police officer arresting without warrant the driver of a motor vehicle shall if the circumstances`
  line `so require take or cause to be taken any steps he may consider proper for the temporary disposal of the`
  line vehicle.
obj_root_law_sections_203:
  sectionId (28480)
  sectionNo (203)
  orderNo 234
  title `Breath tests.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_203_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 61, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28480&sectionno=203&orderno=234&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_203_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) A police officer in uniform or an officer of the Motor Vehicles Department,`
  line `as may be authorised in this behalf by that Department, may require any person driving or attempting to`
  line `drive a motor vehicle in a public place to provide one or more specimens of breath for breath test there or`
  line `nearby, if such police officer or officer has any reasonable cause to suspect him of having committed an`
  line `offence under section 185:`
  line
  line `Provided that requirement for breath test shall be made (unless, it is made) as soon as reasonably`
  line `practicable after the commission of such offence.]`
  line
  line `(2) If a motor vehicle is involved in an accident in a public place and a police officer in uniform has`
  line `any reasonable cause to suspect that the person who was driving the motor vehicle at the time of the`
  line `accident, had alcohol in his blood or that he was driving under the influence of a drug referred to in`
  line `section 185 he may require the person so driving the motor vehicle, to provide a specimen of his breath`
  line `for a breath test:--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a person who is at a hospital as an indoor patient, at the hospital,`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other person, either at or near the place where the requirement is made, or,`
  line `if the police officer thinks fit, at a police station specified by the police officer:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person shall not be required to provide such a specimen while at a hospital as an`
  line `indoor patient if the registered medical practitioner in immediate charge of his case is not first`
  line `notified of the proposal to make the requirement or objects to the provision of a specimen on the ground that its provision or the requirement to provide it would be prejudicial to the proper care or`
  line `treatment of the patient.`
  line
  line `(3) If it appears to a police officer in uniform, in consequence of a breath test carried out by him on`
  line `any person under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), that the device by means of which the test has been`
  line `carried out indicates the presence of alcohol in the person’s blood, the police officer may arrest that`
  line `person without warrant except while that person is at a hospital as an indoor patient.`
  line
  line `(4) If a person, required by a police officer under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) to provide a`
  line `specimen of breath for a breath test, refuses or fails to do so and the police officer has reasonable cause to`
  line `suspect him of having alcohol in his blood, the police officer may arrest him without warrant except while`
  line `he is at a hospital as an indoor patient.`
  line
  line `(5) A person arrested under this section shall while at a police station, be given an opportunity to`
  line `provide a specimen of breath for a breath test there.`
  line
  line `(6) The results of a breath test made in pursuance of the provisions of this section shall be admissible`
  line `in evidence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, “breath test”, means a test for the purpose of`
  line `obtaining an indication of the presence of alcohol in a person’s blood carried out, on one or more`
  line `specimens of breath provided by that person, by means of a device of a type approved by the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, for the purpose of such a test.`
obj_root_law_sections_204:
  sectionId (28481)
  sectionNo (204)
  orderNo 235
  title `Laboratory test.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_204_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28481&sectionno=204&orderno=235&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_204_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person, who has been arrested under section 203 may, while at a police`
  line `station, be required by a police officer to provide to such registered medical practitioner as may be`
  line `produced by such police officer, a specimen of his blood for a Laboratory test,--`
  line
  line `(a) it appears to the police officer that the device, by means of which breath test was taken in`
  line `relation to such person, indicates the presence of alcohol in the blood of such person, or`
  line
  line `(b) such person, when given the opportunity to submit to a breath test, has refused, omitted or`
  line `failed to do so:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the person required to provide such specimen is a female and the registered`
  line `medical practitioner produced by such police officer is a male medical practitioner, the specimen shall be`
  line `taken only in the presence of a female, whether a medical practitioner or not.`
  line
  line `(2) A person while at a hospital as an indoor patient may be required by a police officer to provide at`
  line `the hospital a specimen of his blood for a laboratory test:--`
  line
  line `(a) if it appears to the police officer that the device by means of which test is carried out in`
  line `relation to the breath of such person indicates the presence of alcohol in the blood of such person, or`
  line
  line `(b) if the person having been required, whether at the hospital or elsewhere, to provide a`
  line `specimen of breath for a breath test, has refused, omitted or failed to do so and a police officer has`
  line `reasonable cause to suspect him of having alcohol in his blood:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person shall not be required to provide a specimen of his blood for a laboratory test`
  line `under this sub-section if the registered medical practitioner in immediate charge of his case is not first`
  line `notified of the proposal to make the requirement or objects to the provision of such specimen on the`
  line `ground that its provision or the requirement to provide it would be prejudicial to the proper care or`
  line `treatment of the patient.`
  line
  line `(3) The results of a laboratory test made in pursuance of this section shall be admissible in evidence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "laboratory test" means the analysis of a specimen of`
  line `blood made at a laboratory established, maintained or recognised by the Central Government or a State`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_205:
  sectionId (28482)
  sectionNo (205)
  orderNo 236
  title `Presumption of unfitness to drive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_205_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28482&sectionno=205&orderno=236&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_205_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding for an offence punishable under section`
  line `185 if it is proved that the accused, when requested by a police officer at any time so to do, had refused,`
  line `omitted or failed to consent to the taking of or providing a specimen of his breath for a breath test or a`
  line `specimen of his blood for a laboratory test, his refusal, omission or failure may, unless reasonable cause`
  line `therefor is shown, be presumed to be a circumstance supporting any evidence given on behalf of the`
  line `prosecution, or rebutting any evidence given on behalf of the defence, with respect to his condition at that`
  line time.
obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_206:
  sectionId (28483)
  sectionNo (206)
  orderNo 237
  title `Power of police officer to impound document.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_206_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 88 (w.e.f. 1-10-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28483&sectionno=206&orderno=237&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_206_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any police officer or other person`
  line `authorised in this behalf by the State Government may, if he has reason to believe that any identification`
  line `mark carried on a motor vehicle or any licence, permit, certificate of registration, certificate of insurance`
  line `or other document produced to him by the driver or person in charge of a motor vehicle is a false`
  line `document within the meaning of section 464 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), seize the mark or`
  line `document and call upon the driver or owner of the vehicle to account for his possession of or the presence`
  line `in the vehicle of such mark or document.`
  line
  line `(2) Any police officer or other person authorised in this behalf by the State Government may, if he`
  line `has reason to believe that the driver of amotor vehicle who is charged with any offence under this Act`
  line `may abscond or otherwise avoid the service of a summons, seize any licence held by such driver and`
  line `forward it to the Court taking cognizance of the offence and the said Court shall on the first appearance of such driver before it, return the licence to him in exchange for the temporary acknowledgment given`
  line `under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(3) A police officer or other person seizing a licence under sub-section (2) shall give to the person`
  line `surrendering the licence a temporary acknowledgment therefor and such acknowledgment shall authorise`
  line `the holder to drive until the licence has been returned to him or until such date as may be specified by the`
  line `police officer or other person in the acknowledgment, whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any magistrate, police officer or other person authorised by the State Government in`
  line `this behalf is, on an application made to him, satisfied that the licence cannot be, or has not been, returned`
  line `to the holder thereof before the date specified in the acknowledgment for any reason for which the holder`
  line `is not responsible, the magistrate, police officer or other person, as the case may be, may extend the`
  line `period of authorization to drive to such date as may be specified in the acknowledgment.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) A police officer or other person authorised in this behalf by the State Government shall, if he has`
  line `reason to believe that the driver of a motor vehicle has committed an offence under any of sections 183,`
  line `184, 185, 189, 190, 194C, 194D, or 194E, seize the driving licence held by such driver and forward it to`
  line `the licensing authority for disqualification or revocation proceedings under section 19:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person seizing the licence shall give to the person surrendering the licence a`
  line `temporary acknowledgement therefor, but such acknowledgement shall not authorise the holder to drive`
  line `until the licence has been returned to him.]`
obj_root_law_sections_207:
  sectionId (28484)
  sectionNo (207)
  orderNo 238
  title `Power to detain vehicles used without certificate of registration permit, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_207_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28484&sectionno=207&orderno=238&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_207_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any police`
  line `officer or other person authorised in this behalf by the State Government may, if he has reason to believe`
  line `that a motor vehicle has been or is being used in contravention of the provisions of section 3 or section 4`
  line `or section 39 or without the permit required by sub-section (1) of section 66 or in contravention of any`
  line `condition of such permit relating to the route on which or the area in which or the purpose for which the`
  line `vehicle may be used, seize and detain the vehicle, in the prescribed manner and for this purpose take or`
  line `cause to be taken any steps he may consider proper for the temporary safe custody of the vehicle:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such officer or person has reason to believe that a motor vehicle has been or`
  line `is being used in contravention of section 3 or section 4 or without the permit required by sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 66 he may, instead of seizing the vehicle, seize the certificate of registration of the vehicle and`
  line `shall issue an acknowledgment in respect thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a motor vehicle has been seized and detained under sub-section (1), the owner or person in`
  line `charge of the motor vehicle may apply to the transport authority or any officer authorised in this behalf by`
  line `the State Government together with the relevant documents for the release of the vehicle and such`
  line `authority or officer may, after verification of such documents, by order release the vehicle subject to such`
  line `conditions as the authority or officer may deem fit to impose.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 207, Central Act 59 of 1988.—In the proviso to sub-section (1) of Section`
  line `207 of the principal Act, the expression “or without the permit required by sub- section (1) of Section 66”`
  line `as occurring between the expression “Section 3 or section 4” and the expression “he may” shall be`
  line deleted.
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 2 of 1993, s. 3.]`
obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_208:
  sectionId (28485)
  sectionNo (208)
  orderNo 239
  title `Summary disposal of cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_208_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28485&sectionno=208&orderno=239&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_208_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court taking cognizance of any offence (other than an`
  line `offence which the Central Government may by rules specify in this behalf) under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) may, if the offence is an offence punishable with imprisonment under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(ii) shall, in any other case,`
  line
  line `state upon the summons to be served on the accused person that he--`
  line
  line `(a) may appear by pleader or in person; or`
  line
  line `(b) may, by a specified date prior to the hearing of the charge, plead guilty to the charge and remit`
  line `to the Court, by money order, such sum (not exceeding the maximum fine that may be imposed for`
  line `the offence) as the Court may specify, and the plea of guilt indicated in the money order coupon`
  line `itself:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court shall, in the case of any of the offences referred to in sub-section (2), state`
  line `upon the summons that the accused person, if he pleads guilty, shall so plead in the manner specified in`
  line `clause (b) and shall forward his driving licence to the Court with his letter containing such plea.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the offence dealt with in accordance with sub-section (1) is an offence specified by the`
  line `Central Government by rules for the purposes of this sub-section, the Court shall, if the accused person`
  line `pleads guilty to the charge and forward his driving licence to the Court with the letter containing his plea,`
  line `make an endorsement of such conviction on his driving licence.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an accused person pleads guilty and remits the sum specified and has complied with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1), or as the case may be, sub-sections (1) and (2), no further proceedings in`
  line `respect of the offence shall be taken against him nor shall he be liable, notwithstanding anything to the`
  line `contrary contained in this Act, to be disqualified for holding or obtaining a licence by reason of his having`
  line `pleaded guilty.`
obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_209:
  sectionId (28486)
  sectionNo (209)
  orderNo 240
  title `Restriction on conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_209_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28486&sectionno=209&orderno=240&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_209_content:
  string
  line `No person prosecuted for an offence punishable under section 183`
  line `or section 184 shall be convicted unless--`
  line
  line `(a) he was warned at the time the offence was committed that the question of prosecuting him`
  line `would be taken into consideration, or`
  line
  line `(b) within fourteen days from the commission of the offence, a notice specifying the nature of the`
  line `offence and the time and place where it is alleged to have been committed was served on or sent by registered post to him or the person registered as the owner of the vehicle at the time of the`
  line `commission of the offence, or`
  line
  line `(c) within twenty-eight days of the commission of the offence, a summons for the offence was`
  line `served on him:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing, in this section shall apply where the Court is satisfied that--`
  line
  line `(a) the failure to serve the notice or summons referred to in this sub-section was due to the fact`
  line `that neither the name and address of the accused nor the name and address of the registered owner of`
  line `the vehicle could with reasonable diligence have been ascertained in time, or`
  line
  line `(b) such failure was brought about by the conduct of the accused.`
obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_210:
  sectionId (28487)
  sectionNo (210)
  orderNo 241
  title `Courts to send intimation about conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_210_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28487&sectionno=210&orderno=241&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_210_content:
  string
  line `Every Court by which any person holding a`
  line `driving licence is convicted of an offence under this Act or of an offence in the commission of which a`
  line `motor vehicle was used, shall send intimation to--`
  line
  line `(a) the licensing authority which issued the driving licence, and`
  line
  line `(b) the licensing authority by whom the licence was last renewed,`
  line
  line `and every such intimation shall state the name and address of the holder of the licence, the licence`
  line `number, the date of issue and renewal of the same, the nature of the offence, the punishment awarded for`
  line `the same and such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_210_a:
  sectionId (49510)
  sectionNo 210A
  orderNo 242
  title `Power of State Government to increase penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_210_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 89 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49510&sectionno=210A&orderno=242&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_210_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[210A. Power of State Government to increase penalties.--Subject to conditions made by the`
  line `Central Government, a State Government, shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify a`
  line `multiplier, not less than one and not greater than ten, to be applied to each fine under this Act and such`
  line `modified fine, shall be in force in such State and different multipliers may be applied to different classes`
  line `of motor vehicles as may be classified by the State Government for the purpose of this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_210_b:
  sectionId (49511)
  sectionNo 210B
  orderNo 243
  title `Penalty for offence committed by an enforcing authority`
  content obj_root_law_sections_210_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 89 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49511&sectionno=210B&orderno=243&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_210_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[210B. Penalty for offence committed by an enforcing authority.-- Any authority that is`
  line `empowered to enforce the provisions of this Act shall, if such authority commits an offence under this`
  line `Act, shall be liable for twice the penalty corresponding to that offence under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_210_c:
  sectionId (49512)
  sectionNo 210C
  orderNo 244
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_210_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 89 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49512&sectionno=210C&orderno=244&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_210_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[210C. Power of Central Government to make rules.--The Central Government may make rules`
  line for--
  line
  line `(a) design, construction and maintenance standards for National highways;`
  line
  line `(b) such other factors as may be taken into account by the Court under sub-section (3) of section`
  line 198A;
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is, or has to be, prescribed by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_210_d:
  sectionId (49513)
  sectionNo 210D
  orderNo 245
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_210_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 89 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49513&sectionno=210D&orderno=245&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_210_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[210D. Power of State Government to make rules.-- The State Government may make rules for`
  line `design, construction and maintenance standards for roads other than national highways, and for any other`
  line `matter which is, or may be, prescribed by the State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_211:
  sectionId (28488)
  sectionNo (211)
  orderNo 246
  title `Power to levy fee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_211_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28488&sectionno=211&orderno=246&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_211_content:
  string
  line `Any rule which the Central Government or the State Government is`
  line `empowered to make under this Act may, notwithstanding the absence of any express provision to that`
  line `effect, provide for the levy of such fees in respect of applications, amendment of documents, issue of`
  line `certificates, licences, permits, tests, endorsements, badges, plates, countersignatures, authorisation, supply`
  line `of statistics or copies of documents or orders and for any other purpose or matter involving the rendering`
  line `of any service by the officers or authorities under this Act or any rule made thereunder as may be`
  line `considered necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government may, if it considers necessary so to do, in the public interest, by`
  line `general or special order, exempt any class of persons from the payment of any such fee either in part or in`
  line full.
obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_211_a:
  sectionId (50184)
  sectionNo 211A
  orderNo 247
  title `Use of electronic forms and documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_211_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 90 (w.e.f. 1-10-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=50184&sectionno=211A&orderno=247&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_211_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[211A. Use of electronic forms and documents.--(1) Where any provision of this Act or the rules`
  line `and regulations made there under provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the filing of any form, application or any other document with any office, authority, body or`
  line `agency owned or controlled by the Central Government or the State Government in a particular`
  line manner;
  line
  line `(b) the issue or grant of any licence, permit, sanction, approval or endorsement, by whatever name`
  line `called in a particular manner; or`
  line
  line `(c) the receipt or payment of money in a particular manner, then notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in such provision, such requirement shall be deemed to have been satisfied if such filing,issue, grant, receipt or payment, as the case may be, is effected by means of such electronic form as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government or the State Government shall, for the purpose of sub-section (1),`
  line prescribe--
  line
  line `(a) the manner and format in which such electronic forms and documents shall be filed, created or`
  line `issued; and`
  line
  line `(b) the manner or method of payment of any fee or charges for filing, creation or issue of any`
  line `electronic document under clause (a).]`
obj_root_law_sections_212:
  sectionId (28489)
  sectionNo (212)
  orderNo 248
  title `Publication, commencement and laying of rules and notifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_212_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28489&sectionno=212&orderno=248&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_212_content:
  string
  line `(1) The power to make`
  line `rules under this Act is subject to the condition of the rules being made after previous publication.`
  line
  line `(2) All rules made under this Act shall be published in the Official Gazette, and shall unless some`
  line `later date is appointed, come into force on the date of such publication.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by any State Government shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made before`
  line `the State Legislature.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act, every scheme made by the Central`
  line `Government under sub-section (1) of section 75 and sub-section (1) of section 163 and every notification`
  line `issued by the Central Government under sub-section (4) of section 41, sub-section (1) of section 58,`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 59, the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 112,`
  line `^1[section 118] ^2[sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 163A]`
  line `^3[section 164, section 177A] and sub-section (4) of section 213 shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the rule, scheme or notification or both Houses agree that the rule or`
  line `scheme should not be made or the notification should not be issued, the rule, scheme or notification shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule, scheme or notification.`
  line
  line `^1[(5) Every notification issued by the State Government under section 210A shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or`
  line `where such Legislature consists of one House, before that House, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before`
  line `the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, the`
  line `House agrees or both Houses agree, as the case may be, in making any modification in the notification or`
  line `the House agrees or both Houses agree, as the case may be, that the notification should not be issued, the`
  line `notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 54 of 1994, s. 62 (w.e.f. 14-11-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-10-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_213:
  sectionId (28490)
  sectionNo (213)
  orderNo 249
  title `Appointment of motor vehicles officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_213_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28490&sectionno=213&orderno=249&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_213_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, for the purpose of`
  line `carrying into effect the provisions of this Act, establish a Motor Vehicles Department and appoint as`
  line `officers thereof such persons as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such officer shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may make rules to regulate the discharge by officers of the Motor Vehicles`
  line `Department of their functions and in particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing`
  line `power to prescribe the uniform to be worn by them, the authorities to which they shall be subordinate, the`
  line `duties to be performed by them, the powers (including the powers exercisable by police officers under`
  line `this Act) to be exercised by them, and the conditions governing the exercise of such powers.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, having regard to the objects of the Act, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, prescribe the minimum qualifications which the said officers or any class thereof shall`
  line `possess for being appointed as such.`
  line
  line `(5) In addition to the powers that may be conferred on any officer of the Motor Vehicles Department`
  line `under sub-section (3), such officer as may be empowered by the State Government in this behalf shall`
  line `also have the power to,--`
  line
  line `(a) make such examination and inquiry as he thinks fit in order to ascertain whether the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder are being observed;`
  line
  line `(b) with such assistance, if any, as he thinks fit, enter, inspect and search any premises which is in`
  line `the occupation of a person who, he has reason to believe, has committed an offence under this Act or`
  line `in which a motor vehicle in respect of which such offence has been committed is kept:`
  line
  line `Provided that,--`
  line
  line `(i) any such search without a warrant shall be made only by an officer of the rank of a`
  line `gazetted officer;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the offence is punishable with fine only the search shall not be made after sunset`
  line `and before sunrise;`
  line
  line `(iii) where the search is made without a warrant, the gazetted officer concerned shall record`
  line `in writing the grounds for not obtaining a warrant and report to his immediate superior that such`
  line `search has been made;`
  line
  line `(c) examine any person and require the production of any register or other document maintained`
  line `in pursuance of this Act, and take on the spot or otherwise statements of any person which he may`
  line `consider necessary for carrying out the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) seize or take copies of any registers or documents or portions thereof as he may consider`
  line `relevant in respect of an offence under this Act which he has reason to believe has been committed;`
  line
  line `(e) launch prosecutions in respect of any offence under this Act and to take a bond for ensuring`
  line `the attendance of the offender before any court;`
  line
  line `(f) exercise such other powers as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be compelled under this sub-section to answer any question or make`
  line `any statement tending to incriminate himself.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall, so far as may be apply`
  line `to any search or seizure under this section as they apply to any search or seizure under the authority of`
  line `any warrant issued under section 94 of that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_214:
  sectionId (28491)
  sectionNo (214)
  orderNo 250
  title `Effect of appeal and revision on orders passed by original authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_214_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28491&sectionno=214&orderno=250&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_214_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an appeal`
  line `has been preferred or an application for revision has been made against any order passed by an original authority under this Act, the appeal or the application for revision shall not operate as a stay of the order`
  line `passed by the original authority and such order shall remain in force pending the disposal of the appeal or`
  line `the application for revision, as the case may be, unless the prescribed appellate authority or revisional`
  line `authority otherwise directs.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if an application made by a person for the`
  line `renewal of permit has been rejected by the original authority and such person has preferred an appeal or`
  line `made an application for revision under this Act against such rejection, the appellate authority or, as the`
  line `case may be, the revisional authority may by order direct that the permit shall, notwithstanding the`
  line `expiration of the term specified therein, continue to be valid until the appeal or application for revision is`
  line `disposed of.`
  line
  line `(3) No order made by a competent authority under this Act shall be reversed or altered on appeal or`
  line `revision on account of any error, omission or irregularity in the proceedings, unless it appears to the`
  line `prescribed appellate authority or revisional authority, as the case may be, that such error, omission or`
  line `irregularity has, in fact, occasioned a failure of justice.`
obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_215:
  sectionId (28492)
  sectionNo (215)
  orderNo 251
  title `Road Safety Councils and Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_215_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 13-01-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28492&sectionno=215&orderno=251&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_215_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, constitute for the country a National Road Safety Council consisting of a Chairman`
  line `and such other members as that Government considers necessary and on such terms and conditions as that`
  line `Government may determine.`
  line
  line `(2) A State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute for the State a State`
  line `Road Safety Council consisting of a Chairman and such other members as that Government considers`
  line `necessary and on such terms and conditions as that Government may determine.`
  line
  line `(3) A State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute District Road Safety`
  line `Committee for each district in the State consisting of a Chairman and such other members as that`
  line `Government considers necessary and on such terms and conditions as that Government may determine.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that where a State Government has not constituted the District Road Safety Committee,`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute a Committee for such`
  line `District, consisting of a Chairman and such other members as it considers necessary and on such terms`
  line `and conditions as it may determine.]`
  line
  line `(4)The Councils and Committees referred to in this section shall discharge such functions relating to`
  line `the road safety programmes as the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be,`
  line `may, having regard to the objects of the Act, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_215_a:
  sectionId (49514)
  sectionNo 215A
  orderNo 252
  title `Power of Central Government and State Government to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_215_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49514&sectionno=215A&orderno=252&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_215_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[215A. Power of Central Government and State Government to delegate.--Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government shall have the power to delegate any power or functions that have`
  line `been conferred upon it by the Act to any public servant or public authority and authorise such public`
  line `servant or public authority to discharge any of its powers, functions and duties under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the State Government shall have the power to delegate any power or functions that have been`
  line `conferred upon it by the Act to any public servant or public authority and authorise such public`
  line `servant or public authority to discharge any of its powers, functions and duties under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_215_b:
  sectionId (49515)
  sectionNo 215B
  orderNo 253
  title `National Road Safety Board`
  content obj_root_law_sections_215_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49515&sectionno=215B&orderno=253&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_215_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[215B. National Road Safety Board.--(1) The Central Government shall, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, constitute a National Road Safety Board consisting of a Chairman, such number of`
  line `representatives from the State Governments, and such other members as it may consider necessary and on`
  line `such terms and conditions as may be prescribed by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(2) The National Board shall render advice to the Central Government or State Government, as the`
  line `case may be, on all aspects pertaining to road safety and traffic management including, but not limited`
  line to,--
  line
  line `(a) the standards of design, weight, construction, manufacturing process, operation and`
  line `maintenance of motor vehicles and of safety equipment;`
  line
  line `(b) the registration and licensing of motor vehicles;`
  line
  line `(c) the formulation of standards for road safety, road infrastructure and control of traffic;`
  line
  line `(d) the facilitation of safe and sustainable utilisation of road transport ecosystem;`
  line
  line `(e) the promotion of new vehicle technology;`
  line
  line `(f) the safety of vulnerable road users;`
  line
  line `(g) programmes for educating and sensitising drivers and other road users; and`
  line
  line `(h) such other functions as may be prescribed by the Central Government from time to time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_215_c:
  sectionId (49516)
  sectionNo 215C
  orderNo 254
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_215_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49516&sectionno=215C&orderno=254&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_215_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[215C. Power of Central Government to make rules.--(1) The Central Government may make`
  line `rules for the purposes of carrying into effect the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for--`
  line `(a) the use of electronic forms and means for the filing of documents, issue or grant of licence,`
  line `permit, sanction, approval or endorsements and the receipt or payment of money as referred to in`
  line `section 211A;`
  line
  line `(b) the minimum qualifications which the Motor Vehicles Department officers or any class`
  line `thereof shall be required to possess for appointment as such, as referred to in sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 213;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms and conditions of appointment of Chairman and Members of the National Road`
  line `Safety Board under sub-section (1) of section 215B;`
  line
  line `(d) the other functions of the National Road Safety Board under sub-section (2) of section 215B;`
  line and
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made by rules by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_215_d:
  sectionId (49517)
  sectionNo 215D
  orderNo 255
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_215_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2019, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=49517&sectionno=215D&orderno=255&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_215_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[215D. Power of State Government to make rules.-- (1) The State Government may make rules for`
  line `the purposes of carrying into effect, the provisions of this Chapter, other than the matters specified in`
  line `section 215C.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the use of electronic forms and means for the filing of documents, issue or grant of licence,`
  line `permit, sanction, approval or endorsements and the receipt or payment of money as referred to in`
  line `section 211A;`
  line
  line `(b) the duties and functions of the officers of the Motor Vehicle Department, the powers to be`
  line `exercised by such officers (including the powers exercisable by police officers under this Act) and the`
  line `conditions governing the exercise of such powers, the uniform to be worn by them, the authorities to`
  line `which they shall be subordinate as referred to in sub-section (3) of section 213;`
  line
  line `(c) such other powers as may be exercised by officers of the Motor Vehicles Department as`
  line `referred to in clause (f) of sub-section (5) of section 213; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made by rules by the State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_216:
  sectionId (28493)
  sectionNo (216)
  orderNo 256
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_216_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28493&sectionno=216&orderno=256&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_216_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of three years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
