obj_root_law_sections_217:
  sectionId (28494)
  sectionNo (217)
  orderNo 257
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_217_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286&sectionId=28494&sectionno=217&orderno=257&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00009_198859_1517807326286
obj_root_law_sections_217_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Motor Vehicles Act, 1939 (4 of 1939) and any law corresponding`
  line `to that Act in force in any State immediately before the commencement of this Act in that State (hereafter`
  line `in this section referred to as the repealed enactments) are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal by sub-section (1) of the repealed enactments,--`
  line
  line `(a) any notification, rule, regulation, order or notice issued, or any appointment or declaration`
  line `made, or exemption granted, or any confiscation made, or any penalty or fine imposed, any forfeiture,`
  line `cancellation or any other thing done, or any other action taken under the repealed enactments, and in`
  line `force immediately before such commencement shall, so far as it is not inconsistent with the`
  line `provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been issued, made, granted, done or taken under the`
  line `corresponding provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any certificate of fitness or registration or licence or permit issued or granted under the`
  line `repealed enactments shall continue to have effect after such commencement under the same`
  line `conditions and for the same period as if this Act had not been passed;`
  line
  line `(c) any document referring to any of the repealed enactments or the provisions thereof, shall be`
  line `construed as referring to this Act or to the corresponding provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the assignment of distinguishing marks by the registering authority and the manner of display`
  line `on motor vehicles in accordance with the provision of the repealed enactments shall, after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, continue to remain in force until a notification under sub-section (6) of`
  line `section 41 of this Act is issued;`
  line
  line `(e) any scheme made under section 68C of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1939 (4 of 1939) or under the`
  line `corresponding law, if any, in force in any State and pending immediately before the commencement`
  line `of this Act shall be disposed of in accordance with the provisions of section 100 of this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) the permits issued under sub-section (1A) of section 68F of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1939`
  line `(4 of 1939), or under the corresponding provision, if any, in force in any State immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall continue to remain in force until the approved scheme under Chapter`
  line `VI of this Act is published.`
  line
  line `(3) Any penalty payable under any of the repealed enactments may be recovered in the manner`
  line `provided by or under this Act, but without prejudice to any action already taken for the recovery of such`
  line `penalty under the repealed enactments.`
  line
  line `(4) The mention of particular matters in this section shall not be held to prejudice or affect the general`
  line `application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), with regard to the effect of`
  line repeals.
obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes:
  string
  line
